title: pinwheel snacks
directions: Lightly spray a 8 or 9 inch square pan with no-stick cooking spray.
Use paper towel to spread on bottom and sides.
Mix gelatin and water in a 1 1/2 to 2 quart microwaveable bowl.
Microwave on high 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir to dissolve completely.
(Cooking time varies with ovens.)
Add marshmallows to gelatin.
Microwave 1 minute or until marshmallows are almost melted.
Stir until completely melted and mixture is smooth.
(Creamy layer will float on top.)
Pour into prepared pam.
Refrigerate 45 minutes or until set.
Loosen edges using knife dipped in warm water.
Starting at one end, roll up tightly, jelly-roll fashion.
With seam down, slice in 1/2-inch slices.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: date loaf
directions: Sift dry ingredients together three times.
Sift over fruit and nut mixture.
Add beaten egg yolks; fold in stiffly beaten egg whites to which vanilla has been added.
Let stand 30 minutes. Mix again.
Line angel food pan or loaf pan with wax paper. Grease; pack batter lightly in pan.
Cover top with foil.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours; remove foil and bake 15 minutes.

title: tin plate special(western)
directions: Wash beans; cover with cold water overnight.
Bring to boil and cook 1 hour.
Drain and discard water.
Brown meat in hot fat in Dutch oven or roaster.
Add pepper and onions.
Cook to tender. Add beans and remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours or until beans are tender.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: party sandwiches
directions: Brown meat, add spices and cheese.
Spread on rye bread slices.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: clippership soup
directions: Steam chopped onion and sliced zucchini in 1/2 water until tender.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add cooked pasta and V-8 juice; simmer for 5 minutes.
Cover top with Parmesan cheese. Stir into soup.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and remaining ingredients.
Mix together and set jello.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel, core and slice apples into a bowl. Add 1/2 cup sugar, all spices and lemon juice.
Mix lightly and pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Blend remaining sugar, flour, salt and butter to a crumbly consistency.
Bake for 45 minutes or until apples are tender and crust is nicely browned. Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: superb cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrots, onion and rice in mixing bowl. Blend remaining ingredients; add to rice mixture and toss lightly. Chill.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pete's favorite relish
directions: Still have zukes to eat?
Tired of eating them?
Try this relish; keeps well for one year.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Peel and quarter apples.
Arrange in overlapping rows in pie shell
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Add 1/4 cup butter; mix with a fork until it becomes crumbly.
Spoon over apples.
Spread sour cream over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: In a plastic bowl with tight lid, combine pudding mix, sugar, cinnamon and pecans.
Pour butter into a shallow bowl.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Dip pieces in butter, then place in bowl. Cover and shake.
Remove and place in a greased 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan 30 minutes before inverting into a serving plate.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: watermelon rind preserves
directions: Cut up watermelon rind.
Let soak until sugar melts.
Add lemon peel from 1 lemon and juice to it.
Let soak until juice forms, then slice lemon real thin and cook until its candied.
Put in jars and seal.
Good to use in fruit cake.
Takes several hours to cook. Use as a preserve also.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 10-inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven back to 325° and continue baking until lightly brown, 20 minutes.

title: beef ala stroganoff
directions: Simmer all ingredients on top of stove for 1 1/2 hours.
Just before serving, add 1 cup sour cream.
May be served over noodles or pasta of your choice.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Salt and pepper both sides of each piece of chicken.
Roll each piece in melted butter.
Then into the potato flakes.
Bake at 350 degrees in a glass dish until golden brown about 30-45 minutes.

title: texas goulash
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter until soft.
Add ground beef and stir until brown.
Add rice, tomatoes, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.
This freezes well.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each one.
Add part of flour.
Add part of milk; beat well.
Add the rest of ingredients and beat well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cut in sugar and Crisco real good.
Add eggs, vanilla and flour.
Mix well, then knead real good.
Roll, then cut out and bake at 325° until brown.
These are real good.

title: peanut butter oatmeal squares
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients.
Add egg, peanut butter, soda and vanilla.
Mix well, then add flour and oats.
Stir until well blended.
Pack mixture in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook until vegetables are done.

title: cereal candy
directions: Heat butterscotch bits and peanut butter in saucepan until bits are melted.
Pour over Special K.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer in order listed on
a large plate.
Serve with taco chips.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and make into small balls.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until brown.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and milk.
Cook until forms ball in cool water.
Add vanilla and butter.
Beat until turns dull in color. Pour into buttered pan.
Cut in squares.

title: butterscotch eclair
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with graham crackers.
(Do not crush.)
Mix 2 small boxes vanilla instant pudding, 3 cups milk and add 1 (12 ounce) Cool Whip.
Mix well and spread a part of this mixture over graham crackers.
Layer another layer of graham crackers, then repeat mixture.
On top add another layer of graham crackers.
Chill at this point.
Slightly heat a container of cake frosting (your choice) in microwave.
I use butterscotch cake frosting.
When pudding mix is cooled, drizzle about 1/2 the container of frosting mix.
Put in refrigerator to stay cool.

title: crab salad
directions: Boil rotini noodles until tender, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients and mix, then chill and serve.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown half the beef in its own fat in a large skillet. Transfer to a kettle or Dutch oven and repeat with the other half. Rinse the skillet with a cup of water and add the liquid to the meat.
Cover and cook slowly over low heat.
Fry the onions; stir in paprika and salt.
Add to the meat.
Stir in the green peppers and cook for 2 hours until meat is tender, not soft.
Serve with soft noodles.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Combine cabbage and onions, set aside. Combine almonds, sesame seeds and Ramen noodles, set aside. Combine remaining ingredients. When ready to serve, mix all of above together.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken with salt until tender, then pick off bone.
Add cream of chicken soup to chicken.
Cook spaghetti until tender. Also cook carrots and celery until tender in 2 separate kettles. Drain and combine chicken and soup mixture, noodles and vegetables.
Mix well and serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, raisins, sunflower kernels or nuts and bacon. Combine mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar and add to broccoli mixture. Toss well and refrigerate.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicago cheese spread
directions: Mix and serve at room temperature.
Mound on plate or in bowl to serve.
It's fairly salty.
Serve on wheat crackers or bagel chips.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put all in covered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix pickles, onions, green and red peppers and salt well. Cover with ice.
Set, covered with ice, for 3 hours.
Make sure there is plenty of ice water to cover.
In large cooking pans, mix vinegar, sugar, turmeric and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil and add pickles.
Do not rinse, just drain off water from pickles. Bring to a simmer.
Do not boil pickles.
Put in sterilized jars.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and melted oleo.
Pat mixture into cake pan; save 1/2 cup of mixture to put on top of cake.

title: basic white sauce
directions: Heat butter.
Blend in flour until smooth.
Gradually add soup stock, stirring constantly.
Bring to boiling point.
Cook for 3 more minutes.
Add cream and seasoning.

title: banana chip bars
directions: Cream butter and both sugars together until thoroughly blended and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add creamed mixture gradually, beat well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread in greased and floured 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars and enjoy!

title: frank's old new orleans gourmet stuffed bell peppers
directions: First, cut the tops off the bell peppers, remove the seeds and wash them well inside and out.
Then place them into lightly salted boiling water and cook them until they just begin to wilt slightly.
Do not overcook!

title: golden rum cake
directions: Mix together in mixer the cake mix, eggs, water, oil and rum, blending well. Stir in pecans. Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichoke hearts, cheese and bell peppers; set aside. Press garlic clove into a bowl and add mayonnaise, green onion and oregano; mix. Add artichoke, cheese and pepper to this mixture.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Chop chicken, onion and eggs; mix with pepper and salt and place in the bottom of a 3-quart casserole.
Layer Veg-All, soups and broth over the chicken.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased griddle or into frying pan with a little oil.
Cook as you would pancakes.
Serve with syrup.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together and cook at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash and cook in small amount of water until tender. Saute onion in melted margarine.
Add to squash.
Add cheese and mix well.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Crumble cornbread and cover bottom of casserole dish.
Add squash mixture.
Cover top with cornbread.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients using a blender, food processor or mixer.
Process until smooth.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Dot with extra sharp Cracker Barrel cheese, just before finished baking.

title: baby cheese cake
directions: Butter 4 miniature pans (muffin pans).
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs in the pan.
Shake pan to get them on bottom and sides.
Mix cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar and 3 egg yolks.
Beat 3 egg whites stiff; fold into mixture.
Fill pan almost full.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; remove from oven and let cool.
They will fall in the middle.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in flat baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover top with miniature marshmallows.
Return to oven and bake just long enough to melt marshmallows.

title: lazy day peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk and pour onto melted margarine.
Add peaches.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: slim baked potatoes
directions: Prick potatoes with fork.
Bake 425° for 55 to 60 minutes. While potatoes are baking, melt butter in small saucepan.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Keep warm until potatoes are done.

title: chicken salad
directions: When chicken is cool and cut-up, add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Will keep in refrigerator several days.
Makes a good sandwich or eat on lettuce leaf.

title: fudgy oatmeal candy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in heavy boiler.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Mix thoroughly and drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: g.i.s.o.s. - all you past, present and future soldiers take note!
directions: Saute ground beef and onion in skillet.
Add bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Pour in desired amount of milk.
Thicken with flour and water mixture.
Serve over toast.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl with electric mixer for 10 to 15 seconds.
Add coconut.
Pour mixture into buttered deep 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.

title: individual salad
directions: Rip 2 leaves of lettuce to fit in a salad bowl.
Put in salad bowl.
Cut a piece of cucumber into small pieces.
Add to salad bowl.
Cut a baby tomato and put in salad, if desired.
Cut up broccoli and put in salad bowl, if desired.
Add croutons.
Add and mix salad dressing of your choice.

title: meringue kisses
directions: Beat whites of eggs until stiff.
Add gradually sugar and cream of tartar plus vanilla.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Heat oven to 350°.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Turn off oven as soon as you put cookies in oven.
Take out when oven is cool or about 1 hour.

title: strawberry angel squares
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add juice from berries; heat, bringing to a boil.
Cool.
Cut the cake into squares.
Put 1/2 in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Whip 1 pint whipping cream.
Add sugar.
Fold in berries and gelatin mixture.
Put 1/2 of this over cake in pan. Repeat with other 1/2 of cake and cream mixture.
Served with whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli cheese bake
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets and stems into pieces.
Parboil and drain.
Place in casserole dish.
Combine soup, milk and cheese. Pour over broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wackie cake
directions: Pour over dry ingredients and mix with fork until smooth. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: shower punch
directions: Allow sherbet to soften slightly.
Place in punch bowl.
Pour sprite over; mix and serve.

title: salmon (or tuna) yule log
directions: Drain and flake salmon (or tuna).
Add cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish, liquid smoke and salt.
Combine well. Chill for several hours or overnight.
Shape into a log.
Chill for 2-3 hours.
Sprinkle pecans on wax paper and roll log in pecans to cover.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.
This may be kept in the refrigerator for several days.

title: easy casserole
directions: Favorite cheese may be sprinkled on top last few minutes of cooking time.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Saute beef and drain. Add all other ingredients except macaroni.
Bring to a good boil. Simmer for 30 to 40 minutes. Add cooked macaroni.
Let stand until cool. Add cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Light oven; get out utensils and ingredients.
Remove blocks and toy autos from table.
Grease pan and crack nuts.

title: salad dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in quart jar.
Shake vigorously until blended.
Let set 12 to 24 hours before using to give flavor a chance to set.

title: pork and peaches(crock-pot)
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot except pork roast. Add pork roast. Cook on high for 8 hours.

title: chunky chicken casserole
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package, using chicken broth instead of water. Add 1/2 cup more liquid than called for and omit butter. (I use broth from boiling the chicken breasts or whole chicken, whichever you use.) To cooked rice mixture, add the remaining ingredients with the exception of the cheese. Pour mixture into casserole. Top with grated cheese to cover mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: strawberry-apple rhubarb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix rhubarb, strawberries, apples, sugar and tapioca in large bowl and let stand for 15 minutes. Prepare pie crust according to the package for two-crust pie, using a 9-inch pie pan. Fill with fruit mixture and then dot margarine on top of filling. Cover with top pie crust, seal and flute edges. Cut slits or designs in top crust to permit steam to escape. Sprinkle a small amount of granulated sugar on top crust and cover fluted edge with foil. Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until juices bubble and crust is golden brown.

title: chocolate monkey
directions: Blend in blender the chocolate milk and creme de cocoa.
Add banana.
Blend until smooth.
Add ice cubes, one by one.
Blend until smooth.
Pour in glass top with chocolate wafers (crushed) or chocolate chips.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together.
Add a little milk to make it moist. Add egg yolks and mix well. Add remaining milk and cook until thick. Add flavoring.

title: impossible cake
directions: Place all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
Whisk until smooth.
Pour into a buttered 10-inch pie dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Comes out in layers, pastry, custard and coconut.

title: chicken and rice casserole(diabetic)
directions: Cook rice until tender and fluffy. Combine soup and broth in a small saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until smooth. Add chicken, rice and parsley to soup mixture.
Mix well.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: sunburst yam bake
directions: Arrange yams in
a circle in a 9-inch pie plate.
Place pineapple in center. Sprinkle a bit of cinnamon and nutmeg on top of yams. Dot yams and pineapple with marmalade.
Top with marshmallows. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate custard cake
directions: Combine cocoa and oil in small bowl; stir well and set aside. Combine sugar and next 4 ingredients in electric blender.
Process at medium until smooth.
With blender running, pour cocoa mix into blender; process until smooth.
Pour into large bowl.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Boil and crush sweet potatoes.
Add sugar, crushed pineapple, raisins, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, melted butter and pecans.
Bake in a Pyrex dish at 350° for 30 minutes until lightly golden brown. Cool on wire rack.
Then add marshmallows on top and bake for 10 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop onto hot griddle to desired size.
Cook until bubbly; turn and cook 1 to 2 minutes longer.

title: veg-all chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Spoon into crust.
Cover with top crust and brush with egg.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until brown.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: linguica dip
directions: Fry linguica and save fat from pan.
Grind together on fine blade.
Mix all other ingredients together, then add to linguica. Chill and serve with your favorite crackers.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla to milk.
Alternate milk with flour which has been sifted with salt, soda and cocoa. The alternating begins with flour and ends with flour, thus dividing the milk in thirds and the flour in fourths.
Add boiling water all at once and stir until well combined.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 12-inch pan for 45 minutes or until done.
Bake layer pans for 30 minutes or until done.
This is a large, moist cake.
It will keep well.

title: texas hash casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, peppers and onions.
Add salt and pepper. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add water.
Pour into two 9-inch pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 325° and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: jello strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add water and cook until clear.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Cool, add berries and refrigerate.
Pour into cold pie shell.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Top with whipped cream.

title: frozen fancy
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix well with sugar.
Add remaining ingredients (except for bananas) and mix well.
Stir in bananas by hand.
Chill in refrigerator for several hours.
(If this makes more than you need, you can freeze or freeze in muffin pans in paper cupcake cups and take out as you need it.)

title: pasta salad
directions: Cut up vegetables while pasta is cooking.
Cool pasta by running cold water over it.

Mix all the pasta and vegetables together. Sprinkle the dry dressing on top and then mix it. Depending on how much rotini is used, pour on the bottle dressing approximately 8-10 oz. per 9 oz. of rotini.

title: one-step farmhouse chicken stew
directions: Place chicken pieces in deep kettle.
Melt butter in large saucepan; blend in flour.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Pour over chicken.
Cover; simmer 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican beans
directions: Combine beans.
Fold in green pepper, celery, onion, chili sauce, catsup, garlic salt and brown sugar.
Place in a 4-quart casserole.
Cover top with bacon strips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel oatmeal chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Combine oats, flour, brown sugar, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in margarine; mix until well blended.
Reserve 1 cup.
Press remaining onto bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.
Top with nuts and chocolate chips.
Mix caramel topping and 1/4 cup of flour until smooth.
Drizzle over chocolate pieces.
Sprinkle with reserved oat mixture.
Bake additional 18 to 22 minutes, then cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix cooked chicken, sliced celery, minced onion, cream of chicken soup, salt, pepper and ginger.
Blend lemon juice, Miracle Whip and chicken broth.
Mix with chicken.
Add cashew nuts, boiled eggs and Chinese noodles.
Bake at 450° in greased casserole for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with 2 cups of potato chips. Bake 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; crumble into small pieces.
Combine the broccoli, bacon, onions and raisins in a large bowl.
In a separate small bowl, blend together the mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over the broccoli salad.
Marinate for 1 to 3 hours. Add the pecans just before serving.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice and cook carrots.
Mix sugar, mustard, soup, vinegar and oil.
Add bell pepper and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over cooled carrots and mix lightly.
Marinate overnight.

title: barbara's chocolate sauce
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar in a saucepan, adding milk a little at a time.
Add margarine.
Cook over low heat and stir until mixture comes to a good boil.
Serve while warm.

title: chicken little fingers
directions: Cut chicken into 1/4-inch strips.
Combine next 9 ingredients. Add chicken, mixing until well coated.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Drain chicken thoroughly.
Combine bread crumbs and sesame seed, mixing well.
Add chicken and toss to coat.
Place chicken in 2 greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dishes.
Combine margarine and shortening and brush on chicken.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with Plum Sauce.
Yields 12 to 14 appetizer servings.

title: elegant eggnog
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat, in another bowl, egg yolks, sugar and salt until very thick and lemon colored.
Stir in rum.
Fold egg yolk mixture into whipped cream.
Fold egg whites into egg yolk-cream mixture.
Chill.

title: cocktail chestnuts
directions: Heat ketchup, molasses, brown sugar and soy sauce on burner top until well mixed.

title: christmas biscuits
directions: Sift the flour and baking soda together.
Set aside.
Cream the butter until softened. Add the sugar gradually, creaming until fluffy.
Add the eggs in thirds, beating well after each addition. Alternately add the dry ingredients in fourths and the sour cream in thirds to the creamed mixture, mixing until blended after each addition.
Chill dough overnight.

title: papaya seed dressing
directions: Place vinegar and dry ingredients in blender and gradually blend in onion and papaya seed.

title: mexican dish
directions: Cook hamburger meat and onion.
Drain. Add soup, taco sauce and green chilies.
Crumble taco shells in casserole.
Pour meat mixture over shells.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.
The last 5 or 10 minutes, add 2 cups of grated cheese on top.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Combine 1/3 cup soup and 1/4 cup milk; set aside.
On waxed paper lightly coat chicken with flour.
Dip into soup mixture.
On another piece of waxed paper, coat chicken with stuffing.
Arrange chicken on baking sheet.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine.
Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir once while baking.

title: virginia's chicken gumbo salad
directions: Soften Knox gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water.
Add 1/4 cup boiling water to dissolve.
Mix mayonnaise with celery, pepper and pimento, then add all the other ingredients.
Pour into salad mold.
Chill.

title: holiday pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add green pepper, onion, pineapple, seasoned salt and one cup chopped pecans; mix well.
Shape into ball and roll in remaining pecans.
Chill for several hours; serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.
Keeps for a week or more in the refrigerator or one can be frozen.

title: hearty upstate minestrone soup
directions: Slice sausage into 1/2-inch pieces; brown in oil in Dutch oven.
Drain sausage and save a little oil mixture with sausage drippings.
Add onion, garlic, carrots and basil and cook 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add zucchini, tomatoes with liquid, bouillon, cabbage, salt, pepper and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 1 hour.
Add beans with liquid; cook another 20 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.
A meal in itself, this soup tastes better the second day.

title: chicken kiev
directions: In a small bowl with rubber scraper, thoroughly mix butter, parsley, thyme, garlic, salt and pepper.
In foil, shape into 6-inch square.
Freeze until firm, about 40 minutes.

title: soup texas-style(low-fat)
directions: In large pan, cook turkey, onion and garlic until meat is browned; drain off fat.
Add tomatoes, corn, chilies, water, broth, chili powder and bay leaf.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes. Add zucchini; simmer 5 to 10 minutes more or until zucchini is tender.

title: chili sausages
directions: Heat
chili
sauce and jelly together in electric skillet. After
heated
through, add sausages and/or franks.
May be served in this pan, keeping them warm.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into boiling broth.
Cook 20 minutes in a covered pot.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain hamburger.
Add salt, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder (can add more chili powder, if desired).
Add tomatoes; let simmer 15 minutes.
Add beans; let get hot again while mixing cornbread.
Follow directions on box. Pour beans into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish or pan.
Spoon cornbread over top.
Bake like cornbread.

title: lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Scramble ground round, onion and bell pepper until done.
Drain.
Then add Prego sauce and spaghetti mix. Cook noodles and drain.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked 8 or 9-inch pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°, then 1 hour at 250°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, almonds, chestnuts, celery, seasonings, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Combine onion rings and cheese and sprinkle over chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in a skillet with onion.
Mix pineapple juice and ketchup; pour over chops.
Cover and cook on low heat until tender.
Can be baked in oven for 45 minutes.

title: chocolava cookies
directions: Combine flour white sugar, brown sugar,
cocoa, baking powder, and salt. Add butter. (Mixture will be crumbly.) Add egg whites and vanilla.

title: frosty treasures
directions: In a bowl, combine the oil and chocolate chips.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes or until the chocolate melts.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour the mixture over Crispix cereal in a large bowl.
Place confectioners sugar into a gallon-size plastic bag. Shake to coat bag.
Then add coated cereal and close bag tightly. Shake bag until cereal is coated.
Refrigerate in airtight container.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla; add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda together; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Spread half of batter in a 10-inch tube pan that has been greased and lined on the bottom with waxed paper.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage. Put in 9 x 12 baking dish. Beat eggs and add salt and pepper. Pour over sausage. Break up bread and sprinkle over sausage and egg mix. Pour 1/2 cup milk over bread. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sandies
directions: Cream together oleo and powdered sugar.
Add vanilla, nuts, water and flour.
Bake until lightly browned on ungreased baking sheet.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.
Heat oven to 300°.

title: quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spinach as directed.
Drain and stir in mushrooms.
Mix eggs and half and half together; add half of the cheese.
Stir in spinach and mushrooms.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake 45 minutes or until crust is brown and cheese is raised.

title: country potatoes
directions: Mix butter, soup, onion, cheese, sour cream and salt and pepper together.
In large baking dish, add liquid mixture to potatoes.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 35 to 45 minutes.
It's done when sides get crispy.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off grease.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: caramelized apples
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add brown sugar; heat on medium until starts to caramelize. Add sliced apples and turn fire down. Cook until apples are tender.

title: snicker pie
directions: Put yogurt in large bowl, let stand until workable.
Sprinkle with pudding mix; add peanut butter and Grape-Nuts.
Mash with potato masher until well blended.
Then fold in Cool Whip.
Mix real well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass pan and freeze until serving time.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs, sour cream, oil and corn. Blend cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Combine the two and mix well.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in an 8 x 8 or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Serve warm.
Reheats very well.

title: potato rolls
directions: Scald milk and let cool.
Make instant potatoes and let cool. Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Beat eggs in large bowl. Add sugar, salt and Crisco; then blend with mixer.
While blending, add yeast, potatoes and scalded milk.
Slowly add flour to mix while
mixing.
When mixture is thick and tacky, set in warm water, covered with damp cloth for approximately 1 1/2 hours. Makes about 1 dozen.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta 8 to 10 minutes, until tender.
Drain and place in cold water until cool.
Drain again and place in bowl.
Add vegetables and dressing.
Serve now or place in refrigerator.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat egg yolks with a whisk.
Add the milk to egg yolks and mix well.
Mix cornstarch with sugar.
Add this to the egg mixture.
Cook until it thickens, then add
margarine, vanilla and coconut.
Pour this in a baked pie crust.

title: hot sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes and onions in food processor.
In large pot, mix all ingredients together.
Boil 3 to 4 hours.
Stir frequently so it doesn't scorch.
Seal in jars and place in hot bath for about 15 minutes.

title: corn bread (best)
directions: Stir all ingredients.
Bake at 450° until done.
Bake in large black skillet.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: bewitching blueberry pancakes
directions: Stir all ingredients together and say three times:

title: easy dressing
directions: Cook chicken and debone. Bake corn bread. Boil eggs. Chop all veggies. Add all ingredients to crock-pot and cook on low for 3 to 4 hours or high for 2 hours.

title: martille's potato soup
directions: Barely cover potatoes, onion and celery with water.
Cook until tender.
Mash with potato masher.
Add milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve topped with parsley.

title: granola
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt the butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Add honey and all remaining ingredients, mixing all together thoroughly.
Spread evenly in pan and bake for about 30 minutes or until lightly browned and crispy.
Keep an eye on the mixture during the baking, stirring occasionally to prevent burning.
When cool, store in a tightly covered container.
Serve as a cold cereal, snack or a yummy topping on ice cream.

title: honey fruit cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and honey thoroughly.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Gradually beat into creamed mixture.
Blend in fruit and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: "perfectly chocolate" chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Combine dry ingredients in large bowl. Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla. Beat for 2 minutes on medium speed. Stir in boiling water. (Batter will be thin.) Pour into two 9-inch round greased and floured pans. Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pans to wire rack. Cool completely. Frost. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: imitation crab pasta salad
directions: Prepare the pasta nuggets by following the cooking directions on the box.
Cut the broccoli into florets.
Place the broccoli florets in a saucepan with 1-inch of water.
Partially cook the broccoli florets.
Dice 1/3 cup of red pepper and 1 medium sized tomato.
Slice the imitation crab into bite sized pieces.
Combine all these ingredients in a large salad bowl.
Add desired amounts of mayonnaise and Italian dressing.
Refrigerate for at least an hour.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add other ingredients.
Blend with mixer over low heat until all is melted.
Pour into a bowl and chill in refrigerator.
Add whipped cream and pecans.
Blend with mixer.
Pour in bowl and chill.

title: candy popcorn
directions: Pop the popcorn. Cook over medium heat the sugar, margarine, syrup and salt.
Stir constantly until boiling.
Continue cooking without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and baking soda.
Put popcorn in two 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans. Pour half the cooked mixture over popcorn in each pan.
Stir well.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: pecan rolls
directions: The night before baking, partially defrost bread dough (about 2 hours).
Cut into 8 even slices.
Lay each slice flat in bottom of greased and fluted tube pan.
Evenly sprinkle with pudding mix, brown sugar, pecans and cinnamon.
Drizzle with melted margarine. Cover pan and let sit out overnight.
Do not refrigerate.
Next morning, uncover pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with margarine.
Put 2 1/2 cups in layer on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Save 1/2 cup for topping.) Beat Dream Whip and milk.
Cream together sugar, vanilla and cream cheese.
Put this topping on top of crumbs.
Pour cherry pie filling on top.
Sprinkle remaining graham cracker crumbs on top.

title: golden punch
directions: Add water to concentrates as directed on cans.
Combine with apricot and pineapple.
Chill.
Yields 39 (4 ounce) cups.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix. Bake in a large pie pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until softened. In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Slowly add sweetened condensed milk, beating smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla until well mixed.
Pour into crust; chill 3 hours, until firm.

title: orange oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, orange juice and grated peel.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Stir in rolled oats until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake in preheated 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies to enjoy during the holidays or to give as gifts.

title: tom's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.

title: shredded potatoes au gratin
directions: Boil potatoes in skins; chill, peel and shred.
Stir in cheese and 4 tablespoons melted butter.
Fold in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Place in greased casserole and dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: Mix together and put in fridge until firm, then roll in chopped pecans. Serve with graham crackers.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Bring to boil the ground meat and water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Boil down for approximately 1 hour.

title: catfish stew
directions: Place fish, onions, celery and butter in pot and cover with water. Cook until fish is done. Remove fish and set aside. Return stock to the burner and add potatoes. Remove bones from fish; tear fish into small flakes. When potatoes are almost done, add fish back to the stock. Let simmer for a few minutes and add milk. Simmer until ready to serve.

title: parmesan breadsticks
directions: Combine yeast and 1/2 cups of warm water.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Combine 2 cups flour and salt and set aside.
Combine yeast mixture, remaining 1 cup water, honey and egg in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating until well blended.
Gradually stir in enough remaining 2 cups flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in a well greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let stand.
Combine butter and remaining 3 ingredients in a small saucepan, cook over medium heat until butter melts.
Set aside.
Roll dough into a 21x6 inch rectangle. Cut dough crosswise into 21-inch strips.
Twist each strip 2 times.
Place strips on a lightly greased baking sheet and brush with half of butter mixture.
Cover and let rise in a warm place. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Brush with remaining butter mixture. Yields 21 breadsticks.

title: escalloped corn and oysters
directions: Drain oysters; remove bits of shell.
Chop coarsely and mix corn with cream, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Prepare cracker crumbs; melt butter.
Add the crumbs, corn and oysters in layers in a 2-quart casserole, having 3 layers of crumbs and 2 layers each of corn and oysters.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: pineapple mexican wedding cake
directions: I use Duncan Hines cake mix and follow the directions on the box. After beating the egg whites, add 1/3 cup poppy seed and 1 tablespoon vanilla. Continue as directed on the box.

title: chocolate pudding cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put pudding mix and baking mix in bowl. Mix with wooden spoon.
Add oil and egg.
Mix together until mixture forms a ball.
Take a small spoonful of dough and shape into a 1/2-inch ball.
Place ball on ungreased cookie sheet. Place balls about 2-inches apart.

title: elephant stew
directions: There are 2 basic formulas.
Use a white under-eye makeup stick for good overall coverage.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti following directions on box.
Drain and rinse. Cut up vegetables and mix with Italian dressing.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: old timey head cheese
directions: Clean hogs head by removing snout, ears, eyes, brains and all skin.
Trim off all fat.
Cut head in four pieces and soak in salt water (1/2 cup salt to 1 gallon
water) for 3 to 5 hours to draw out all blood.
Drain and wash well in clear water.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix well and form into small balls.
Stick a toothpick in each.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients together; place it in a baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef jerky
directions: Cut meat into thin strips no longer than 1/8-inch wide. Marinate for 30 minutes.
Dry in oven at 150° to 200° for 4 to 7 hours or until dry with oven door slightly ajar.
Line oven bottom with tinfoil.
This also can be done in a dehydrator until dry.

title: cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine. Mix rice, Cheez Whiz, broccoli, soup and onion together. Sprinkle dry dressing on the top. Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Mix everything well and bake in a lightly greased casserole pan at 350 degrees for 45 minutes (don't cover).

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven. Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Serve with crackers.

title: baked beans
directions: In a large skillet, brown hamburger.
Add bell pepper (chopped), onion and brown sugar.
Simmer until pepper is tender. Mix with pork and beans and bake at 375° until beans are bubbly.

title: chicken tenders
directions: Cut chicken in pieces.
Crush up crackers in mixing bowl.
Mix egg and buttermilk together.
Salt and pepper chicken pieces and dip in egg and milk mixture.
Then coat with cracker crumbs.
Drop in hot vegetable oil until golden brown.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
In another bowl, mix eggs, salad oil, and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients and stir just until mixed.
Stir in pineapple, pecans, and bananas (or carrots or sweet potatoes).
Pour batter into 3 well greased and floured 9 inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30
minutes, or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes,
remove from pans and cool completely.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix together ingredients and let boil.
Let it get almost cool.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pinch together crescent rolls and bake on pizza pan at 350° for 7 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool.
Mix cream cheeses, mayonnaise, and dill together and spread on crust.
Cut into slices before adding toppings.
Chop all vegetables and sprinkle over pizza, pressing them down.
Top with cheese.

title: texas delight
directions: Mix and press ingredients in 11 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° and cool.

title: clam scallops
directions: Mix together and bake for 3/4 of an hour in a 325° to 350° oven.

title: lazy day salad
directions: Combine all ingredients well and chill in dish.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: shrimp and orzo salad
directions: Place water in a 3-quart microwavable casserole; cover. Microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes or until water boils.
Stir in pasta; re-cover.
Cook on High for 4 minutes, then on Medium for 6 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: chicken-wild rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken and tear into small pieces. Cook rice according to package directions.
Mix chicken soup and green chilies with hot rice.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and eggs.
Sift flour with salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with water.
Add vanilla, chips and nuts.
Set in refrigerator for 1 hour, then drop balls by tablespoon and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and blend.
Make a paste with food coloring and cocoa.
Add to mixture.
Alternately add flour, salt, buttermilk and vanilla. Mix soda and vinegar in small bowl and add to batter.
Add butter flavor and blend.
Bake in two 8-inch greased and floured pans for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli and drain.
Cook rice and set aside.
Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add two cans cream of chicken soup and 1 cup milk to margarine.
Simmer over low heat until soup is dissolved.
Add jalapeno Cheez Whiz, stir until well blended.
Add cooked rice to mixture and stir well.

title: fruit preserves pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to boil; let boil slowly for 5 minutes.
Put on cake while still hot.

title: meal-in-one
directions: Mix soup and milk.
Place potatoes in deep casserole.
Cover with 1/2 of the soup mixture.
Place peas or beans on top.
Cover with hamburger and mushrooms.
Season with onion, salt and pepper. Cover with remaining soup.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Tear bread into small pieces in large bowl.
Add sugar, cocoa and margarine on top of torn up bread.
Add 3 cups boiling water. Stir well.
Cool completely.

title: miracle whip chocolate cake
directions: Combine salad dressing, sugar and vanilla. Add dry ingredients alternately with water.
Bake at 350°.

title: jamaica pizza
directions: Combine ground beef and onion in a large saucepan.
Brown over medium heat until meat is no longer pink.
Stir taco seasoning into meat mixture.
Heat through.
Place tortillas on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with meat mixture, tomato, green pepper and cheeses.
Place under broiler for 5 to 10 minutes or until hot or bubbly and cheese is melted.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: overnight salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin according to package directions.
Add pineapple and bananas after gelatin cools a little.
Let gelatin almost set; cover with miniature marshmallows.
Cook egg yolks, pineapple juice, cornstarch and sugar in double boiler until thick; let cool.
Whip the topping mix according to package directions; mix with cooked mixture.
Pour over gelatin which is firm.
Grate cheese and sprinkle on top.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt Hershey bar in double boiler; add to Cool Whip.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Put in refrigerator for about 30 minutes before serving.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well and chill thoroughly. Serve with fruit.

title: rye bread pizzas
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except bread; mix well.
Spread on bread rounds and place on baking sheets.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 5 to 8 minutes until cheese is bubbly.

title: fried won ton
directions: Combine all ingredients, except won tons skins and egg. Chill for 1/2 hour.
Place about 1 teaspoon or less of meat in a corner of the won
ton skin.
Fold skin over meat, about 1/3 of the way to the
opposite
corner.
Put
the
egg in a small bowl and mix with a fork.
Using your finger, dip into egg and spread
on the won ton skin over the seam.
This keeps the oil out
of
the meat. Fry in a Dutch oven with oil over a medium heat.
You
want
the filling to cook, but you don't want the won
ton
skin
to burn. Serve with hot mustard and sweet and sour sauce.

title: salmon rice bake for microwave
directions: Mix all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave 5 minutes.
Stir.
Cover and microwave until rice is tender, about 6 to 7 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: fancy tuna
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Fill small egg rolls.
Wrap tinfoil tightly around rolls.
Store overnight or several hours in refrigerator.
Heat 30 minutes at 250°.
Serve warm.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Combine cucumbers with boiling water to cover in bowl.
Let stand for 4 to 5 hours.
Drain cucumbers and pack into hot sterilized 1-pint jars.
Boil remaining ingredients in saucepan for 5 minutes.
Pour into prepared jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace; seal with 2-piece lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Yields 6 pints.

title: baked beans
directions: Crumble the bacon.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Add cherries, sugar and about 1 cup water together; boil.
Add biscuit droppings to boiling mixture.
Cook until dough is almost cooked, then place pie crust on top of cherry mixture.
Top with brown sugar; pat with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: Mix together meat, parsley, salt and pepper.
On a floured board, flatten meat to a rectangular shape.
Put ham slices on the meat.
Spread on the mashed potatoes and lay the slices of cheese on top.
Roll up like a jelly roll and press edges closed.
Heat oil in large frypan.
Place meat loaf in pan.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Pour tomato sauce over meat.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Let meat stand 10 minutes before slicing.
Serves 6.

title: molded pineapple salad
directions: Bring pineapple, sugar and lemon to boil.
Add gelatine, previously soaked in 1/4 cup cold water.
Let cool.
Add cream cheese and mix well.
When entirely cool, add whipped whipping cream.
Pour into mold.

title: antipasto party dip
directions: Chop pepperoncini in food processor.
Add sour cream, mayonnaise, onion powder and garlic powder.
Process until well blended.
Stir in salami and olives.
Serve with vegetable dippers or crackers.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: marshmallow icing
directions: Boil
sugar,
syrup, salt and water until it forms soft ball in	cold
water.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Continue beating and
pour
syrup over egg whites slowly.
Take 3 or 4 minutes longer, then add vanilla and marshmallows and continue beating until icing forms peak when lifted with a spoon, about 4 minutes. Makes enough for a large 3 layer cake.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain fruit. Add jello to Cool Whip. Mix well. Add pineapple and oranges to Cool Whip mixture. Blend in marshmallows. Refrigerate.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Two hours before serving, add the remaining ingredients.

title: cherry cheese tarts
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
Blend the cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice well.
Put melted chocolate in bottom of tart shell.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over chocolate.
Spoon cherry pie filling over cheese mixture.
Drizzle a little chocolate syrup over top, if desired.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix white cake mix, jello and flour together in large mixing bowl, then add oil, water, eggs and strawberries.
Beat well. Make 2 layers or 1 oblong cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crab spread
directions: Spread cream cheese on plate.
Spread crab meat on top.
Mix cocktail sauce and Worcestershire sauce together to taste and spread over crab meat mixture.
Serve with crackers.

title: quick orange salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over cottage cheese and mix well.
Add fruit and Cool Whip.
This keeps well and is ready to eat as soon as it is mixed.

title: breast of chicken magnifique
directions: Use large skillet.
Brown chicken in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Stir in soup, mushrooms, garlic and seasonings.
Cover and cook over low heat 30 minutes or until tender.
Stir occasionally. Serve over rice.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Put Crisco and sugar into mixer and beat.
Add eggs and milk and beat again.
Add remaining ingredients to form a soft ball of dough. Put dough into refrigerator or freezer until very stiff. Roll cookie dough and cut.
Place on cookie sheet and top with sugar.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Prepare cake mix as directed and bake for 25 minutes.
Blend well cream cheese with pudding and milk.
Spread on top of cool cake.
Drain pineapple very well and spread over creamed mixture, then the Cool Whip. Sprinkle on nuts, coconut and cherry halves.
Refrigerate.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix and pour into baking pan.
Cool until firm.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together flour, oats, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
In small mixing bowl, stir together eggs, milk, butter and brown sugar.
Add to flour mixture; stir until blended.
Pour batter onto grid of preheated, lightly greased waffle iron.
Close lid quickly, do not open during baking.
Top with fresh fruit and yogurt.
Yields 12 waffles.

title: spinach dip
directions: *Half of a jar of peppers makes the dip spicy. You might need to adjust the amount to your liking.

title: easy spinach manicotti
directions: Boil manicotti only 8 to 10 minutes, drain, rinse with cool water and set aside on wax paper so they don't stick together.

title: sweet meat ball(club member: jason harvey)
directions: Add all ingredients to meat. Roll in small balls. Place in baking dish and set aside. Prepare sauce.

title: orange corn muffins
directions: Beat together the milk, egg, oil, honey and 1 teaspoon orange peel.

Add to combined cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt, mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened.* Fill 12 greased or paper lined medium size muffin cups 2/3 full.** Sprinkle combined remaining peel and sugar evenly over batter.
Bake at 425° for about 15 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with bananas.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, apples and sugar.
Dissolve jello in hot water and add juice.
Chill until partially set.
Add cranberry mixture, grapes and nuts.
Pour into molds and chill until firm.

title: gingered fruit
directions: Combine the apples, pears and peach slices with the juice and ginger in a microwave-safe 2-quart casserole dish.
Stir to blend in the ginger.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Top each serving with nutmeg and a tablespoon of vanilla yogurt.
One serving = 73 calories, 0 g protein, 14 g. carbohydrates and 07 fat.

title: cantonese beef
directions: In a bowl, mix beef slices, soy sauce, sherry and garlic salt. Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Drain beef, reserving marinade.
In a wok (or large skillet), heat oil until hot.
Add beef and stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes or until browned.
Push meat up sides of wok.
Add reserved marinade and all remaining ingredients except almonds.
Stir-fry over high heat until vegetables are tender-crisp, about 5 minutes.
Mix in meat and almonds.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Serve with herbed rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Make pudding as directed on box.
Add Cool Whip and mix together with mixer until well blended.
Layer crackers in pan. Pour pudding mixture over top. Continue layering until pudding is used up.
Melt chocolate frosting in pot of water on low heat. Spread evenly over top.
Refrigerate until crackers are soft-8 to 10 hours.

title: strawberry cake # 1
directions: Mix cake mix and jello.
Add Wesson oil, water and eggs, one at a time.
Mash berries.
Use 1/2 in the cake and the other half in the filling.
Pour into 3 prepared cake pans.
Bake as directed on cake mix box.

title: quick caramel rolls
directions: Melt butter, brown sugar and syrup over medium heat; bring to a boil.
Pour mixture into an 8-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Arrange rolls on mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Turn out on plate.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/4 cup cheese, sour cream, pimentos and 1/4 can of onions.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes longer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place the chicken breasts on a cutting board and pound lightly with a mallet until 1/4-inch thick. Combine eggs, salt and pepper. Dip the chicken in the egg mixture and then in the breadcrumbs. Heat the oil until hot in a large skillet. Brown the chicken on both sides; remove it to a shallow baking dish. Pour out excess oil from the skillet. Stir the tomato sauce, basil and garlic into the skillet. Simmer 10 minutes or until it has thickened. Stir in the margarine. Pour over the chicken and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and place the Mozzarella cheese triangles over the chicken. Bake for 10 minutes longer.

title: southern pralines
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Microwave on High until mixture reaches soft boil stage (235°).
Stir in pecans.
Cool 1 minute. Beat by hand until creamy and thickened.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: grandma scherer's potato dressing
directions: In 1 1/2-inches depth of melted lard in a quart pan, cook onions.
Add to potatoes and soaked bread.
Add the beaten eggs, parsley, salt, pepper and sage.
Mix really good.
Place in baking pan and bake until heated through.

title: molded cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in mixer bowl.
Add cream cheese, horseradish, mayonnaise and salt; beat until smooth.
Add lemon juice; mix well.
Chill until partially set.
Add cucumber and onions; mix well.
Pour into 4-cup mold.
Chill until set. This is very pretty made in a fish-shaped mold.
Use thinly sliced cucumber for scales and chives to outline the fins.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: peanut butter and fudge bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large mixing bowl, beat brown sugar, butter and 1/4 cup peanut butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add combined flour, baking soda and salt.
Beat until well mixed.
Stir in oats; mix well. Separate mixture evenly and reserve 1 cup.
Spread remaining oat mixture evenly into prepared pan.

title: cornflake chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken in butter.
Roll in cornflakes.
Place chicken in large pan lined with Reynolds Wrap. Cover with Reynolds Wrap.
Bake for about 1 hour.

title: marinated squash
directions: Place thinly sliced, washed, raw squash in a large jar.
Pack tightly as possible.
Cover with bottled dressing to within 1/2-inch top of jar.
Cheeses may be added if desired.
Refrigerate about 2 weeks.
The squash will be firm and crunchy.

title: chocolate cream cake
directions: Bake cake as it says on box.
Let cool.
Mix sour cream, sugar and cocoa.
Spread on cake.
Keep in a cool place.

title: salsa
directions: Jalapenos may be chopped and added to taste (optional).
It's probably best when made the day before, but I've made it right before serving and it was just fine, too.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Pour cake mix, Wesson oil and eggs in a bowl and mix well. Add Jell-O and strawberries and beat 1 minute.
Pour into well-greased pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Blend well and bake in unbaked pie crust in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat water to boiling.
Remove from heat; stir in rice.
Cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
Blend eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Sprinkle rice mixture with cinnamon.
Pour very hot water 1 1/4-inches deep into pan.
Bake pudding about 70 minutes until knife inserted comes out clean.
Remove casserole from water.
Serve pudding warm or cool.

title: breakfast cheese strata
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 pan.
Layer 1/2 the bread and 1/2 the cheese.
Top with meat and mushrooms, followed by another layer of bread and cheese.
Beat eggs, dry mustard, pepper and milk.
Pour over bread mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let set a while before cutting.

title: rice sauté
directions: Saut onions, mushrooms and garlic in oil about 1 1/2 minutes. Add rice, salt and pepper. Cook 1 1/2 minutes longer.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut.
Chop next 4 ingredients.
Mix with kraut.
Put in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and soup mixture.
Sift together flour, powder, cinnamon and nutmeg and add to mixture with raisins and cloves.
Pour in greased Bundt pan or angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Cool completely.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: sweet chunk pickles
directions: Cut pickles into chunks; put into weak brine overnight.
In the morning, boil remaining sugar and water until mixture strings. Heat vinegar and mixed spices.
Put boiling sugar into hot vinegar, then place pickles into this (mixed hot vinegar and sugar).
Heat and can.
Do not cook or boil pickles.

title: dreamsicle fruit salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with 1 cup water, then add juice.
Mix well and add sherbet.
Mix well and add Cool Whip and then fold in oranges.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: golden potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 400° for 1 hour or until well done.
Cut potatoes lengthwise and scoop out.
Combine with butter, salt and enough milk to whip into a fluff.
Spoon the mixture into the potato shell.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Heat at 450° until slightly brown and cheese melts.
May be prepared ahead and frozen until needed.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Mix together and simmer for 3 hours.

title: mashed potato cakes
directions: Combine ingredients.
Shape into cakes and brown in Crisco on both sides.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat oil and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each addition.
Sift ingredients and fold into first mixture; blend well.
Last, fold in carrots and nuts.
Pour into greased pan and bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar with mixer. Pour in graham cracker pie shell.
Put Thank You cherries on top. Refrigerate.

title: strawberry cream cake
directions: Mix strawberry Jell-O with boiling water.
Add crushed strawberries.
Put in refrigerator until firm.
When firm, fold in Cool Whip.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, break up angel food cake into pieces.
Pour Jell-O mixture over cake.
Serve with extra cream.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream
shortening
and sugars until creamy; add eggs and flavoring
and
mix
well.	Add
dry
ingredients, then stir in chips.
Spoon
onto cookie sheet and bake in a 325° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: selma biscuits
directions: Mix the ingredients; beat with hand beater.
Put in small, ungreased muffin tins.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Will not rise so fill muffin tins.

title: date nut balls
directions: Mix together and bake in an 8-inch square pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.
Take out and cool just enough to handle and roll into balls.
Roll in additional sugar.
Store in covered container.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix ground chuck, bell pepper, onion and Worcestershire sauce. Cook until done.
Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook until done.

title: texas-style beef brisket
directions: Spread dry soup mix over surface of brisket, then wrap securely, using at least 3 layers of heavy-duty foil.
Seal foil well to hold in all the juices.
Start fire in your barbecue. When coals are white hot, move them to one side.
Place foil wrapped brisket on rack, but not directly above coals.
Cover grill; cook brisket for 3 hours, turning once.
Remove brisket carefully from wrappings, pouring drippings off into glass measuring cup.
Return brisket to grill rack, directly over coals this time, and cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes, until crusty brown, basting with drippings from time to time.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Drain shrimp.
Rinse well with lemon juice.
Beat all ingredients with electric mixer.
Salt and pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Tastes great on Ritz crackers.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Prepare unbaked pie shell.
Mix sugar, cocoa and margarine; stir well.
Add eggs and beat for 2 1/2 minutes.
Add salt, milk and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: mississippi mud(this is a great cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 15 x 10 x 2-inch pan.
In mixer bowl, combine butter and sugar. Beat with mixer until light and fluffy.
Add cocoa, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour. Beat on lowest speed.

title: quick peach pie(club member: jason baldwin)
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. In a bowl, mix flour and sugar. Add milk and vanilla. Mix well. Add peaches and stir. Pour this mixture into baking dish. Bake at 350° until it browns, about an hour.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Put Rice Krispies in a large bowl.
In saucepan, mix the sugar and syrup.
Let come to a boil.
Stir in peanut butter and mix. Pour over the Rice Krispies and mix.
Put into a 10 x 13-inch pan and press down.
In microwave, put both chips in and melt.
Stir when melted.
Pour this on top of Rice Krispies and spread.
Let set.

title: mrs. fahey's chicken
directions: Cover large skillet with the liquid sauces, then brown chicken cutlet.
Then put frozen broccoli on top.
Sprinkle some more light soy sauce on top of broccoli.
Cover and simmer until cooked.

title: broccoli salad 1
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Break in pieces.
Chop broccoli and onion.
Add cheese and raisins.
Mix together.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar together.
Pour over other ingredients.

title: cube steak parmesan
directions: Cut cubed steak into serving sized pieces.
Prepare cubed steak by dredging with flour, salt and pepper mixture and browning in small amount of oil.
Drain and arrange in baking dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and spoon Ragu in the center of each piece.
Top with grated Swiss or Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.
Can be done with venison.

title: butch's goulash
directions: In a large pot, add salt and chicken.
Cover in water and cook until done.
Remove chicken (do not drain off water) and cut up and debone.
Add potatoes, carrots and onions.
Cook until potatoes are tender. Do not stir. Add bread to thicken.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange
apples
in
a greased baking dish; pour orange juice over the apples.
Combine 1/2 cup of sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle evenly
over
the
apples.	Combine
flour	with the remaining 1/2 cup
sugar
and
salt.
Cut in butter until the mixture
is crumbly.
Spoon mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45
to 60 minutes or until apples are tender and the crust is brown.	Serve warm or cold with ice cream or milk.

title: frozen daiquiri or pina colada salad
directions: In blender or mixing bowl combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in pineapple and cherries.
Freeze firm. Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: potato pizza hot dish
directions: Cover bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with potatoes.
Combine soup and milk and pour over potatoes.
In a skillet brown ground beef with onion and drain.
Spread over soup mixture and pour pizza sauce over meat layer.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until the potatoes are tender. Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes.

title: yum yum bars
directions: Mix all ingredients except candy bars.
Bake in a greased pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove and put broken candy over top. Spread over the top when melted.
Do not overbake.

title: brownie muffins
directions: Melt the chocolate and butter in a saucepan; when melted, add pecans and set aside.
Mix flour, sugar and eggs; add chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Do not beat.
Pour into baking cups, small or miniature muffin pans, filling cup 2/3 full.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Don't overcook.
Cool in pan 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: savory fried chicken
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Combine flour sealing in large bag. In shallow bowl, beat eggs and 2 tablespoons water with whisk. Place chicken in bag.
Shake a couple at a time, then dunk into egg mixture.
Back into bag; shake off excess, then into deep fryer pan with oil deep enough to cover 3/4 of chicken.
Brown well on both sides, skin side first, 8 to 10 minutes on each side; well cooked.

title: turkey divan
directions: Cook broccoli.
Arrange it in a greased baking dish.
Layer turkey on top.
Combine the next 3 ingredients.
Pour over turkey. Sprinkle with white or yellow cheese.
Combine the crumbs and butter and sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Bake uncovered.

title: praline pie
directions: Mix margarine, brown sugar and pecans together and pour into unbaked pie shell; bake at 400° until pie shell is golden brown and praline mixture is bubbly.
Remove from oven and set aside to cool.
Add the butter pecan pie filling to 1 cup cold milk and mix until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour mixture into cooled pie shell.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Pound chicken to 1/2-inch thickness; sprinkle both sides with flour.
In small bowl, mix milk and cheese.
Mix crumbs and seasonings on wax paper.
Dip chicken in milk, then coat both sides with crumbs.
Fry in oil or bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes per side.
Serves 4.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Brown chops in pan with 1 tablespoon of salt and place in a casserole.
Mix the sliced onions, green pepper, pimentos, canned tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and salt and pepper.
Place the cooked rice over the casserole.
Cover and simmer on stove for 2 hours at 350°.

title: mississippi mud pie(for one 9-inch pie; serves 10)
directions: Mix cookies in food processor or blender until crumbly.
Pour in butter.
Pat mixture in 9-inch deep pie plate.
Then put in vanilla ice cream over crust.
Pour generous amount of fudge sauce and marshmallow over ice cream.
Sprinkle with nuts, then repeat with chocolate ice cream, fudge, marshmallow and nuts.
Chill for 3 hours for best results.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry icebox cake
directions: Bread cake into pieces.
Place in mold or bowl.
Melt Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Add ice cream, stir until dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries.
Add to cake in bowl.
Let set until solid, serve cold.

title: potato rolls
directions: Put sugar, milk, butter and salt in saucepan.
Simmer.
Remove from heat and add mashed potatoes.
When cool, add eggs and yeast, which has been dissolved in 1/2 cup lukewarm water and 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Add 3 cups of flour and beat with mixer.
Then add remaining flour and put into greased bowl.
Let rise until double. Make into desired rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° until done and brown, about 30 to 35 minutes.
You can also use this dough to make cinnamon rolls or coffee cake.

title: fran's tomato-basil pasta
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil about 2 minutes.
Add chopped plum tomatoes.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add basil and Mozzarella. Stir until cheese starts to melt.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour over cooked pasta.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Cut gumdrops into fine pieces.
Do not use black gumdrops. Mix gumdrops, raisins and nuts; lightly flour and set aside.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Keeps for a long time.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix salt, flour and sugar in a 3-quart stewer.
Add eggs; thoroughly mix.
Add milk; thoroughly mix.
Before putting the mixture on heat, prepare the dish you plan to pour the cooked mixture into by doing the following.

title: baked carrot custard
directions: Beat all of these together. Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Tastes like custard instead of carrots!

title: devilish crab eggs
directions: Remove cartilage from crabmeat.
Peel eggs and cut in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks; put yolks in bowl and mash well.
Add celery, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Add crabmeat and mix well. Stuff egg whites with yolk mixture.
Chill before serving.
Makes 1 dozen Devilish Crab Eggs.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla, flour and nuts.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Shape dough into balls about 1-inch in diameter. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake and cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Temperature: 350°.
Time: 20 minutes.

title: burgundy beef over noodles
directions: Cut up sirloin to stew-size pieces.
Season with pepper. Brown in margarine.
Simmer for about 2 hours or until just tender with Burgundy, parsley, bay leaf (leave in for 15 minutes only), garlic powder, onion powder, cut up tomatoes, pearl onions, salt, pepper and water.
Add cubed potatoes, carrots and green beans. When vegetables are almost tender, add mushrooms and mixture of flour and 3/4 cup cold water.
Simmer until liquid is thickened to desired consistency.
Serve over noodles.

title: baked meat loaf alaska
directions: Combine top 4 ingredients; make into loaf 2-inches high. Prepare instant potatoes according to package.
Spread over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes; top with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: opulent chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and paprika; brown in 4 tablespoons of butter and arrange in serving dish.

title: gold water beans
directions: Soak beans overnight and cook. Brown ground beef and add all ingredients into beans.
Cook until flavors are blended.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Lay out cream cheese and beat until creamy.
Add Eagle Brand milk, then lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Chill pie filling about 30 minutes before putting on pie.

title: hash brown scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, cheese and onions and put into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour broth over top.
Top with some cheese and dot with butter.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes; drain.
Beat eggs and mix with soup, mayonnaise, onion, salt, pepper and cheese.
Place broccoli in buttered dish.
Pour sauce over broccoli.
Top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: white chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt in small bowl. Beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in large bowl until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually beat in flour mix.
Stir in chips.
Drop by well-rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: spicy zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Continue beating until foamy, adding zucchini and pineapple.
Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, nuts and currants; stir into above mixture until blended.
Divide loaves.
Bake in greased and floured pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and turn out.

title: cory's favorite treats
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, salt, butter and milk.
Cook until mixture comes to boil.
Let boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Stir to blend.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let cool until firm. Store in tight container.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together until creamy.

title: not so secret barbecue sauce
directions: Puree all ingredients in a blender or food processor.

title: great pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix flour, oats, soda, cinnamon and salt in medium bowl. In another bowl, beat butter and sugars until light and fluffy. Add pumpkin, eggs and vanilla; mix well. Gradually add flour mixture; blend well. Stir in nuts and 1 1/3 cups raisins. Drop by cookie scoop or 1/4 cup onto greased baking sheet and spread into 3-inch circle. Bake at 350° for 14 to 16 minutes or until firm and lightly brown. Cool on sheets for 2 minutes, then remove to racks to cool completely. May decorate with icing if desired. Makes 40 large cookies.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil water,
cranberries
and
sugar until berries pop. Stir to
keep
from sticking.
Turn burner off.
Add marshmallows and jello; stir until marshmallows melt.
Let cool.
Add apples, celery and pecans.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: marinated squash
directions: You will need 6 pint jars with lids (warm).

title: sour cream-chocolate bit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix butter with 1 cup sugar until blended, then beat in eggs, one at a time. Stir dry ingredients together.
Blend with creamed mixture.
Mix in sour cream.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Scatter the chocolate bits evenly over the batter, then sprinkle with the remaining 1 tablespoon sugar and pecans (if desired).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake just begins to pull away from sides of pan. Serve warm or cooled (do not refrigerate).

title: wacky cake
directions: Pour 2 cups warm water over it; stir until smooth.
Bake in 350° oven until done, when toothpick comes out clean.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the sugar and Crisco.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Very moist cake.

title: maple cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese and margarine well.
Add powdered sugar (sifted) and flavoring.
Cream very well.
Be sure cake is completely cool before frosting.

title: strawberry fig jam
directions: Cover figs with jello and sugar.
Let stand 45 minutes.
Cook slowly 5 minutes.
Raise heat, but don't bring to a boil.
Cook 15 minutes or until thickens.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: reuben muffin triangles
directions: Spread muffin halves with mustard; top with beef, sauerkraut and cheese.
Place on a baking sheet and broil until cheese melts. Cut each muffin into quarters.
Makes 32.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Pour liqueur (or other liquid) over warm brownies just out of the oven.
Let cool completely.
Crumble half of brownies into glass bowl; will be very sticky.
Spread half of mousse over brownies.
Sprinkle with half of chips.
Spread half of whipped topping over all.
Repeat layers and top with chips for decorations.
Can be made 1 day ahead.
Serves 20 +.

title: baked stuffed onions
directions: Scoop out centers of 8 onions.
Leave shell 1/4-inch thick. Chop enough centers to make 1 1/2 cups.
Blanch onion cases in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Turn upside-down on rack to drain.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into 9-inch baked pie crust.

title: turkey chili
directions: Brown turkey, onion and green pepper in heavy skillet.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Remove bay leaves before serving.
Serves 4.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream margarine and 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs (one at a time), creaming after each addition.
Add lemon rind.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add, alternating with milk; blend well after each addition.
Add chopped nuts, if desired.
Grease long loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 5 minutes.
Prick bread all over.

title: scalloped chicken casserole
directions: Line casserole bottom with bacon.
Add layer of sliced potatoes, then layer of salted chicken, layer of sliced tomatoes, onions and green pepper.
Season to taste.
Repeat until bowl is full.
Pour sour cream over casserole and sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 or 2 hours.

title: finnish raspberry strip cookies
