directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour and mix well.
Gather crumbly mixture and work between hands until warmth makes smooth dough.
Roll dough on countertop or lightly floured board with palms of hands into logs 1/2-inch in diameter, long enough for your cookie sheet (add sections until correct length).
Place logs on lightly greased cookie sheet.
With side of little finger or handle of wooden spoon, press a groove lengthwise down middle of each log.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove and fill groove with jam.
Return to oven and bake 10 minutes more until dough is set and very light golden.
While hot, brush with glaze.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread bread with mustard.
Cut in cubes.
Place in bottom of buttered casserole.
Crumble corned beef on top.
Stir sauerkraut, soup, water and relish.
Pour over corned beef.
Cut cheese slices in triangles and put on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: tortilla crisps
directions: Cut flour tortillas into triangles.
Dip into deep fryer for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.

title: "spanish potatoes"
directions: Fry onion, pepper and pimento in fat until light brown.
Add potatoes, ham and seasoning; cook until thoroughly heated. Serves 4.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin and evaporated milk. Mix ginger, sugar and cinnamon together and then add to the liquid mixture; mix well. Pour this all into ungreased 9 x 13 cake pan (glass works best). Sprinkle dry cake mix over this. Drizzle melted butter over top. Sprinkle chopped pecans on top. Bake 1 hour at 350° or until a knife comes out clean when
inserted into the center. Best served warm and topped with whipped cream.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Heat water and sugar in 2-quart saucepan to boiling (1 minute). Add cranberries.
Heat to boiling (5 minutes).
Stir in gelatin until dissolved. Stir in pineapple with syrup and celery. Pour into 6 cup mold or 8 individual molds. Refrigerate until firm, 6 hours.
Unmold on salad greens. Garnish with sour cream and, if desired, pineapple chunks.

title: heavenly hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in double boiler. Add sugar very slowly. Mixture will be very stiff. Very slowly add milk and salt and continue stirring over heat until smooth. Keeps nicely in refrigerator for days. May be reheated. Make a sandwich of yellow cake and vanilla ice cream and top with fudge sauce.

title: chicken on sunday
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle rice over bottom of pan. Heat soups and milk in saucepan.
Pour over rice.
Place chicken pieces on top. Sprinkle onion soup over; seal pan with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours and 15 minutes.
(No peeking!)

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks.
Sift flour, soda or baking powder and add to mixture along with sour cream.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Fold egg whites into mixture.
Put cake in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: make pudding pound cake(in a hurry?)
directions: Beat eggs one at a time.
Add other ingredients and beat until smooth. Pour into a well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a medium saucepan, combine chocolate chips and butter.
Cook and stir over very low heat until chips are melted and smooth.
Add sweetened condensed milk and mix well. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup.
Level off.

title: simple salisbury steak
directions: In large bowl, mix thoroughly 1/4 cup soup, ground beef, bread crumbs, onion and egg.
Shape firmly into 6 oval patties of even thickness.
Spray 10-inch skillet with vegetable cooking spray. Over medium-high heat, cook half of patties until browned on both sides.
Remove; set aside.
Repeat with remaining patties.
Spoon off fat.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients. Let set 2 hrs. in refrigerator. Add garlic. Shake well and use.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix together.
One banana and pineapple chunks may be added. Refrigerate.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Cube Velveeta and melt in crock-pot. When cheese is nearly melted add rest of ingredients.
Stir well and let set enough to heat thoroughly.

title: hot cheese and rye appetizers
directions: Mix Cheddar, Jack, olives and onions in medium size bowl; add seasoning and enough mayonnaise to get the mixture to stick together.
Spread thin layer on rye breads and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Broil until cheese begins to bubble or until slightly brown, about 5 minutes.
Excellent!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl.
Pour into baking dish.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Cook ground beef.
Add to broth, V-8 juice and 2 cans of cream soup.
Add vegetable cans.
Cook and heat.
Serve warm.

title: fudgsicle pie
directions: In large bowl, combine pudding mix and milk.
Gently fold mixture into ice cream.
Pour into prepared shell.
Cover and freeze until firm, several hours.

title: apricot ice
directions: Place apricots in saucepan with enough water to cover and bring to boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until fruit is soft (about 20 minutes).
Drain and reserve about 3/4 cup of fruit liquid.
Cool.
Puree fruit in food processor or blender with reserved fruit liquid.
Add lemon juice and sugar to fruit and puree 30 seconds longer.
Pour into 8-inch square pan; place in freezer and stir every 15 minutes until creamy.
Cover and freeze until semi-hard.
Yield:
4 servings.
Approximate calories/serving:

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in saucepan with onion in salted water; boil until soft.
Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream; stir in carrots. Fold in squash, onion and cheese.
Combine stuffing and butter. Put 1/2 stuffing mixture in bottom of baking dish; put vegetable mixture over it.
Sprinkle rest of stuffing on top.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cool whip icing
directions: Mix pudding, milk and confectioners sugar.
Put in refrigerator for 5 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip.
Store cake in refrigerator until serving time.

title: forever ambers
directions: Mix together well all ingredients except powdered sugar.
Pour in greased 12-inch shallow pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 275°.
Pour back into mixing bowl and stir in powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Cool.

title: stove top cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine.
Cook 1 minute at hard boil.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Stir until mixed.
Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: spaghetti bravissimo
directions: In a large saucepan, combine soup mix and water; bring to a boil. Add spaghetti and cook for 20 minutes. While this is cooking, brown meat and drain fat. Stir in tomato sauce and pasta, parsley, oregano and basil. Add to onion soup and spaghetti. Heat. I serve this with Parmesan cheese on top.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve lemon gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Add marshmallows and chill until partially thickened.
Fold in cottage cheese, pineapple and whipped cream or topping.
Turn mixture into an 11 x 7-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Dissolve strawberry gelatin in 1 3/4 cups water.
Chill until partially thickened. Spread over first layer.
Chill again for several hours or overnight.

title: puppy chow
directions: Put in saucepan and melt; pour over Chex cereal and mix well. In large bag, put sugar in; add cereal mix and shake well to coat cereal.

title: strawberry glace pie
directions: Mash enough berries to measure 1 cup.
Stir together sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in water and crushed strawberries. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Cool.
Fill shell with remaining whole berries; pour cooked berry mixture over top.
Chill at least 3 hours or until set.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil together the sugar and vinegar.
Pour this mixture over the other ingredients.
Let stand 12 hours in refrigerator.
Pour off excess juice before serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix salad oil, sugar and eggs, adding eggs one at a time.
Add zucchini.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Add to mixture.
Add pecans.
Bake 1 hour at 325° in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Delicious.

title: mom's cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, milk, beef and onion.
Form into ball.
Chill.
Roll in chopped pecans and serve.

title: frozen punch
directions: Combine bananas and fruit juices.
Mix well.
Add water, sugar and Jell-O.
Mix well.
Freeze.
Thaw 1 hour before serving.
Add Sprite.

title: red wine-basil vinaigarette
directions: Combine garlic, mustard, vinegar and pepper; whip well.
Add oil in a slow stream, whisking constantly until slightly thickened.
Fold in basil and parsley.

title: pork chops with italian sausage sauce
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.
Brown well on all sides in oil in a large frying pan.
Remove chops from pan and reserve.
Pour off and discard all but about 1 tablespoon of the pan drippings.
Remove casings from sausages and crumble meat into same pan.
Mix in onion and mushrooms.
Cook, stirring until onions and sausage brown lightly.
Mix in garlic.
Return pork chops to pan, spooning sausage mixture over them.
Pour in wine or broth and tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bring to boiling. Cover; reduce heat and simmer until pork chops are tender, 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve chops with sauce spooned over.

title: sweet cornbread
directions: Bake at 500° for 15 minutes.
Grease pan.
Serves about 6 people.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream butter, sugar, and flour as for pie crust.
Add pecans. Form into small balls and bake in
hot oven.
When slightly cooled, roll in powdered sugar.

title: 3-in-1 cheese ball
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, milk, onion, and Worcestershire sauce until fluffy.
If a smoother spread is desired, process in a food processor until creamy. Divide into thirds (about 1 c. each).
Shape first portion into a ball; roll in cracked pepper.
Add the blue cheese to the second portion; mix well, shape into a ball; roll in parsley.
Add garlic powder to the remaining portion; mix well.
Shape into a ball; roll in nuts.
Cover and refrigerate.
Remove from refrigerator and let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken with water and salt until tender.
Remove chicken from broth and cool.
Debone chicken and cut meat into bite size pieces.
Set aside.
Bring broth to a boil; add pepper.
Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mix resembles meal.
Add milk to moisten.
Turn onto floured surface and knead 4 to 5 times.
Pat dough and roll into 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 2-inch strips and drop into boiling broth.
Leave strips covered with flour to thicken broth.
Reduce heat and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes.
Add chicken.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: salsa
directions: Mix together.
Put in blender for about 5 seconds.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased pan, 9 x 13 x 2-inch.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake is brown and leaves edges of pan.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chips and 14 oz almond bark in 2 qt bowl.
Continue stirring until smooth.
Stir in marshmallows, peanuts, and cereal. Pour onto greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with sliced and drained cherries and sprinkle with coconut.
Melt remaining 2 oz bark until smooth.
Drizzle over coconut.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Cook onions in butter in a large skillet until transparent and golden.
Place onions in a casserole dish; top with a mixture of sour cream, soup, cheese and 1 cup of bread stuffing.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of stuffing over top; dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes, until bubbly.

title: special k cookie bar
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to boil. Remove from stove and add peanut butter and cereal. Stir until well mixed and spread in a 10 x 15 cookie sheet.

title: benedict arnold casserole
directions: Layer rice, chicken chunks and broccoli.
Mix together the soup, chicken broth, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry.
Pour on top.
Sprinkle stuffing that has soaked in margarine.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberries in a cloud
directions: Beat eggs and cream of tartar until foamy.
Beat in sugar a tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Do not underbeat.
Spoon meringue onto heavy brown paper in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Makes 9-inch square of meringue.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 275°.
Turn off oven.
Leave meringue in oven 1 more hour. Cool.
Blend cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
In chilled bowl, beat whipping cream until stiff.
Gently fold in cream cheese mixture and marshmallows.
Cover and chill 12 hours.
Before serving, add one can of thickened fruit.

title: oven tuna goulash
directions: Drain tuna.
Cook noodles just 5 minutes, drain.
Mix succotash, onion and salt into bowl.
Spoon half of the noodles into a buttered 2-quart baking dish; top with half each of tuna and vegetable mixture; repeat.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs; drizzle milk over all.
Bake until crumbs are golden brown.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: oatmeal-peanut butter-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat butter and peanut butter at medium speed until fluffy. Gradually add sugar and brown sugar, beating well.
Add eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Combine oats and baking soda; add to butter mixture, mixing well.
Stir in chips.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet for 5 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Yields 7 dozen.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Glaze top with sugar, vanilla and milk as needed.

title: rich dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk, add sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in warm water; add lukewarm mixture.
Add beaten eggs.
Stir in small amounts of flour until mixture is sticky and slightly stiff.
Knead on floured board for several minutes.
Let rise in warm area for 30 minutes.
Divide into 2 balls.
Set on kneading board with towel draped over for about 10 minutes to relax dough.
Roll into desired thickness and cut into desired shapes. Place on lightly greased baking sheets and let rise another 30 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for about 25 minutes.

title: apricot bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. You will need an 8 x 8 x 2 pan.

title: butter pecan rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine hot milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool
to
lukewarm.
Add 1 cup of flour. Beat in softened yeast and	egg.
Add
rest
of
flour to form soft dough. Cover and let
rise
until
doubled.
Turn out on lightly floured surface and
divide
in half.
Roll each piece into a 12 x 8-inch rectangle, 3/8-inch thick.	Brush each with melted butter. Combine
sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle half on each rectangle. Beginning
with
long
side,
roll jelly roll fashion.
Cut into 8 (1-inch) slices.
In
each of two 9 1/2 x 5
x 3-inch pans, mix brown
sugar,
corn
syrup	and
melted butter.
Sprinkle with pecans
and
place	rolls
on top.	Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 400°.
Remove immediately.

title: golden champagne punch
directions: Mix juices and sugar; chill.
Pour juice mixture over block of ice or ice ring in punch bowl.
Add wines and stir.
Serves 15 to 18.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour with salt.
Add flour alternately with milk to creamed mixture, beating after each addition.
Add coconut, lemon and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until cake is done.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Serves 12.

title: lamb stew with wine and rosemary
directions: Trim excess fat and cut into chunks.
Brown onions and lamb for about 5 minutes in olive oil.
Scrape into casserole.
Deglaze the pan with the wine, pouring it into the casserole.
Add to the casserole the garlic, rosemary, tomato and enough stock to cover ingredients.
Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325° in oven or until lamb is tender.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle sugar, lemon juice and salt over apples.
Add celery, cherries, raisins, marshmallows and pecans.
Fold salad dressing into whipped cream.
Gradually fold into apple mixture.
Chill. Makes 10 servings.

title: play dough
directions: *If you can't find it at the grocery store, it is available at the drugstore.

title: salmon salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve on crackers.
Amount of each ingredient can be changed to suite taste.

title: old settlers beans
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon in frypan; drain off excess fat. Place in crock-pot with rest of the ingredients.
Cook on low overnight.

title: green bean casserole(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Cook beans just enough to thaw, then drain them.
Mix soup and milk together.
Layer half the beans, water chestnuts and soup in a baking dish.
Repeat.
Top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Grind together bologna and cheese.
Cook beef until lightly browned; stir in bologna mixture, sauce and spices.
Spread on top and bottom halves of buns.
Garnish with cheese if desired.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Begin with a large mixing bowl as mixture increases in volume. Beat milk until stiff.
Gradually add sweetener and thawed orange juice, blending well.
Spoon into small containers and freeze.

title: baklava
directions: Mix together nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
For thick layers, use a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
For thinner layers, use a 1/4-inch sheet cake pan.
Spray with cooking spray.

title: yellow cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually, creaming until light.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating after each addition.
Beat 1 minute.
Bake in 2 greased and lightly floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch round pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Brown onions and pepper in oil or bacon drippings.
Add other ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°. Put cooked bacon on top.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease two cookie sheets.
In large bowl, beat butter, sugars, egg and vanilla at medium-high speed until fluffy.
Reduce mixer speed to low and add flour and oatmeal.
Increase mixer speed gradually and beat until just blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop heaping tablespoonfuls of dough 2 1/2 inches apart onto prepared sheets.
Bake 1 sheet at a time for 17 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Cool on sheets
5 minutes before removing to racks to cool completely. Makes 2 dozen.

title: bringing home baby carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover, simmer 10 to 14 minutes or until carrots are tender.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place corn in bottom of greased baking dish. Add chopped onion.

Brown hamburger with 1/2 teaspoon salt and spread over chopped onion. Add the tomatoes. Cream the cooked potatoes with 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/2 stick margarine and small amount of milk. Spread creamed potatoes on top of tomatoes in dish. Bake at 350° until potatoes are lightly browned on top.

title: sweetheart potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray mini heart pan with vegetable pan spray.
Stir seasonings into melted butter.
Using second smallest heart cutter (from 6-piece heart graduated cookie cutter set) cut 6 little hearts out of potatoes.
Place one in center of each cavity. Brush with seasoned butter.
Divide remaining potatoes among the cavities; make 3 layers in each one.
Brush between layers with seasoned butter and sprinkle with small amount of cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until fork-tender.
Let potatoes set for 5 minutes before taking out of pan.
Invert to remove.

title: light and easy lemon broccoli chicken
directions: Combine soup and milk.
Stir in lemon juice and pepper; pour over washed chicken.
Bake at 325° until tender.
Garnish with lemons before serving.
(The soup mixture serves as a gravy.)

title: lentil soup
directions: Heat
oil
in a
large	pot.
Brown
garlic.
Add
ham, sausage and onion.	Cook
for 5 minutes.
Add celery, lentils, water, salt and hot sauce.	Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat to low and simmer
24	hours.	Add chopped spinach.
Cook 10 minutes.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients (in order given).
Pour into pie shell. Turn pecans right side up.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sweet and hot pickles
directions: Drain pickles; discard juice.
In large pan, mix pickles, sugar and Tabasco.
Return all to the gallon jar and seal.
Turn jar several times a day for 2 days.
Pickles can be put in one-pint jars and sealed.

title: giant sesame seed braid
directions: Combine yeast and 1/4 cup warm water in a small bowl; set aside.
Combine 2 cups hot water, oil, butter, sugar and salt in a large bowl; stir until butter melts.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in yeast mixture and 2 eggs.
Gradually add 3 cups flour, beating well.
Add enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.

title: tomato jam
directions: Peel, core and cut tomatoes into 1 1/2-inch pieces and put into a large saucepan.
Add lemon peel, juice and salt.
Tie spices in cheesecloth bag and add.
Stir in sugar; boil.
Add Certo and bring to a rolling boil for 1 minute.
Stir constantly. Remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes and put into hot, sterilized jars.

title: corn dogs
directions: Will also need sticks.

title: cool fruit dessert
directions: Mix all
ingredients together.	Put in bowl.
Chill for couple of	hours
before serving.	May also put in oblong dish and freeze.
Cut in slices to serve.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix in bowl.
Roll into balls, then roll in coconut.
Place on waxed paper.

title: rice krispie cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Add vanilla. Combine flour, cream of tartar and baking soda; mix together with shortening.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
using a teaspoon, place dough on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press each cookie lightly with fork.
Bake at 350° watching carefully for 9 to 10 minutes. Yield: approximately 6 dozen.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, egg and lard.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Crumble ground beef into frying pan; add green pepper.
Cook until ground beef is brown; drain.
Mix in chili powder, tomato sauce, tomato paste, olives and water.
Simmer for 6 to 8 minutes. Place 2 tortillas in 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Top with 1/2 meat mixture and 1/2 of both cheeses, then place 2 more tortillas over that layer.
Then top with rest of ground beef and other halves of both cheese.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350° or until cheese is melted.
Can also microwave for 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted, if desired.
Top with shredded lettuce, sour cream and tomatoes.

title: shrimp and shell salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, saving shrimp until last. One can is plenty, but if you really love shrimp, add a second can.
Serves 12 to 14 people.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Bake in iron skillet at 350° to 375° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: layer salad
directions: Arrange the ingredients in the order listed in a large dish. Cover and chill for 24 hours.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix and put in ice cream freezer and mix until done.
Very soft, but a smooth taste.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chicken style seasoning
directions: Blend ingredients, except parsley.
Stir or shake parsley in mixture in airtight container.
May be used as any other chicken style seasoning.

title: boursin cheese
directions: Soften cheese and
butter.
Cream together.
Add garlic and herbs and cream together.
May
be served as a soft spread or refrigerated and made into a ball.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Stir in soup, water, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes, beans, sausage and vinegar.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Top with bacon bits.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's shrimp mousse
directions: Heat soup in saucepan.
Add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a mold which has been rinsed with cold water.
Chill until set.
Serve with crackers.

title: weight watchers barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: chicken a l'orange
directions: Pound chicken breasts between waxed paper until thin.
In paper bag, combine flour, paprika and orange peel.
Add chicken; close bag and shake.
In skillet, heat oil and brown chicken breasts lightly on both sides; transfer to shallow baking dish. To skillet, add garlic and cook, stirring, for 1 minute.
Add wine, orange juice and thyme.
Heat to boiling and pour over chicken.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Top with orange slices and continue to bake for 15 minutes longer.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini and beef
directions: Ideal for outdoor or indoor entertaining, this tempting sweet and pungent recipe comes from our newest state, Hawaii.
If desired, garnish the platter with fresh lemon leaves, available at florists' shops, and serve with a tossed green salad and your favorite dressing.

title: red cabbage
directions: Using steel blade, process onion, using on/off technique until chopped.
Saute in butter in large saucepan until soft, 5 minutes. Using slicing disc, slice apples.
Add apples to saucepan; cook 5 minutes.
Using slicing disc, slice cabbage.
Stir sliced cabbage, vinegar, sugar, water, salt, nutmeg and cloves into saucepan. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, until cabbage is tender, about 1 hour.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups of hot water, then add frozen orange juice and stir until dissolved. Let cool in refrigerator until slightly thickened. Stir in oranges and pineapple. Chill until firm.

title: homemade dog biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Roll out half of dough at a time into 3/8-inch thickness.
Using a pizza cutter, cut in desired shapes and sizes.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 375°.
Turn off oven and leave biscuits in oven until cool.
Place in airtight container.

title: mother's cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour.
(Add food coloring, if desired.)
Roll out and cut cookies.
Bake 6 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: gina's cheese roll
directions: Let cheese come to room temperature. Mix well and shape into rolls and roll in chili powder. Wrap in foil and refrigerate. Makes 3 rolls.

title: barbecue sauerkraut
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together; drain.
Mix kraut, brown sugar and tomato sauce together in baking dish.
Add hamburger and onion.
Mix well.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana-chip cake
directions: Bananas make this cake incredibly moist and chocolate chips make it extra special.

title: petite cherry cheesecakes
directions: You will need 24 paper muffin cups.

title: crock-pot cube steak
directions: In a frying pan, heat Wesson oil, flour, salt and pepper cube steak.
Brown lightly on both sides.
Don't cook.
Cut large pieces in half.
Put cube steak in crock-pot.
Sprinkle flour in pan with drippings.
Brown well.
Add milk and water, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil.
Pour over cube steak in crock-pot.
Cook on low 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Tender melt in your mouth.

title: from the garden strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Slice rhubarb into 1-inch pieces.
Stem and halve strawberries. Toss with sugar and tapioca.
Put into 10-inch pie shell crust. Dot with butter.
Top with top crust, pierce.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Scald milk and mix chocolate.
Beat. Combine flour, sugar and salt. Add egg yolks.
Pour chocolate over egg mixture.
Return to double boiler and cook until thick, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla. Cool and add to cooked pie shell.
Makes 2 pies.
Delicious.

title: crock-pot venison
directions: Put steak in the slow cooker. Mix first 5 ingredients and pour over steak. Cover and cook 8 to 10 hours on low, 3 to 5 hours on high.

title: topping for cake
directions: Whip until double in bulk.

title: daiquiri pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Beat in Eagle Brand and juice concentrate until smooth.
Add rum and food coloring.
Fold in whipped cream; pour into crust.
Freeze or chill until firm (4 hours in freezer; 2 hours in refrigerator). Garnish with lime twists, if desired.
Refrigerate or freeze leftovers.

title: mama's caramel icing
directions: Cook 1/2 cup sugar in black skillet until melted and golden. Mix egg, butter and remainder of sugar with milk in a heavy boiler and cook over medium heat until butter melts.
Add caramelized sugar.
Cook until soft ball can be formed in cold water.
I use a candy thermometer and cook it to 232°.
Add vanilla; beat.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Layer one cup of grated cheese and macaroni in a buttered casserole dish. Beat eggs well; add milk and seasonings.
Pour over macaroni and cheese.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs; dot with butter.
Top with additional grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until knife inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except strawberries.
Bake in muffin tins for 10 minutes at 350°.
When cool, divide each cake in the middle; fill with berries.
Replace each top; smother with the entire shortcake in strawberries.
Top with ice cream or whipped cream.
This is food fit for a king and all the little princes and princesses, too.
Serves 6.

title: layered ham and macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and chill.
In a 3-quart salad bowl, layer lettuce, celery, cucumber, onion, macaroni, ham and peas. Combine mayonnaise, dill weed and salt.
Mix well.
Spread evenly over top of salad.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and chill several hours.

title: rice pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks with butter and sugar. Add rice, salt and milk. Cook until thick.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Bake at 350° until firm, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: olive cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Shape into ball. Chill overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Add one cup Velveeta cheese and one stick margarine.
Cover and let set until margarine and cheese are melted.
Melt one stick margarine in small saucepan.
Add cracker crumbs to melted butter.
Mix well.
Pour broccoli into casserole and top with crumbs.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
May be made one day before it is baked.

title: forgotten kisses
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix all ingredients together. Drop dough onto foil lined cookie sheet with a teaspoon.
Place cookies in oven; turn oven off.
Leave in oven overnight.

title: carrot marinade
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over carrots.
Chill for 12 hours. Will keep in fridge 2 weeks.
Serve chilled.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Halve eggs. Remove yolks and mash. Combine with all other ingredients. Mix well. Fill egg whites. Chill.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix tomatoes, onion, bell pepper and sweet pickles in large bowl.
Crumble cornbread and toss in salad ingredients.
Mix together mayonnaise and sugar; pour over salad mix.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar with apples; let stand until sugar dissolves.
Add egg and beat.
Sift dry ingredients together; stir into apples. Add nuts.
Bake in 8-inch square pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix according to package directions.
Stir in cookies with a wooden spoon.
Scape into pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Do not overbake.
Cool completely.
Serve with ice cream on top or Cool Whip.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend sugar, flour, butter and cinnamon until it reaches a crumbly texture.
Spread approximately 1/3 of this mixture on bottom of unbaked pie crust.
Wash and dry the peaches and cut each in half.
Remove pit, but do not peel. Arrange cut-side down on crumb mixture in pie crust.
If peaches are very large, trim off portions and fit them into the empty spaces around the pecan halves.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture evenly over peaches.
Sprinkle 4 tablespoons water over all.
Bake 45 minutes.
The peach skins dissolve into a lush red juice!

title: tiger butter
directions: Combine almond bark and peanut butter; melt in double boiler or microwave until melted.
Spread mixture in a waxed paper-lined 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Pour semi-sweet chocolate over the peanut butter mixture and swirl through with knife.
Chill. Makes 6 dozen pieces.

title: fresh mushroom dip
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, drain on paper towel.
Discard all but 1 tablespoon grease.
Add onions and saute for several minutes over medium heat.
Add garlic and mushrooms.
Add cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Stir until cream cheese is melted.
Remove from heat and add sour cream.
Stir in bacon.
Serve warm with bread sticks or crackers. May be made ahead of time and refrigerated.
Makes 25 servings.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mixture should be very moist. Too many bread crumbs will dry it out.
Create 8 portions.

title: brisket
directions: You will need foil and a shallow pan.

title: chicken spaghetti dinner
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add green pepper, onions, celery, garlic.
Saute until done.
Add tomatoes and mushrooms.
Cook for 5 minutes more.
Mix chicken, spaghetti and skillet mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole.
Cover with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and mixture is hot.
Serve with French bread and green salad.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Place pecans and coconut in the bottom of a 9x13 inch pan. Prepare cake mix as directed on the box, pour over pecans and coconut.
Combine powdered sugar, cream cheese, butter and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto top of cake mix.
Bake at 350 degrees for 60 minutes.

title: posh squash
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, onion, salt, cheese, eggs and pepper.
Add squash to mixture and pour into a casserole that has been sprayed with Pam or greased with butter.
Mix the bread crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Scald milk; stir in tapioca and cook until tapioca is clear and thick.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Cool slightly. Stir some of hot mixture into beaten egg yolks, then stir yolks into rest of hot mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into buttered casserole or souffle dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Set casserole in a pan of water while baking.

title: andouille jambalaya with turkey and oysters(oysters optional)
directions: *If in doubt about amounts, go back and add them again!

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.
Serve and enjoy.

title: passover zucchini and carrot latkes *
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into hot oil in a skillet and fry on both sides until golden brown.
Yields 10 to 12 latkes.

title: lekvar (jam) cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour and beat.
Add nuts.
Work with hands. Divide in half.
Grease
dish (12 x 15-inch).
Press in 1/2 of batter.
(Will be very thin.)
Add preserves (apricot or other), leaving 1-inch from edge.
Press on remaining batter.
(I roll up little balls and pat out with my hands.)
Bake at 300° for about 45 minutes.
Check at 30 minutes.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except broccoli.
Cook broccoli until tender; drain and add to rest of ingredients.
Mix well and put into casserole dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: play dough
directions: Stir ingredients together, then cook in a saucepan over medium heat until dough follows spoon and leaves the side of the pan. Cool and knead.
Store in airtight container.

title: mosaic cookies
directions: Mix well.
Make 2 rolls and roll in graham cracker crumbs. Wrap in foil and refrigerate.
Slice and serve.
This may also be frozen.

title: speedy baked beans
directions: Cook bacon and onion in skillet until bacon is crisp, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat until bubbly. Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 15 to 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed or bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Mix together until crumbly.
Pat 3/4 of it into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix ingredients together by hand until blended.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tomato bread(pretty pink bread - a meat and cheese sandwich special)
directions: Heat tomato juice and butter together until butter is melted. Add sugar, salt and ketchup.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast on warm water; stir to dissolve.
Add tomato mixture and 3 cups flour to yeast.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed, scraping the bowl occasionally, 2 minutes.
Or beat by hand until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour, a little at a time, first with spoon and then with hands, to make a soft dough that leaves the sides of bowl.
Turn onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in lightly greased bowl; turn dough over to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and divide in half.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into loaves and place in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Cover and let rise until almost doubled, about 1 hour.

title: banana split pie
directions: Pie Crust:
Mix cracker crumbs and 1 stick melted butter. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and pat firmly.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes and cool.

title: apple-onion chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow pan.
In skillet, saute onion in oil until tender.
Add apples; saute 1 minute longer.
Pour onion and apples over chicken, melt margarine.
Combine juice, honey and salt and pour over the chicken and vegetables.
Bake 45 minutes or until chicken is cooked.
Serves 6.

title: inexpensive punch
directions: Prepare drink mix according to package directions using the sugar and juices.
Add ginger ale and ice just before serving. Yields 50 servings.

title: quick and easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in hot water.
Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into greased muffin tins .
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: mashed hot potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes in 4 pieces.
Peel and boil until tender.
Mash until lumps are gone.
Stir in onion, pickles, juice and 3 teaspoons bacon grease.
Fold in eggs.
(Salt and pepper are optional.)
Garnish with chopped bacon and sliced egg.
Makes about 1/2 quart.

title: quick and easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Melt butter in large baking pan or dish.
Pour peaches over butter, then pour mixture over peaches; do not stir.
Bake at 350° until crust is golden brown.

title: no knead egg bread
directions: In large bowl thoroughly mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Add butter.
Gradually add very warm water to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes with mixer.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Cover; let rise in warm place for 35 minutes (until double).
Stir down; turn into 2 greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dishes.
Cover; let rise for 40 minutes.
Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes.
Remove from casseroles to cool.

title: quick fudge
directions: Boil sugar, butter, milk and marshmallow cream in heavy saucepan for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips and vanilla.
When chocolate chips are melted, add nuts.
Pour into greased foil pan.
Let set to cool.
Cut into squares.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Measure all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix on low speed with mixer. Drop by tablespoons onto cookie sheet 2-inches apart. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Pour buttermilk, soda and bananas in a bowl and mix well.
Add to first mixture.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in small loaf pans at 350° until done.

title: royer's mexican rice
directions: Prepare rice.
In large skillet, brown ground meat, onion and green pepper.
Drain grease.
Pour in remaining ingredients (except rice and cheese).
Pour over rice.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix refried beans, Sambole sauce, a few black olives, diced peppers, jalapeno juice, and sour cream.
Put in microwave for 2 minutes, and stir.
Sprinkle black olives and cheese on top. Serve with large corn chips or Doritos.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Mix ingredients, except lemonade.
Bake at 350° according to box instructions.
Defrost frozen lemonade; drizzle over top after taking cake out of pan.

title: broccoli-corn casserole
directions: Combine egg with broccoli, corn, onion, pepper and cheese. Mix stuffing with margarine and reserve 1 cup.
Add 1 cup to broccoli mixture.
Pour into a greased baking dish and top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix the cake according to directions on box.
Pour half of the batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion for 5 minutes and drain.
Combine soup, sour cream, carrots and dressing mix.
Fold in squash.
Mix stuffing and butter.
Spread half on bottom of casserole dish. Pour on squash mixture.
Add remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: smashed peanut butter and jelly sandwich
directions: Spread peanut butter on one slice of bread.
Spread jelly on other slice of bread, then smash together!!!!
Add a glass of cold milk!
Life can't get any better!!!!

title: sour cream raisin bars
directions: Mix oatmeal, flour, brown sugar and butter well and press. Add half the mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Save flour mixture.
Fry lightly to a golden brown in oleo. Use juice of large can of pineapple slices.
Combine with 1/4 cup soy sauce; pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 250° for 1 hour or at 350° for 45 minutes.
About 15 minutes before serving, roll pineapple slices in remaining flour and fry lightly in oleo.
Place over chicken.
Serve with rice.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Put pineapple and juice in pan and heat.
Add beaten eggs, flour and sugar; cook 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Later, add marshmallows, chopped nuts and halved grapes.
Thin with whipped cream.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Heat cider; stir in brown sugar.
Add spices.
Continue to simmer, stirring occasionally to dissolve sugar.
Float orange slices on top.
Serve hot.
If serving from an urn, putting cloves and cinnamon in cheesecloth or a tea ball prevents clogging the spigots.

title: yummy potato casserole
directions: Remove skins from cooked potatoes.
Shred into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Saute onion in melted butter until tender.
Remove from heat. Stir in soup and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes and cheese; mix well.
Combine crushed cornflakes with melted butter; sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nissan salad
directions: Boil together pineapple and sugar.
Let boil 5 minutes. Dissolve gelatine in 1/4 cup water and pour into hot mixture.
Let cool.
Add nuts, cream cheese and whipping cream.
Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.

title: vincent price's sweet-hot chicken
directions: Put everything (except chicken) in a small saucepan and heat over medium-high heat.
Stir with a whisk, just until everything is melted and is smooth.
(This just takes a few minutes.)
If you have time, let sauce cool for about 20 minutes before pouring over the chicken.
Let chicken marinate for an hour or 2.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, pumpkin and eggs.
Add rest of dry ingredients and mix.
Bake in greased and floured jelly roll pan. Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.
Cool and frost.

title: crescent taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large skillet brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, olives and taco seasoning mix; set aside.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place triangles in ungreased 10-inch pie pan or 9-inch square pan. Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Sprinkle corn meal over crust.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
(Crust will be puffy.) Remove from oven; spoon meat mixture over corn meal.
Spread sour cream over meat; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 14 to 19 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Serve topped with lettuce, tomato and avocado.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni; drain and place in greased baking pan or dish. Mix eggs, milk, seasoning and cheese.
Pour on macaroni.
Mix well.
Top with more cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 30 or 40 minutes or until set and lightly browned.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix it all together.

title: irish scone
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a loaf pan with shortening.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in butter and raisins.
Place buttermilk, egg and baking soda in a bowl and beat with a fork.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients, stirring until blended. Turn out dough onto a floured board and knead lightly until smooth.
Place in pan and bake. Check after 35 minutes (may take a bit longer).

title: crispy chicken with honey dipping sauce
directions: Mix salad dressing, honey, mustard and peanut butter.
Remove 1/2 cup of the salad dressing mixture; set remaining aside.
Brush chicken with 1/2 cup of the salad dressing mixture; coat with crushed chips.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 9 minutes.
Turn.
Bake an additional 4 to 5 minutes or until chicken is cooked through and lightly browned.
Serve with remaining salad dressing mixture as dipping sauce.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and mash well, add well beaten eggs one at a time.
Stir in 1 stick melted margarine, 1 1/4 c. sugar, mix well. Pour into large casserole dish.
Mix crushed corn flakes, pecans, 1 stick melted margarine and brown sugar.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes.

title: baked mushroom rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Butter a 7x11 baking dish and pour in uncooked rice.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Press in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Blend the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla; spread over crumb crust.
Slice bananas over mixture.
Put pineapple over bananas; spread Cool Whip.
Top with chopped cherries.
Sprinkle nuts over this.
Chill.

title: freezer pie crust
directions: Mix the flour and Crisco well.
Beat together the egg, white vinegar and water and pour all at once over flour mixture.
Mix well.
Divide into 5 parts and freeze until needed.
I pack enough for 1 shell.
I sprinkle salt on rolled out pie crust for better flavor.
Keeps up to 6 months in freezer.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix powdered sugar and dry milk.
Stir in peanut butter, water and chocolate chips.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in graham cracker crumbs.
Makes 25 or so.

title: jello-rice salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add rice, marshmallows and pineapple.
When it begins to congeal, add whipped cream.
Chill.

title: *chocolate caramels
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar, syrup, milk and chocolate. Cook to 240° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour into greased container (about 8 x 8-inch).
Let cool completely and cut into pieces.
Shape and wrap each piece individually in wax paper.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar, milk, margarine, vinegar and coconut.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and make a well in the center.
Add all other ingredients in the well.
Mix well in mixer.
Place in pans and let set for 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: holiday cranberry slush
directions: Mix jellied cranberry sauce with mixer until smooth.
Add cranapple drink, lemonade and spices.
Mix on low speed until blended and smooth.
Pour mixture into a freezer-safe non-metallic container.
Cover and freeze 8 to 10 hours or overnight.
To serve, thaw slush until it can be easily scooped.
Add chilled, carbonated beverage and stir.

title: soup-er macaroni salad
directions: Cook pasta using directions on package; drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Stir soup mix and mayonnaise together; add to pasta.
Chop or sliver vegetables as desired.
Use whatever combination of vegetables your family likes.
Stir into pasta.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Spray a Bundt pan with Pam.
Add nuts.
Add frozen rolls.
Mix sugars and dry pudding together.
Sprinkle over rolls.
Drizzle melted oleo over top.
Let set out overnight covered with wax paper.
Next morning, bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes and turn onto large plate.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine over tap water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Grease and flour 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Place 1/2 of mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken on top and add remaining soup mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and almonds.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 300°.

title: good morning pancakes
directions: Beat egg until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Grease griddle.
Cook pancakes until it bubbles, then turn.
Cook until golden brown.

title: heavenly layer cake
directions: Cut cake while frozen into 4 equal lengthwise slices.
Place slice on serving plate and spread with some of the pie filling. Continue layering, ending with cake layer.
Frost sides and top of cake with thawed whipped topping.
Sprinkle with nuts or chocolate, as desired.
Chill before serving.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly.

title: baked mushrooms
directions: Thaw spinach and spoon into mushroom caps.
Arrange on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
"Simple but so good."

title: mandarin salad
directions: Cook almonds and sugar over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is melted and almonds are coated.
Cool and break apart.
Prepare dressing.
Tear both kinds of lettuce into bite size pieces.
Toss with dressing, celery, onions, oranges and almonds.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package.
Mix and stir all ingredients together and put in casserole dish.

title: sausage beans
directions: Cook pot of beans; leave soupy.
Fry sausage and onion together until done.
Pour sausage and onion into beans.
Add tomato juice.
Add sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, stirring continually.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: special pineapple chunks
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Combine pineapple juice, vinegar, sugar, cloves, cinnamon stick and salt in a saucepan. Bring to a boil; simmer 10 minutes.
Add pineapple chunks and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from stove; cool.
Refrigerate.
The longer kept, the better it gets.
Delicious with a chicken salad or ham sandwich.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Saute mushrooms in 1/2 cup butter.
Stir in pasta.
Melt 1/2 cup butter in flour.
Stir in broth.
Cook.
Stir until boiling. Add 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Set aside.
Mix together pasta and turkey in greased casserole.
Pour sauce; melt remaining butter and mix with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: the best sugar cookies you ever snitched
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add next four ingredients.
After measuring, sift the dry ingredients together and mix well with creamed mixture.
Roll into balls between palms of hands about the size of a golf ball.
Roll in sugar and "smoosh" down with a decorative cookie marker and the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes or until lightly browned on the edges.

title: crab dip
directions: Add more cream or milk if too thick.
Chill.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, pineapple, coconut and vanilla.
Add melted butter.
Pour in 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake on bottom grate of oven for 45 minutes at 325°.
To keep edges of pie shells from browning too much, put tinfoil around top edge.

title: seven can soup
directions: Brown ground round and onion. Mix with the soup and chili and simmer from 1 to 2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain well.
Combine sour cream and onion soup mix; stir in broccoli.
Place in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: turkey dressing hot dish
directions: Brown sausage with onion and celery until tender, then mix with stuffing according to directions on package.
Put half into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then add a layer of baked sliced turkey.
Add box of peas, mushrooms.
Add rest of stuffing mix.
In saucepan, mix chicken broth and the cream soups.
Heat and pour over the stuffing.
Cover with tinfoil.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: texas delight appetizer
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add 3 tablespoons of salsa and whip until fluffy.
Spread in round quiche dish.
Layer with chili, then remaining salsa.
Place thin slices of Monterey Jack over top and bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Place quiche dish on large platter and surround with tortilla chips.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Preparation:
(Prep. time - 20 min.)
Place chicken breast halves between sheets of waxed paper/plastic wrap.
Pound slightly with mallet.
Sprinkle with pepper and salt (optional).

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni.
Beat eggs
slightly and add about 1 1/2 to 2 cups milk.
Add
salt and pepper to taste.
Butter casserole dish. Cube cheese (about 3/4-pound).
Start with a layer of cooked and drained macaroni.
Drop
in
a
layer
of
cubed cheese.
Add enough of milk
and
egg mixture to cover.
Place small slices of margarine
about
the
layer.
Continue layers until macaroni and milk-egg mixture is used up.
Add more milk if necessary to cover. Top
with
margarine
slices.
Cook in 400° oven until golden brown, about 45 minutes.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook and peel
4 quarts of whole beets.
Slice and pack while hot in
hot
jars.	Mix
vinegar, sugar, water, salt and cinnamon together.
Bring to a boil and boil 15 minutes.
Pour over beets. Seal while hot.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cut Twinkies in half.
Place cream side up in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Slice bananas on top. Add slices of strawberries.
Mix vanilla pudding according to directions on box.
Spoon over strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Refrigerate.

title: heavenly hash browns
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix hash browns, butter, salt and pepper.
Add chicken soup, sour cream and Cheddar cheese.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed corn flakes mixed with melted butter.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate. Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate cream cake roll
directions: Prepare chocolate sponge cake batter and put in sheet pan. Bake according to package directions.
Remove from oven and roll jelly roll style and set aside.

title: cranberry cole slaw
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar; let stand.
Moisten cabbage with orange juice.
Add sugared cranberries, celery and green peppers to cabbage.
Add mayonnaise and mix well.
Can add 1 cup chopped green grapes (optional).

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour; add milk.
Mix well.
Add flavoring.
Bake in a well-greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: This is quick and easy when mixed in the blender.
Mix all ingredients, using egg yolks and pour into two 9-inch pie shells. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. After baking, top with meringue or Cool Whip.
If you top with Cool Whip, add
1 whole egg to pie instead of 2 egg yolks.
Freezes well.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix together Cool Whip and milk until well blended.
Add thawed lemonade and mix together well.
Pour into crust. Refrigerate.
Makes 2 small pies or one oblong pie.

title: french toast
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and 1 tsp. cinnamon in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Add apples and Craisins.
Spread mixture evenly over baking dish.
Arrange slices of bread on top.
Mix eggs, milk, vanilla, 2 tsp. cinnamon until well blended.
Pour egg mixture over bread evenly - cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake with foil over top in 375° oven for 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 5 minutes.
Remove from oven, pour maple syrup evenly over everything.
Let sit for 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: crabmeat mornay
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt the butter and saute the onions and parsley. Blend in flour, cream and cheese until the cheese melts. Add the seasonings, except sherry, and gently fold in crabmeat. It is important to continually stir to keep from scorching.
Just before serving, blend in dry sherry. This is great served as an hors d'oeuvre in a chafing dish with Melba rounds or in patty shells.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix brown sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in bananas.
Sift flour and soda together and add to ingredients.
Add nuts last. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Bake in 2 loaf pans.

title: marv's favorite cheese cake
directions: Reserve 1 cup of dry cake mix.
In a large bowl, combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil.
Mixture will be crumbly. Press crumb mixture evenly into bottom and 3/4 way up sides of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press sides first.

title: acorn squash with apples
directions: Cut acorn squash lengthwise in half and remove seeds.
Place cut side down in shallow baking pan with about 1/2 inch of water and sprinkle of salt, if desired.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Take out of oven and pour most of water out; turn cut side up.

title: herring in tomato sauce(sild i tomat saus)
directions: *If not available locally use 3 small jars and eliminate first step.

title: ham-cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Form into a ball and cover with pecans, if desired.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Put popcorn in a large mixing bowl or dish pan.
Boil all ingredients except popcorn and soda for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Stir well and pour over popcorn, mixing well. Put in large, flat pans and bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir occasionally.
Store in tightly closed container when cool.

title: cherry and chocolate cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix using package directions for 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Fold maraschino cherries into whipped topping. Spread between layers.
Prepare frosting mix using package directions.
Spread over top and side of cake.
Chill until serving time.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine butter, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
After mixed together, add Rice Krispies.
Mix well and shape into small balls.
In a double boiler, melt chocolate chips and paraffin (or dipping chocolate) over hot water.
Dip balls into chocolate with toothpick and place on waxed paper to cool.

title: tuna-potato pie(may use canned salmon instead)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil potatoes until tender; drain. Meanwhile, melt margarine in large skillet over medium heat. Saute vegetables and herbs until tender.
Add spices.
Add flour and cook at medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Add milk and cook until thickens and bubbles, stirring frequently. Remove from heat.
Add drained potatoes, tuna and peas to milk mix.
Stir to blend.
Place 1 crust in 9-inch pie plate.
Spread 1/3 of cheese on bottom, then layer with 1/2 of tuna/potato mix, then 1/3 of cheese, then rest of tuna and last 1/3 of cheese.
Top with 2nd crust.
Trim and crimp edges of crust.
Make vent holes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until golden.
Freezes well.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread crushed pineapple in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Top with cherry pie filling. Sprinkle fruit with dry cake mix; dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mexican rice
directions: Simmer broth, chilies and onions for 10 minutes; add tomatoes and condiments and simmer down.
Add rice; stand 5 minutes and serve.

title: scalloped oysters with celery
directions: Grease dish and cover bottom with 1/3 of crumbs.
Add a layer of oysters and half the celery.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and parsley.
Cover with more of the crumbs and dot with half of the butter.
Add the remaining oysters, celery, parsley, salt and pepper.
Top with remaining crumbs and dot with butter.
Pour on the oyster liquid, cream and milk.

title: carrot cookie bar
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl with spoon.
Pour in a 17-inch cookie sheet pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: crock-pot rabbit
directions: Salt and pepper rabbit pieces thoroughly and place them inside the crock-pot.
Dissolve in another pan the broth, vinegar, molasses, catsup, Lea & Perrins, onion and mushrooms.
Mix thoroughly and pour mixture over the meat.
Cover and cook on low heat for 7 or 8 hours and serve with a mound of long grain and wild rice.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Put brisket in large covered dish; sprinkle with ingredients. Refrigerate and marinate overnight or longer.
Add 1 cup barbecue sauce.
Bake 3 to 4 hours at 300°.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Rub potatoes with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Cut lengthwise.
Remove potatoes to bowl and mash. Saute onion and pepper 5 minutes.
Heat milk.
Add vegetables, milk, butter, salt, pepper, paprika and 1 cup cheese to potatoes; mix well.
Spoon into shells.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 15 minutes at 425° or until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, walnuts and margarine; press in a baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, combine first 5 ingredients.
Place spices in a piece of cheesecloth and tie with string; add to punch.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Reduce to low heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve hot. Yield: about 3 quarts of punch.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cornstarch, water and 2 cups blueberries in a medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 tablespoon lemon juice and 1 tablespoon butter.
Cool slightly.
Place the remaining 2 cups blueberries (raw) in the pie shell.
Top with the cooked berry mixture.
Chill pie at least 3 hours.

title: maw maw's hot chocolate
directions: Mix cocoa & sugar together, then add your two cans evaporated milk, mixing it well.
Then finish filling pot with regular milk. Cook on low or medium heat stirring regular until hot.
Drink & enjoy!

title: yumbo shrimp
directions: Peel, devein and butterfly shrimp.
Place in 9 x 12-inch cooking pan.
Marinate with approximately 4 ounces dressing for at least 30 minutes.
Broil 8 minutes.
Serve in small bowl with marinade.

title: 1-2-3 cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, stirring well after each cup.
Add other ingredients.
Save a little of the batter.
Put in small pan.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, 1 cup milk and the other 1/2 can of pineapple. Cook until thick, like a pudding.
Add 2 tablespoons oleo.
Let cool.

title: hank bryant's vegetable beef soup
directions: Put all ingredients into a large pot (3 1/2 or 4-quart size). Add tomato juice or water to bring it to desired consistency. Cook, covered, 1 to 1 1/2 hours on "low" setting of burner.
A small amount of spaghetti may be added shortly before soup finishes cooking.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Bring peanut butter, sugar and syrup to a boil in very large saucepan.
Add Rice Krispies; mix and press into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch bits together in a pan.
Spread on frosting over Rice Krispies mixture.
Cool; cut as you eat them.
Great for kids' lunches.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix margarine, crackers and poppy seed together; set aside. Shred chicken.
Mix chicken, cream cheese and cream of chicken soup together.
Take oblong baking dish; coat bottom with 1/2 cracker crumb mixture.
Add all chicken mixture (layer).
Spoon on remaining cracker mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy hot fudge sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, put chocolate pieces and evaporated milk. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until the chocolate is melted and the sauce is smooth.
Pour over ice cream or your favorite dessert.

title: curried fruit
directions: Mix melted butter, brown sugar and curry powder in an ovenproof casserole dish.
Drain fruits on paper towels.
Using 4 or 5 (Number 1) cans of peach, pear, apricot, pineapple, etc., add to casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
May be stored in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix ham, pork bread crumbs, eggs, milk and pepper and form into a loaf.
Baste with brown sugar, vinegar, water and dry mustard mixture.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: lite wheat and onion bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
In saucepan, combine milk, sugar, shortening and salt.
Just heat until sugar dissolves.
Stir in egg and cracked wheat, then stir in 2 cups of flour.
Mix until smooth. Add remaing flour.
Knead until elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl and let raise until double, 1 1/2 hours.

title: ricotta-stuffed blueberry pancakes
directions: Prepare stuffing and reserve.
In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer or in a food processor fitted with metal blade, process Ricotta, vanilla, cinnamon and sugar until smooth and fluffy.
In a mixing bowl combine biscuit mix with eggs, milk, butter and a tablespoon of syrup or honey.
Beat until smooth.

title: surprise balls
directions: Roll olives in cream cheese and then in pecans.
Chill for several hours and then slice and serve.
Good at Christmas.
They are real pretty.

title: salty candy
directions: Melt the chocolate over hot water.
Stir in the peanuts and pretzels.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and allow to harden or spread the mixture onto a lightly greased cookie sheet and chill for 15 minutes.
Break into pieces.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix and roll in 1-inch balls.
Brown under broiler or in skillet in small amount of oil.
Set aside.

title: red velvet cake
directions: To Make Cake:
Mix red food coloring and cocoa to make a paste.
Then cream shortening, sugar, eggs and color paste.
Beat well.
Add buttermilk, flour, salt and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add vinegar and baking soda.
Mix by hand.
Pour into a greased pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash potatoes and mix with pineapple, butter and sugar.
Shape into balls around marshmallows.
Roll in crushed cornflakes.
Place in shallow baking dish and bake for 5 minutes at 350°.
Yields 10 to 12 balls.

title: mama's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans, by hand, 50 strokes or electric mixer for 1 minute on medium speed.
Add pecans.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 45 minutes, until it doesn't shake in the middle.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, sour cream, white sugar, oil and eggs together with beater and pour half the batter into a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Save the other half of the batter.

title: raisin walnut pie
directions: Mix together first 7 items.
Pour into an uncooked pie shell. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.
Top with whipped cream flavored brandy.
Serve warm.
Very special for Thanksgiving or Christmas.

title: mint chocolate chip pie
directions: Spoon ice cream into crust.
Melt chocolate; stir until smooth.
Drizzle over ice cream.
Freeze for 6 to 8 hours or overnight.
Remove from the freezer 15 minutes before serving. Keeps up to 2 months in freezer.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside.

title: hoe cakes
directions: Combine cornmeal and salt in a bowl.
Pour in boiling water. Stir constantly. Beat until smooth.
Drop spoonful of mixture into skillet of hot fat.
Pat into flat circles.
Brown on each side.

title: tuna dip
directions: Mix together first 2 ingredients, then add lemon juice, cayenne pepper and soup mix. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: old south tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, mixing well.
Add soda in buttermilk and lemon flavoring and mix well.
Add flour mixing to form a soft dough.
Roll small amount out thinly and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until golden.

title: crock-pot dinner
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Brown onion and bacon. Drain.
Put in crock-pot with beans, catsup, brown sugar, vinegar, liquid smoke and butter beans.
Stir together and cook on high for 30 minutes, then on low for about 2 hours.

title: snickers bar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine butter, peanut butter and sugars using a mixer on a medium to low speed until light and fluffy. Slowly add eggs and vanilla until thoroughly combined. Mix in flour, salt and baking soda. Cover and chill dough 2 to 3 hours. Unwrap all Snickers. Remove dough from the refrigerator. Shape about 1 tablespoon of dough around each candy. Place on a greased cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes. Let cookies cool on baking rack. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: company sweet potatoes
directions: Combine all and pour into a shallow baking dish.

title: winter salad
directions: Everything is supposed to be sliced (like little squares). Put in the salad bowl.
Cover with mayo, then mix together.
This is Russian cuisine.

title: sour cream salad
directions: Drain the fruit.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Tastes better the second day.

title: whiskey steaks dijon
directions: Season steaks with salt, pepper and garlic.
Heat butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add steaks; saute 2 to 3 minutes on each side (desired doneness).
Remove from skillet; keep warm. Add mushrooms to drippings.
Saute 1 to 3 minutes.
Stir in whiskey, mustard and stock.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Return steaks to skillet; turn to coat with sauce. Garnish with watercress.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in covered quart jar; shake well or mix in blender or food processor.
Keep refrigerated.

title: strawberries
directions: Mix milk, coconut and gelatin very well.
Shape by teaspoonfuls into strawberries.
Tint sugar and slivered almonds with food coloring.
Dip end of strawberry into sugar and place almond stem in each.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni; let cool.
Mix well all ingredients. Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients with a fork in a medium size casserole dish, adding Grape-Nuts last.
Place glass casserole dish in a pan of water and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Test with a sharp knife.
Pudding should be firm.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Mix together the flour and shortening with a pastry blender until flour is the size of small peas.
Beat together the vinegar, egg and water.
Add to flour mixture and mix well.
Divide dough into two equal parts; roll and chill for 30 minutes.
Roll out one of the crusts into a 9-inch pie pan and pat into pan.
Reserve 2nd portion or make two pies.

title: cherry tart
directions: Mix together margarine flour and sugar.
Line cookie sheet pan with mixture.
Pat on sides and bottom.
Bake at 375° for 18 minutes (until brown).
Beat the cream cheese and confectioners sugar together until smooth.
Beat the Dream Whip, cold milk and vanilla as you would whip cream.
Combine both mixtures (cheese and whip).
Spread over baked, cool crust.
Put cherries on top. Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spread hash browns in casserole dish.
Salt and pepper to your desire.
Mix chicken soup, sour cream, cheese, green onions and butter.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 325°.

title: butter herb baked fish
directions: Melt butter in long baking dish 5 to 7 minutes.
Mix crumbs, seasonings and cheese.
Dip fish first in butter, then crumbs. Arrange fish in pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lobster love(serves 4)
directions: Thaw the lobster tails.
With a knife, remove the shell from the lobster tail and cut lobster tail into 1-inch pieces.
In a heavy saucepan, melt butter.
Add olive oil and lobster meat; saute until the meat stiffens and turns white.
Add onion, chervil and thyme; saute 3 more minutes.
Add the bourbon and wine.
Set the bourbon and wine aflame and let blaze for 20 seconds, then cover to put the flame out.
Empty the can of tomatoes, saving the juice. Chop the tomatoes into coarse chunks.
Add the tomatoes and juice to the pan; stir well.
Simmer slowly for 5 more minutes.
Add 3 dashes of cayenne.
Stir and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, green pepper and onion.
Add 1 cup chopped pecans.
Mix well.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in 1 cup chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and toss with the following dressing:

title: lemonade pie
directions: Thaw lemonade and beat with mixer.
Add Cool Whip and milk. Beat until smooth.
Pour into crusts and chill.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil and drain potatoes.
Mix with mixer until well creamed. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Place in 9 x 13-inch dish. Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable meat loaf
directions: Mix together; shape into loaf pan and bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together; pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole and bake at 350° until set (45 minutes to 1 hour).
Cover with grated cheese.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine ingredients and mix for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix Bisquick and margarine in 9-inch pie plate.
Pour boiling water over butter mixture.
Stir with a fork until dough forms soft ball and cleans pie plate.
Pat dough evenly over the edge of pan.
Pinch all over with fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 450°.

title: old-fashioned popcorn balls
directions: In saucepan, mix sorghum, granulated sugar, brown sugar and 1/2 cup water.
Cook to the hard ball stage (about 300°).
Add butter and cook 30 seconds.
Add vinegar.
Add soda in 1 tablespoon hot water.
Stir.
Pour foaming onto popcorn.
Stir. You can leave it as is or you can form into balls.
To form into balls, put margarine on hands so
balls will not stick to them.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain well.
Add sour cream, salt and pepper.
Let simmer for about 10 minutes.
Add mushroom soup. Heat until creamy.
Cook egg noodles in salted boiling water as directed on package.
Drain well.
Spoon meat mixture over egg noodles.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and drop in grease.

title: bran muffins
directions: Cream sugar and margarine. Sift soda, flour and salt. Pour boiling water over crushed wheat and let cool. Cream sugar and margarine. Add eggs, buttermilk and cooled wheat. Sift dry ingredients and add all at once with bran. Mix until moist. Fill tins 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Will keep in refrigerator 5 weeks or more. One pint makes 1 dozen. Makes several dozen. Can do ahead.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces.
Heat oil in a large, heavy skillet.
Drop in garlic; add meat and brown very well on both sides over medium heat.
Remove meat and discard garlic.
Cook onion and mushrooms in drippings until tender.
Blend flour, salt and pepper into fat.
Stir in water and wine gradually.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Place browned meat slices in gravy.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes or until meat is tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Blend sour cream and cream cheese until smooth; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
If tortillas are not flexible enough to roll easily, place in microwave oven on Low for 1 or 2 minutes until soft.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Add a few bouillon cubes to taste.
Boil 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips. Refrigerate overnight.
Add cheese and crushed potato chips on top before baking at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour off excess fat, if any.
Cook onion and pepper for about 3 minutes in skillet with a little grease.
Stir in creamed corn.
Mix Jiffy cornbread mix by box directions in bowl.
Pour a layer of cornbread mix in bottom of casserole dish.
Stir in all of hamburger mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture.
Pour remaining cornbread mix over that.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: Put olive oil in saucepan.
Put onion and garlic into oil until onion turns clear.
Add meat.
Brown meat, then add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 2 hours.
Then add to cooked spaghetti.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Mix together.
Let set minimum of 6 to 8 hours (preferably overnight), for best flavor and aroma.
Serve warm.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Add water to fresh fruit.
Combine 1st four ingredients together in a large bowl, stirring well.
Add fruit.
Toss gently. Place in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll pie crust thin and cut into squares, big enough to fold over apple mixture.
Cube apples (1 per each pie square).
Add 1 tablespoon or more sugar to each, sprinkle cinnamon and add 1 teaspoon butter.
Fold corners of crust together and pinch shut. Place dumplings in pan.
