Heat water, 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over dumplings.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in melted butter, then in crumb mix.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, uncovered.
Do not turn.
Do not overcook, chicken becomes dry.

title: break-away bread(pull apart bread)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In a large bowl, pour boiling water over shortening and dissolve.
Add sugar, salt, eggs, dissolved yeast and gradually add flour.

Mix well and refrigerate overnight in a large plastic bowl, covered. Dough will be very soft. When ready to use, turn out on well floured board and knead lightly. Roll dough to about 1/4-inch and cut with biscuit cutter. Dip each biscuit in melted margarine and stack in Bundt pan.
Let rise 2 to 3 hours. Bake
at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.
Makes 2 pans.
Recipe may be cut in half.

title: billy graham's mother's famous tea
directions: Strain the orange and lemon juices.
Mix the juice in the tea. Serve quite hot.

title: stuffed shells with cheese
directions: Cook shells in salted water until just slightly bendable. Rinse in cold water after draining and then set in cold water to stop cracking.
Mix together Ricotta cheese, one 16 ounce package of Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese and spices.
Blend well.

title: sauce for meatballs
directions: Put in saucepan. Melt jelly on low heat. Add mustard, more or less to taste. Simmer meatballs at least 30 minutes.

title: charcoal broiled shrimp
directions: Start charcoal fire until coals are white.
Place 10 shrimp on a skewer.
Season lightly with Lawry's.
Place skewers on the grill about 6-inches above coals.
Broil 3 minutes on each side. Baste with barbecue sauce and keep turning and basting for 6 minutes.
Remove from skewers and serve with drawn butter and lemon.
Enjoy!

title: beef heart and dressing
directions: Cook heart in water until tender.
Cube bread.
Mix with milk and broth.
Add butter, onion, sage and pepper; mix well.
Spread half of mixture in baking pan.
Cut heart in half; place over dressing.
Cover with remaining dressing.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Combine hash browns, soup, sour cream and cheese. Spread evenly in a 9 by 13 inch ungreased pan. Cover pan with foil. Bake for 2 hours (remove foil after one hour). Spread topping evenly over potatoe mixture and bake an additional 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple crisp #3
directions: Mix and drop by spoonfuls in 9 portions on apples.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: nippy salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water (drain pineapple).
Then add all ingredients together.
Mix well and chill.

title: marie's pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Have flour sifted 3 times with cream of tartar.
Add flour and eggs alternately, beginning with flour and ending with flour.
Add vanilla.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: easy fantasy fudge
directions: Lightly grease 13 x 9 inch pan.
Mix margarine, sugar and milk in heavy 2 1/2 to 3 quart saucepan; bring to full rolling boil on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes on medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234 degrees, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Cool at room temperature, cut into squares.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown meat with salts.
Add cheese and onion.
In a saucepan heat soup, milk, Velveeta, dip mix, chilies and pimento.
Soften tortillas, add meat mixture, roll and place in greased casserole. Pour soup mixture over and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry rice salad
directions: Cook rice in water until tender.
Drain rice, reserving water. Dissolve jello in 1/2 cup hot rice water.
Add sugar, rice and pineapple.
Refrigerate.
When partially set, add Cool Whip.

title: beef and lentil stew
directions: Coat cubed beef with flour and brown in hot oil on all sides in a Dutch oven or large saucepan.
Add lentils, tomatoes, soy sauce and 1 3/4 cups water.
Stir once.
Cover and simmer 2 hours or until beef and lentils are tender, stirring mixture gently occasionally.
Stir in jalapeno peppers and cook only until heated. Serve with sour cream, cilantro and diced red bell pepper, as desired.
Crusty French bread and a salad make a nice meal.

title: barbecue sauce recipe
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer over low heat.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add whole cranberry sauce and stir until blended.
Chill until partially thickened.
Add nuts and crushed pineapple.
Pour in greased dish.
Chill.

title: lincoln logs
directions: Cut bacon in three sections.

title: wanda's coconut crunch
directions: Mix ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes to crumble and to golden brown.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald milk and pour over bread crumbs.
Cool and add other ingredients, mixing well. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake about 1 hour at 350° until you can insert a knife and it comes out clean.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Combine butter, evaporated milk, sugar and salt in saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
(Start timing when mixture starts to "bubble" around edges of pan.)
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute until marshmallows melt and blend.
Pour into 8-inch square buttered pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients in order given. Pour into a greased loaf pan or casserole dish.
Form into a flat loaf.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serve immediately with or without ketchup.

title: spaghetti and beef casserole
directions: Heat butter in a heavy skillet.
Add ground beef and onions. Saute until meat is browned, stirring to crumble; drain off pan drippings.
Combine mushrooms, tomato sauce, tomato paste, oregano and garlic powder.
Add to meat mixture; mix well.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Place half of spaghetti in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: quick minestrone beef soup
directions: Crumble beef into 6 to 8-quart pot; cook over moderate heat 3 to 4 minutes.
Add onion and cook until limp.
Add tomatoes, water, bouillon, basil, oregano and garlic salt.
Bring to boil; reduce heat; cook gently 5 to 10 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables and macaroni.
Add zucchini, wine, garbanzo beans, kidney beans and cook until macaroni is tender.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, soda, baking powder and extract, then add milk and flour.
Add in small amounts until dough is stiff enough to roll.
Roll out and cut as desired.
Bake at 300° to 325° until lightly browned.

title: pepper steak with rice
directions: While rice
is cooking, cut steak to 1/4-inch thickness and cut
into
1/4-inch wide strips.
Mix with paprika.
Allow to stand while preparing other mixtures.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix chocolate cake mix as directed, except substitute 1/2 cup butter for oil.
Pour 1/2 of cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
tags: pudding style German chocolate cake mix

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a tight container and chill.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, eggs, vanilla, salt and soda dissolved in sour milk.
Add apples and sifted flour.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix salt and flour. Mix yeast and water; let bubble. Add sugar, milk and shortening. Start mixing; add salt and flour mixture evenly. Pinch and bake at 350° until done.

title: old-fashioned soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream
butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add vanilla. Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Drop one full tablespoon
of mixture on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, cream well.
Add 1 egg at a time. Beat well after each egg.
Reduce speed.
Alternate flour and sour cream.
Add vanilla.
Add black walnuts, if desired.
Bake in greased tube or Bundt pan at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Test for doneness as it may take a longer baking time.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients according to directions on grits box.
Do not use instant grits.
Into hot grits, stir remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream oil, butter and both sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients into creamed mixture and mix well. Chill the dough before shaping.
Preheat oven to 375°.
With spoonful of dough, roll into ball.
Roll each ball into granulated sugar or colored sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Press a crisscross design on top of each cookie using a fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Dough may be kept in refrigerator for several days.

title: hot seafood canapes
directions: Saute shallots in 1/2 stick of butter.
Add thyme, bay leaves and dash of cayenne and saute for 3 minutes.
Remove bay leaves and add shredded crab meat, pimentos and dash of Tabasco.
Blend flour and rest of butter.
Add milk and cook until it thickens slightly.
Combine mixtures, adding wine and brandy.
Spread on toast rounds and top with grated cheese.
Broil quickly so cheese will melt.
Makes approximately 1 cup.

title: olive, nut sandwich
directions: Mash cream cheese with fork.
Add mayonnaise; blend well. Stir in pecans, salad olives, olive juice and pepper.

title: cheese pops
directions: Beat cream cheese and milk in small mixer bowl on medium speed, scraping bowl often, until smooth (1 to 2 minutes).
Add cheese and green onions.
Continue beating until well mixed (1 to 2 minutes).
Cover; refrigerate at least one hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in pecans.
To serve, place pretzel stick in each ball.

title: tuna noodle
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add Miracle Whip, more or less to taste.
Refrigerate immediately.

title: texas style chili
directions: In a large saucepan, brown the beef cubes (half at a time) with onion and garlic in hot oil.
Stir in beef broth, water, sugar, oregano, cumin, cayenne, paprika and bay leaves.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in chili peppers and corn meal.
Simmer 20 more minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaves and serve over a bed of rice and beans.
(Don't forget the cornbread!!!)

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins with just enough water to cover them.
Cook until water is almost cooked out of them, then add milk and bring to a boil.
Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Pour into boiling raisins.
Cook until desired thickness, or if needed add more cornstarch.
Pour into pie shells and put top crust on it.
Spread melted butter over crust and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top crust is browned.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cinnamon crescent cheesecake
directions: Press 1 package crescent rolls onto bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cream cheese, vanilla and 1 cup sugar until creamy. Pour over bottom layer of rolls.
Roll out the second package of rolls and put on top of cream cheese mixture.
Melt butter.
Pour over entire cake.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon and sprinkle on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove the skin and the chicken from the bone.
Break up the chicken.
Add 3 cups broth to the Stove Top stuffing.
Let stand about 5 minutes, then mix up with a fork.
In a large baking dish, layer chicken and stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry-nut salad
directions: Combine gelatin with boiling water in large bowl, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Fold in strawberries with juice.
Add drained pineapple, mashed bananas and nuts (chopped).
Turn 1/2 of mixture into a 12 x 8-inch dish; refrigerate until firm.
Spread top with sour cream; add rest of strawberry mixture.
Refrigerate; cut into squares to serve.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Stir dry ingredients with a fork to work air into them. Pour melted shortening into milk and stir quickly to keep from hardening.	Add
to
dry ingredients gradually to make a thick dough.
Preheat
12-inch
Dutch
oven
and	put
baking pan in bottom of
Dutch
oven.
Drop
tablespoons	of
mix in pan and cover.
Bake 10 minutes at medium-high heat.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken in electric skillet.
Set temperature to 350°. Mix ketchup and Coke and pour over chicken.
Cook for 1/2 hour with lid on.
Turn chicken often.
(You can also fix this on the stove top.)

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix well all ingredients
and
pour into a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until lightly browned on top.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Blend together all ingredients.
This will be a very moist dough.
Spoon by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake about 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix together and pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: crowd size cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and carrots.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add to cabbage and carrots.
Serves 125 people.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, cover and chill.
Excellent dip for raw vegetables.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Prepare your favorite lattice pastry. Beat eggs slightly and stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan and dot with butter.

Cover with lattice top. Cover edge with a 2 to 3-inch strip of aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning; remove foil for last 15 minutes of baking. Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: cream cheese killer corn
directions: Place corn in a baking dish.
Cut margarine and cream cheese into corn.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir and serve.

title: turkey a la king
directions: In pan, melt margarine; add mushrooms and green onion and saute.
Blend in flour.
Gradually stir in milk and broth.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens.
Add cubed turkey.
Serve on Pepperidge Farm pastry shells.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Mix shortening in with hands.
Stir in just enough milk to make a stiff dough.
Knead on floured breadboard or cloth.
Shape into biscuits 1/4 inch thick with hands.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ensalada espanola(spain)
directions: Cut cheese and salami into 1-inch strips.
Crush bacon.
Mix cheese, salami and bacon with lettuce, onions, celery, green pepper, cucumbers and tomatoes; toss lightly in a wooden bowl, rubbed with garlic.
Mix vinegar, bean drippings, pepper and salt and pour over the salad.
Decorate with olives and eggs.
Serve with garlic butter on sourdough bread or rye bread.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: betty's tuna salad
directions: Flake tuna.
Add eggs, olives, pickles and mayonnaise; blend well.
Serve on lettuce.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 380° for 10 minutes.

title: meat cups
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, onion, green pepper and seasonings.
Mix in half of the tomato sauce (reserve remainder).
Form meat mixture in 8 balls; place in muffin tins and top with reserved tomato sauce.
To catch any run-over, place pan on cookie sheet. Place in 375° oven for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate clusters
directions: Melt
almond
bark
and
peanut
butter in microwave or double boiler, stirring often to mix well.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Stir	with wooden spoon to coat evenly.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Yields 11 dozen.

title: cookie surprise
directions: Save 2 or 3 cookies for garnish.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Heat water.
Add tea bags (not too strong).
Add remaining ingredients and heat.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Line cooled pie shell with
Philadelphia cream cheese.
Fill pie shell with strawberries.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangle squares.
Spread in ungreased pan.
Pinch to seal seams.
Cook 14 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: italian cream coconut cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.

title: heavenly jam
directions: Combine peaches and sugar and let stand overnight.
In morning, add grated rind of one orange and its juice and pulp of two oranges.
Add cut up cherries as well as juice.
Cook one hour only, after it starts to boil.
Enjoy it.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend pudding with milk. Cream in the cream cheese. If not sweet enough, add powdered sugar to taste. Fold in Cool Whip. Layer cookies and cream mixture (1 layer of cream and 1 layer of cookies). On the last layer of cream, top with remaining cookies and refrigerate.

title: birds nest
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Separate egg and yolk. Beat egg white with beater until it is foamy.
Put spread on bread.
Spoon egg white onto bread.
Add egg yolk to center of egg white.
Bake for 15 minutes or until yolk is cooked and white is golden.

title: cheese logs
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add parmesan cheese, horseradish, olives and pecans.
Blend well.
Divide mixture in half and shape into 2 logs or rolls, using plastic wrap to shape (mixture is sticky).
Chill logs wrapped in plastic wrap for several hours. Chop dried beef into tiny pieces.
Unwrap logs and roll in chopped dried beef.
(Logs could also be rolled into chopped nuts.)
Serve on plate or cheese board with crackers.
Decorate with parsley.

title: chicken noodle casserole(makes 10 servings)
directions: Cook chicken, celery, onion and peppercorns in Dutch oven with only enough water to come to tips of wings for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Remove chicken from pot; cool and remove meat from bones.
Cook noodles in chicken water in Dutch oven, stirring at first.
(There will not be much water, but don't add any, because noodles are to absorb all of broth.)
Add chicken and soups to noodles (and mushrooms if desired).
Transfer to 9 x 13-inch pan; grate cheese on top.
Bake at 350° in oven until cheese melts and casserole is bubbly, about 25 minutes.
Casserole can be frozen before baking or divided.
Freeze half for another meal.
Can be cooked frozen for 65 minutes at 350°.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; slowly bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; stir until blended, then add the oats.
Mix well.
Immediately drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and cool.
Enjoy.
These are actually more like a candy - very sweet.

title: sweet monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Mix cinnamon and 3/4 cup white sugar.
Coat biscuit quarters with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Drop into greased Bundt or tube pan.
Use remaining sugar mixture and add 1/2 cup white sugar and 1/4 cup brown sugar to make 1 cup. Melt butter and add sugar mixture.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Pour over biscuits.
Add raisins and nuts, about 1/2 cup total, if you wish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
Pull apart.
Do not cut.

title: fruit goulash
directions: Mix all together in large bowl and cool.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil.
Beat again.
Add salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Beat.
Add vinegar.
Beat.
This is enough sauce for 6 or 7 halves of chicken.
Put chicken in sauce to soak the day before you need it.
The longer it soaks, the better.

title: nisu bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Heat milk and butter to scalding point. Remove from heat and let cool. Beat eggs slightly and add to yeast. Add milk and mix well. Combine 5 cups of flour and the sugar in a bowl. Pour in milk mixture and stir until blended. Dough will be sticky. Pour onto a floured surface and knead 10 minutes. Add flour as needed. Place the dough in a greased bowl, turning the dough to cover with the grease. Cover and let dough rise until it is doubled in size. Turn dough out and divide into 3 balls. Either braid or lay on a cookie sheet or place each in a bread pan. Let rise for 1 hour. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Makes 3 loaves.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain all of the beans. Combine. Add green pepper and onion. Combine sugar, vinegar and salad oil. Bring to a boil.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables and toss.
Chill 12 to 24 hours. Toss 2 or 3 times.
Drain before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken salad(delicious and pretty too!!!)
directions: Press into 1 1/2-quart bowl; chill several hours.
Turn out onto serving plate.
Frost with one 8 ounce package cream cheese, mixed with 1/4 cup salad dressing.
Garnish with grapes.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine in bowl oats and brown sugar.
Stir butter, syrup, salt and vanilla and mix thoroughly into oat mixture.
Press dough in bottom of pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until it bubbles.
Cool! Melt chocolate chips and spread on top.
Sprinkle on nuts.

title: tostado casserole
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Add 1 1/2 cups of the tomato sauce, reserving the rest.
Add taco seasoning mix, stirring well to mix.
Lime bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole with 2 cups of the Doritos.
Set aside remainder of chips.
Spoon meat mixture over chips in casserole.
Combine remaining tomato sauce and refried beans.
Spread over meat mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes, or until heated through.
Sprinkle with cheese, lettuce, tomato bits and Doritos chips.
Serve with hot sauce.

title: fast food biscuits
directions: Mix flour with oil.
Mix milk, sugar and soda.
Mix yeast with water and add to buttermilk mix.
Add all to flour and oil.
Mix well.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Make biscuits and bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: orange julius
directions: In blender combine all ingredients.
Process for 1 minute or until ice cubes are crushed.

title: oven pot roast
directions: Line baking dish with foil.
Put in roast and top with both soups.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 4 hours or until tender.

title: hot chicken salad #2
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potato chips and grated cheese.
I usually blend the mushroom soup with mayonnaise, adding a little milk to thin mixture slightly.
Bake in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with chips and cheese and bake another 10 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Roast and shred into fine pieces the 2 pound roast.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Cover cabbage with water.
Add 1 teaspoon salt.
Let stand 1 hour; drain.
Squeeze out excess moisture.
Add grated carrot and green pepper (optional).
Boil vinegar and water for 1 minute. Add mustard seed, celery seed and sugar.
Cool to lukewarm.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Freeze in plastic bags or containers. (Good after 1 week, 1 month or even 1 year!)

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix dressing, preserves and soup mix in a bowl. Pour over the chicken. Place chicken in refrigerator to marinate about 30 minutes. Place in a baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°. During the last 15 minutes, add carrots, peppers and pineapple. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large 13 x 9-inch dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: delicious pudding
directions: Use an 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Make a syrup of brown sugar, butter and water.
Make batter by combining remaining ingredients.
Bring syrup to a boil and drop batter by teaspoon into syrup.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, pimento cheese, 1/2 of pecans, onions and Worcestershire sauce.
Add pimento and sharp Cheddar cheese last. After mixing well, put in freezer for 10 minutes.
Shape and roll in pecans.

title: pepper steak soup
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients with 1/2 cup water.
Cook on stove over medium for 1 hour or in crock-pot for 3 to 4 hours.

title: apple cookies
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and egg and beat until smooth.
Mix all dry ingredients together and slowly add to creamed mixture.
Hand mix raisins, bits, nuts and apples.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: toad in the hold(yorkshire pudding and sausage)
directions: In blender combine the flour, eggs, milk, salt and a few grindings of pepper and blend at high speed for 2 to 3 seconds. Scrape sides of blender and blend again for 40 seconds. Refrigerate the batter for at least 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 400°. Place sausages in a heavy skillet and prick them once or twice with a fork.
Sprinkle them with 2 tablespoons water.
Cover and cook on low heat 3 minutes.
Remove top and cook until brown.
Arrange sausages in a single layer in baking dish.
Moisten with 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Keep 1 inch apart.
Pour batter over them and bake in middle of oven for 30 minutes or until pudding has risen over top of pan and is crisp and brown.
Serve at once. Serves 4.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: gumbo burgers
directions: Brown
hamburger
meat and onion.
Add catsup, mustard, salt and
pepper
to
taste and chicken gumbo soup.
Stir and heat until bubbly.
Serve on open faced hamburger buns.	This is quick and easy and kids like it!

title: green rice casserole
directions: Cook rice until fairly tender (makes about 2 cups).
Saute onion in butter.
Cook broccoli in salted water and drain.
Toss all together and add Cheez Whiz.
Put in buttered casserole dish. Heat in 350° oven until it becomes bubbly, 5 to 10 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Cook until thick and cool.
Fold in 1 cup cream, whipped. Spread on firm Jell-O and sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: oranges in red wine
directions: Dissolve sugar in water in saucepan.
Add rest of ingredients, except orange sections, and boil until slightly syrupy, about 20 minutes.
Strain into serving bowl and cool slightly.
Add oranges.
Refrigerate until very cold.

title: devilish broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, raisins, sunflower seeds, onions and bacon pieces.
Make dressing of remaining ingredients.
Stir into first mixture; marinate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: "dressed up" grapefruit
directions: Gently toss grapefruit sections and sliced pitted dates with grapefruit juice seasoned with cinnamon, brown sugar and grated lemon rind.
Bake, uncovered, in a moderate 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Scatter chopped pecans on top before serving.

title: spaghetti torta
directions: Butter an 8-1/2 inch springform pan.
Coat inside of pan evenly with grated parmesan cheese.
Cook spaghetti according to pkg. directions.
Drain, rinse with cold water, drain again. Transfer spaghetti to a large bowl.
Remove sausage from casing and discard casing.
Crumble sausage in skillet and cook thoroughly over medium heat.
Drain all but 1 Tbsp. drippings from pan.
Add onion and mushrooms and saute until soft but not brown. Add to spaghetti to bowl.
Add olives, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Toss to combine thoroughly.
Turn half of spaghetti mixture into prepared pan.	Cover with cheese and top with remaining spaghetti mixture.
(Can be covered and refrigerated at this point.

Increase cooking time by 10 minutes if chilled.) Cover with foil and bake at 375 degrees 35 to 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated.	Remove from oven and let sit for 10 minutes. Run a knife around the inside edge of pan before unmolding.
Cut into wedges and serve with spaghetti sauce.

title: potatoes, onions and mushrooms au gratin
directions: Cook potatoes in their jackets.
Cool, peel and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Heat butter in a large kettle.
Saute mushrooms a few minutes until lightly browned.
Stir in flour, then milk, cream and consomme.
Add cheese, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook, stirring, until smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat and add the potatoes and onions, mixing carefully.
Spoon into a shallow 4-quart casserole or two smaller ones, whatever best fits your oven.
Remember that one shelf will be used for the chicken, the second for the potatoes.
Cover casserole and refrigerate until 1 hour before serving.
Bake in a moderate oven, 350°, for about 1 hour, or until golden on top and bubbly.

title: debbie's sour cream banana bread
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, bananas, sour cream and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 60 minutes. Cake test with a toothpick.
The more ripe the bananas, the better the bread!

title: recipe for take out
directions: Gingerly mix the first three ingredients until he is the consistency of putty in your hands.
Smooth the mixture over with generous portions of smiling.
Next, garnish with "I love you's." After mixture has been thoroughly blended, knead the dough out of his wallet and hand over the last two ingredients.
Chill at home for 15 minutes while he goes out to get it.

title: peanut butter chocolate cookies
directions: Beat butter in a large bowl. Gradually add sugar, brown sugar and egg whites. Stir in peanut butter and vanilla. In another bowl, mix baking soda, flour and salt. Gradually add to other mixture. Stir in Butterfinger bars. Roll dough in 1 1/2 inch balls. Cook at 350° for 11 minutes. Cool 3 minutes.

title: tuna balls
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine tuna, egg, bread crumbs, onion, parsley, mayonnaise, poultry seasoning, mustard, black olives and almonds.
Shape into balls (makes 40).
Take each ball and roll in cornflakes, coating each ball.
Dip balls into melted butter. Arrange in shallow baking pan.
Bake ten minutes.
Excellent hors d'oeuvres served on cocktail picks.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Stir in pizza sauce, mushrooms and oregano.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Heat oven to 400°.
Spoon on hamburger buns and top with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Mix together.
Press crust into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: "mom walker's" buttermilk pound cake
directions: Blend sugar with softened butter until smooth and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour with salt and baking soda.
Mix this alternately with the buttermilk into the butter mixture.
Add the flavoring.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done (inserted toothpick comes out clean).
That's all!!

title: veggie pork chop casserole
directions: Slice potatoes, carrots and onions.
Layer in greased baking dish.
Top with partially fried seasoned pork chops.
Repeat until ingredients are used up.
Prepare 1 can cream of chicken or cream of mushroom and 1 can of hot water.
Heat this and pour over vegetables and meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, butter and milk to rolling boil.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and salt.
Mix while slowly adding oats. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: chili cheese corn bread
directions: Combine chilies and cheese in small bowl.
In another bowl, prepare corn bread mix with milk and eggs.
Pour half into greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Spread chili cheese mixture evenly over batter. Cover with remaining batter and remove.
Cut into squares and serve hot.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook Mexican cornbread as directed on package.
Cool and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into baking dish. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: microwave corned beef and cabbage(the convenience of fast cooking with slow-cooked flavor.)
directions: Place the corned beef and seasoning in large roasting bag (few small air vents after sealing).
Set roasting bag in 4-quart casserole.
Cook on low for 40 minutes*.
Open bag.
Add potatoes, carrots and onion; close bag.
Cook on low for 20 minutes.
Add cabbage to bag.
Cook on low for 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Let stand covered for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tasty vegetable soup
directions: In a large pot fry bacon, save oil. Add vegetable oil and saute onions and celery, until tender. Add flour and toss until it forms a nice roux. Add water while stirring. Add all ingredients except zucchini, noodles, and tomatoes. Cook until carrots and potatoes are tender. Add remaining ingredients and cook until noodles and zucchini are tender but not mushy.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar, Jell-O and cornstarch together until thickened.
Pour over berries in crust. Refrigerate until set. Serve with Cool Whip topping.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add marshmallows.
Leave overnight in refrigerator.
The next day, drain fruit cocktail.
Add fruit cocktail and maraschino cherries to pineapple and marshmallows. When ready to serve, add whipped topping and slice bananas on top.

title: robert redford pie
directions: Mix margarine, pecans and flour; press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and cool.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Take chocolate pie filling and mix with 1 1/2 cups cold milk.
When it begins to thicken, make a layer over cream cheese layer.
Repeat this step with next box of vanilla mix.
Top with Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cranberry ice
directions: Cook cranberries in water to boiling and allow to cook for a few minutes or until berries are soft.
Run through sieve.
Return to saucepan and add sugar and grated rind.
Heat again until added sugar is dissolved.
Skim any foam off top.
Add orange juice, remove from heat and allow to cool.
Pour into refrigerator trays and freeze.
When firm, remove from freezer and turn into mixing bowl.
Beat with mixer until fluffy.
Refreeze until ready to serve.
Can serve as an appetizer or along with a meal.

title: scalloped potatoes with pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in hot oil in a 12-inch skillet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour, 1 1/2 teaspoons of salt and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper.
Add chicken broth and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Place potatoes in bottom of an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with onion.
Pour chicken broth mixture evenly over top.
Top with pork chops.
Cover with foil. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove foil and continue baking 30 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: our favorite meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except catsup.
Spray a baking dish with nonstick spray and shape meat loaf in dish.
Cook for 40 minutes at 350°.
Spread catsup over top and cook 15 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Boil 5 minutes.
Beat until cool enough to spread.

title: cream cheese cucumber dip or party sandwich spread
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: cream rolls
directions: Bake at 350° until nice and tan.

title: oatmeal cinnamon drops
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, molasses and vanilla.
Combine flour, cinnamon, soda and salt gradually to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, raisins, nuts and chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes or until light brown.
Yield: 6 dozen.

title: crazy cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in 9 inch square pan, mixing well.
Make 3 wells in dry ingredients.
In first well put vegetable oil, in second well put vinegar, in third well put vanilla.
Pour water over all.
Mix thoroughly with fork.
Bake at 350 for 30-35 minutes.
Ice if desired or sprinkle with confection sugar.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve.

title: low-fat mexican plate
directions: Saute the ground beef, then place in colander and rinse well under very hot water.
Drain and keep hot.
Meanwhile, heat the beans in a small saucepan (caution: mixture is very thick and will burn easily; you may have to thin it with water).
Cover a platter with large tortilla chips and warm in microwave.
Drizzle the chips with the hot bean mixture and ground beef.
Add shredded lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Sprinkle lightly with ranch dressing, serve immediately.

title: refrigerator white rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Heat to melt shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 cup of flour; beat well.
Beat in yeast mixture and egg.
Add remaining flour; beat well.

title: tangerine mimosas
directions: Pour 2 oz. of juice in the bottom of each flute.
Fill with champagne and stir gently. Garnish with a blood orange twist and serve immediately.
Do not assemble cocktails in advance, as they are best fresh.

title: chocolate 'n oat bars
directions: Combine and mix flour, oats, brown sugar and butter. Reserving 1/2 cup, press remaining oat mixture on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing well.
Add milk and flour, blending well.
Add coconut.
Pour into lightly greased (use Pam) 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Makes its own crust.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: orange cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add ground raisins or dates and orange peel. Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese-potato casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients together in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. If desired, sprinkle bread crumbs on top and drizzle 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, covered, and then bake 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in whipped cream and spread over cooled crust.
Chill and set.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add strawberries.
Stir until thawed.
Chill until partially set. Pour over cream cheese.
Chill until set.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in pan. Add rest of ingredients, except berries. Drizzle butter on top.
Add berries. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mom's holiday dressing
directions: Place the white bread, biscuits and cornbread on the cookie sheets (open the biscuits and cornbread in half) and place in oven to dry out (toast lightly).

title: pecan refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and oleo. Add egg, then flour and chopped nuts. Dough will be rather stiff. Roll out
on wax paper to form a roll. Chill in refrigerator until firm.
(May be left overnight.) Slice about 1/3-inch thick.
Lay on greased cookie sheet pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate candy cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar; mix well and set aside.
Combine water, butter and cocoa in a heavy saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir into flour mixture.
Stir in buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
While warm, prick surface at 1-inch intervals with a meat fork; spread with Chocolate Candy Frosting.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and thin with clam juice to "dip" consistency.
Add green onions and clams and stir.
Delicious served with Fritos.

title: pork chop and potato bake
directions: Brown pork chops in lightly greased skillet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; set aside.
Combine soup, milk and sour cream. Stir in potatoes, 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 of onions.
Spoon mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange pork chops over potatoes. Bake, covered at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Serve with tossed green salad.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in marshmallows.
Add cold water.
Drain pineapple and save juice.
Add bananas and let congeal.

title: one easy meal
directions: Brown hamburger and place in casserole dish.
Add green beans, corn and mushrooms.
Add a little milk to soup and pour over mixture.
Place Tater Tots on top.
Place in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
tags: cream of celery soup or mushroom soup

title: licorice caramels(ooh good)
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine condensed milk, sugar, butter, Karo and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until 234° on candy thermometer; remove from heat.
Add food coloring and anise; pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool 2 hours or more.
Cut and wrap in waxed paper.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs.
Add alternately flour and applesauce.
Stir in salt, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.

title: pennsylvania dutch cucumbers
directions: Wash cucumber and score and peel lengthwise with tines of fork.
Slice cucumber and onion in thin slices.
Separate onion into rings.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over slices.
Chill thoroughly (about 1 hour) before serving.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Beat sugar, butter and egg yolks together.
Add juice and rind of the lemon and flour.
Add milk, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease jelly roll pan.
Beat sugar, oil, pumpkin and eggs together for 1 minute.
Stir in Bisquick, spice and raisins.
Pour into pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and frost.
A favorite of everyone I have served them to.

title: mushroom canapes
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on bread.
Broil until bubbly (approximately 1 minute).

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix whipped cream with pineapple and marshmallows, set aside. Cook on low egg, sugar and vinegar until sugar is dissolved, then mix all together and chill.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together with your hands and form into small 1-inch balls; bake at 350° on ungreased baking sheet for about 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and unsweetened chocolate.
Beat sugar, eggs, vanilla and flour.
Add chocolate mixture; fold in nuts.

title: biscuit pocket subs
directions: Cut all meat into quarters.
Heat oven to 400°.
Press or roll each biscuit into 4-inch round.
Place 2 pieces of each meat and 2 pieces of each cheese on each round (more if desired).
Top with onions. Top with remaining biscuits; press edges together to seal. Prick top with fork; sprinkle with poppy seed.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 9 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 3 to 4 minutes.
Cut each in half. Makes 20 appetizers.

title: old fashion potato cakes
directions: Take leftover mashed potatoes and dice small onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well; roll into balls and flatten out.
Have the grease hot.
Place patties in hot grease and fry to golden brown.

title: lazy day lasagne
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water, salted.
Drain.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and oregano.
In a greased 1 1/2-quart or 2-quart baking dish, make layers in order using half each of noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and spaghetti sauce.
Repeat.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil on high heat and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Recipe can be easily halved, but decrease the time slightly.
Serve over frozen yogurt or ice cream.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook beef until brown and drain.
Stir in macaroni, sauce mix, water, chili powder, garlic and cayenne pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes.
Uncover and cook 5 minutes longer. Place lettuce, green pepper, tomatoes, onions and olives in large bowl.
Toss with beef mixture.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl and pour into a 9 x 11-inch baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool 5 to 10 minutes and cut into squares.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter or margarine and add brown sugar and vanilla.
Mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda, eggs and salt.
Mix all ingredients together well. Spread in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and chopped nuts over mixture. Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: peggy's shoe-peg salad
directions: Drain corn and olives. Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, skin and debone.
Cube chicken and put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together soups and sour cream and pour on chicken.
Mix stuffing according to directions and put on top of chicken mixture.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: date nut bread
directions: In saucepan, cook the dates in hot water for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in the walnuts, butter and honey; let cool, then stir in the egg, vanilla, flour and baking soda.
Pour into greased bread pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together; mash three bananas into this.
Add cream, eggs and lastly flour with soda in it.
Bake in loaf pans at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: creamy mushroom-filled rice ring
directions: To make sauce, in saucepan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, cook mushrooms and onion until tender.
Add soup, water, milk, wine, paprika, thyme and pepper.
Heat; stir occasionally.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Cut oranges into little pieces. Mix with dry jello.
Stir in Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Chill and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender, drain; add cheese, pimentos, margarine, salt, and sugar.
Place ritz crackers in baking dish; pour mixture on crackers crumbs.
Using more crackers, crush, stir in melted margarine, place on top and brown in oven.

title: zucchini quiche(easy recipe)
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Add salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Put mixture into greased pie pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. This is good served hot or cold.

title: clam dip
directions: Drain clams.
Melt butter.
Cook onion.
Add following ingredients.
Stir until cheese is melted.
If it gets too thick, add more sherry.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: In large bowl, mix first 3 ingredients until well blended, then stir in the rest. Chill 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: karo nut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 300° and bake 45 to 50 minutes (until pie is set).

title: grandmother's molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Push to one side of the bowl. Beat eggs in the other side and then blend together. Mix molasses with water. Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with liquid, beating only enough to mix. Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken supreme souffle
directions: Cube removed crusts.
Put in bottom of greased casserole. Combine chicken, onion, green pepper, celery, Miracle Whip, salt and pepper; spread over cubed bread in casserole.
Cut bread slices into triangles and put on top of chicken mixture.
Beat eggs well and add 1/2 cup or more milk; pour over all, being careful to apply to each triangle of bread.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Before baking, cover top with can of mushroom soup mixed with enough milk to make consistency of gravy. Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top the last 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rice pudding with raisins
directions: Place cooked rice and cooked raisins in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
In large saucepan (preferably Teflon), warm 3 cups of milk. In large mixer bowl beat, with mixer, eggs, sugar, cinnamon and cornstarch with remaining 1/2 cup of milk.
Add condensed milk to this mixture and beat well.
Add entire mixture to warm milk on stove and heat, stirring, until it begins to thicken.
Add vanilla extract.
Pour mixture over rice and raisins and stir well. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: zucchini bits
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Into a well-greased mini muffin pans, spoon mixture. Bake 20 minutes or until golden.
Makes about 24 appetizers.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook until thick.
Cool and put in pie shell.
Beat whites and brown.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In saucepan, mix together the sugar, butter and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Add all dry ingredients.
Quickly drop from teaspoon onto wax paper and cool.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: chinese vegetable stir fry
directions: Heat oil in a skillet over medium high heat. Add broccoli, carrots, cauliflower and celery. Cook for 2 minutes. Add bell pepper and sugar peas. Cook for two minutes. Add sweet & sour sauce. Bring to a boil and cook for 1 minute, covered. Serve vegetables while hot. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: "puppy chow"
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chips.
Pour over Crispix cereal and mix to coat.
In a paper sack, put in powdered sugar. Add coated cereal and shake.
Store in covered container.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter the bottom of a pan or glass casserole dish.
Cut up chicken into small chunks and then put in the pan.
Add your cream of chicken soup and slightly blend in with chicken.
Mix in a couple of tablespoons of wine, if desired. Then add a layer of sliced Swiss cheese on top.
Last sprinkle your bread crumbs or crumbled crackers for a top layer.
Cook 40 to 45 minutes and serve.

title: miracle peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine the peanut butter and sugar; mix well.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Make in 3/4-inch ball; flatten on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet before removing.

title: pin wheel cobbler
directions: Mix crust. Melt 1 stick of oleo in baking dish. Roll crust in rectangle and spread 2 cups of well-drained fruit (of choice) on crust. Roll crust and fruit up like a jelly roll. Cut and place in buttered dish-cut side up. Mix 2 cups of sugar (if blueberries, add 2 cups water), add juice of 1 lemon. Pour over roll and bake until done at 350°.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix drained blueberries, pineapple with juice and sugar. Coat mixture with cinnamon to taste. In a lightly greased 9 x 14 pan, pour mixture. Sprinkle dry cake mix over top of mixture. Dot with slices of butter generously. Sprinkle with cinnamon and pinch of sugar. Top with pecans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: poor man's pie
directions: Combine.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Cook egg noodles as directed.
Drain.
Add layer of noodles, browned ground beef, sauce and cheeses.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: patty's hot hot wings
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash wings and place in a single layer in large aluminum pan. Sprinkle generously with garlic salt. Bake for 1 hour. Drain wings.

title: stuffed turkey roll
directions: Combine egg, oats, salt and pepper to taste.
Add turkey and mix well.
On waxed paper, pat mixture to a 12 x 9-inch rectangle. In saucepan, cook onion and celery in margarine until tender. Stir in sage, thyme, pepper and salt.
Toss with bread cubes and 2 tablespoons water.
Spread on meat mixture.
Roll up meat, jelly roll style, starting from narrow end; press edge to seal.
Seal ends.
Transfer roll, seam-side down, to greased loaf pan.
Halve bacon strips crosswise atop turkey roll.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: easy caramel orange ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put tablespoon oleo in Bundt pan.
Add marmalade. Sprinkle with pecans.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon. Set aside.
Separate biscuits. Dip biscuits in melted oleo, then in sugar mixture.

Stand biscuits on end in pan, spacing evenly. Sprinkle with remaining sugar mixture and drizzle with remaining oleo. Bake near center of oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown. Cool upright in pan 5 to 10 minutes.
Invert onto serving pan.
Makes 18 to 20 servings.

title: caesar salad(serves four)
directions: Tear romaine into 2-inch pieces; wash, dry and refrigerate. Combine in processor garlic, capers, anchovies, egg yolks, dry mustard, lemon juice and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Add olive oil and process until dressing is like mayonnaise.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Place romaine in bowl with 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Pour dressing down the sides of the bowl, lifting the lettuce to coat leaves evenly.
Add croutons and Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: creamy sweet potatoes
directions: Arrange sliced sweet potatoes in greased
1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine flour, salt and brown sugar; sprinkle over potatoes.
Dot with butter, then marshmallows and almonds.
Cover with cream.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, until bubbly and marshmallows brown.

title: pork chop special
directions: Brown pork chops (remove from pan). Saute onions and green pepper, chopped small, in same pan. Add garlic last. Add tomatoes and pork chops to pan. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Uncover and simmer for 15 minutes more. Serve with hot rice.

title: bourbon rolls
directions: Mix milk and bourbon together.
Add cherries, pineapple, vanilla wafer crumbs and pecan halves.
Mix well and divide into 2 rolls.
Will be sticky at first.
Roll each roll in confectioners sugar, then wrap in wax paper and refrigerate.
You can grind the vanilla wafers in blender.
Be sure to use pecan halves.
If dough is too sticky when rolling, keep a small bowl of bourbon nearby and dip fingers in bourbon before rolling.
After refrigerating overnight, you can cut into rolls.
Keep refrigerated at all times.

title: twice baked potato
directions: Rinse and scrub potatoes.
Pat dry.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Cut a thin slice off the top of each potato.
Carefully scoop out the pulp.
Put in a bowl.
Separate eggs.
Add yolk to potato pulp.
Stir and blend until smooth.
Add butter, cream, onion, bacon, salt and pepper.

title: feather rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, combine 2 cups flour, yeast, potatoes, oil, sugar and salt.
Beat at low speed for 1/2 minute.
Add warm water and at high speed, beat for 3 minutes.
Work in the rest of flour by hand.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours; punch down and turn out on floured board.
Work slightly.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into buns and place on greased pan.
Let rise until doubled their size.
Bake at 400° until done (usually about 20 minutes).

title: texas cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Bring to boil the first 3 ingredients; set aside to cool. Sift together the next 3 ingredients.
Beat eggs and sour cream together.
Add cocoa mixture, then add dry ingredients.
Batter will be very thin.
Pour into pan; bake for 20 minutes.
While still warm, mix the next 6 ingredients and spread on cake.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Knead dough on floured surface and roll into 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut biscuits and place on greased pan.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake until lightly brown at 400°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Put into loaf pan and cook at 400° until brown on top, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: healthy fruit and nut popcorn
directions: Mix all ingredients together except honey.
Spread popcorn mixture on cookie sheet; drizzle honey over all.
Place popcorn in a 150° oven and cook until honey has coated mixture (20 to 30 minutes).

title: cranberry fruit delight
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
While hot, add sugar and cranberries.
Let cool.
Add pineapple, nuts and apples.
Pour into jello mold or baking dish, 9x
13-inch.
Chill until firm.

title: slaw
directions: Chop first three ingredients and bring to boil last five ingredients.
Pour over cabbage and let chill overnight.

title: dump cake
directions: Using a greased oblong pan, add ingredients in layers as listed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: classic crab cakes
directions: In a bowl, combine crab, bread crumbs, egg, mayonnaise, vegetables, and seasonings.
Shape into eight patties.
Broil patties or cook in a skillet in oil for 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Serve with lemon if desired.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: green chili stew
directions: Heat
oil
in
large
saucepan.
Add
onion and garlic; cook, covered,
over
low
heat for about 5 minutes.
Uncover pan, stir in	cumin and black pepper.
Saute for 2 to 3 additional
minutes. Add
oregano,
potatoes,
green
chilies and chicken broth. Optional jalapenos or Green Sauce can be added at
this time. Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer slowly for 45 minutes.
Serve very
hot
with shredded Monterey Jack cheese sprinkled on top, if desired.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: family pie
directions: Mix together smoothly with faith in God.
Add 2 tablespoons of wisdom, 1 teaspoon of flavoring of nature.
Then sprinkle generously with faithfulness.

title: apricot mist
directions: Chill all ingredients; mix well.
Spoon scoops of lime sherbet into mixture.
Makes 40 servings.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken with onion salt and bay leaf.
Bone the chicken. Mix soup, rice and broth and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish, reserving 1 can of soup for top.
Place chicken pieces on soup mix.
Cover with 1/2 can of onion rings and rest of soup.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle rest of onion rings on top and bake another 5 minutes.
Brown lightly and serve hot.

title: fourth of july punch
directions: Mix lime juice, pineapple juice, bourbon and rum.
Pour into a punch bowl over ice and add club soda.
Chill.

title: homemade bread
directions: In a Tupperware Fix 'N Mix bowl, put flour.
Do not sift.
Make a well in the bottom.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Add to lettuce mixture and mix.

title: strawberry butter(children's)
directions: Place strawberries, butter and confectioners sugar in blender container; place top on container.
Blend on high until smooth and well mixed.
Serve on waffles, pancakes or toast.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Place popcorn in a large bowl and set aside.
Grease 2 large forks and set aside.
Combine syrup, vinegar and salt in a deep pot.
(Pot must be deep because the syrup boils up and will overflow if not large enough.)
Bring to a boil over medium heat until it reaches hard ball.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour over popcorn and toss to coat with the greased forks.
Butter hands liberally and form into balls.
Press lightly to make them stick together.
Continue forming balls, rebuttering your hands after each,
until all the corn is used.
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat together sugar, pumpkin, eggs and oil. Add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt. Mix well. Add nuts. Spread batter on a greased and floured cookie sheet. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cool and frost.

title: queen ann cake
directions: Sift cake and pudding mixes together. In another bowl, beat oil, eggs and milk. Add to dry mixture and beat well. Bake at 325° or 350°. Makes 3 layers.

title: apricot or peach salad
directions: Put into saucepan the pineapple, sugar and jello.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat and cool.
In mixing bowl, stir together buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Add cooled jello mixture and fold with buttermilk mixture.
Add pecans.
Pour into mold and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours before serving.
(Use 5 cup mold.)

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook the sausage until browned.
Drain well. In a large mixing bowl, combine the cheese, soup, sour cream, French onion dip, chopped onion, peppers, salt and pepper.
Fold in thawed potatoes.
Mix well.
Spread half of hash brown mixture over bottom of 9 x 13 greased baking dish.
Spread 1/2 of the browned sausage over potato mixture. Repeat layering second 1/2 of hash brown mixture.
Top with remaining sausage.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour or until casserole is golden brown.

title: apple rings from large cucumbers
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain; wash well and let stand in cold water for 3 hours.
Mix next 4 ingredients and pour over cukes.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Drain.
Mix next 5 ingredients and bring to boil.
Pour over cukes for 3 days. Each day reheating syrup to a boil.
On third day, put cukes into jars; heat syrup and pour over them.
Seal.
Makes 7 pints.
Store in refrigerator and use as pickles.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bring to boil, cook slowly to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 1/2 c. peanut butter and 1 jar marshmallow cream.
Add 1 tsp. vanilla.
Pour into buttered dish and cut into squares.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In
large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat
in
Eagle Brand until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla. Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.

title: christmas punch
directions: Pour boiling water over tea, let it steep a few minutes and strain; sweet to taste.
When cold, add juices, taste and add more sugar if necessary.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
This will make about 125 punch cups.
Serve in
large punch bowl with block of ice in it.
Top the ice with a sprig of Oregon holly if you like, float orange slice in punch to which halves of red maraschino cherries and green mint cherries have been speared with cocktail picks.
Pour the syrup from cherries into punch.

title: golden chicken casserole
directions: Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish with rice. Layer on onion and green pepper. Salt lightly. Arrange chicken, breasts or preferred pieces, onto rice, enough to cover the rice. Chicken can be skinned.
Salt lightly.
Spread soup from cans over chicken with spatula.
Pour on 2 to 3 cups water. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Add more water, if necessary.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in
unbaked pie shell for approximately 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter
directions: Cook sugar, water and syrup to a hard boil (little yellow). Add peanuts.
Cook until golden brown, less than 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and baking soda.
Mix well.
Pour into a well-buttered cookie pan.

title: mini reubens
directions: Cut Swiss cheese and pastrami slices so they will fit on the pieces of bread. (Do not hang over the edge of bread.)

title: low-fat ranch dressing
directions: In a large bowl, blend package (or seasonings) with yogurt and mayonnaise.
Mix in buttermilk.
This stores well in the refrigerator for several weeks.
Yields 3 cups.

title: thistle dip
directions: Puree artichoke with liquid until smooth.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour before serving. Sprinkle paprika on top before serving.

title: royal apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add water and vinegar; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove.
Add butter and vanilla; pour this over apples.
Put in unbaked crust; put top crust on.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes, or until done.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Mix and bake in 350° oven or put in crock-pot and simmer for 4 hours or longer; stir occasionally.
Start crock-pot on high for 1 hour and then to simmer for 3 hours.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes; melt butter in glass bowl and add chicken. Microwave until soft (about 4 minutes).
Heat soup until it will blend, then add sour cream and salt.
Mix together potatoes, onions, soup mixture and cheese.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix crushed flakes with 1/2 cube melted butter and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift flour, blend in shortening until crumbs are the size of peas.
Beat egg; add vinegar, salt and water.
Mix with fork until mixture leaves the sides of bowl and forms a ball.
Roll out on floured surface.
Makes pastry for one 2-crust pie.

title: simply elegant french dressing
directions: Beat well and store in refrigerator for 48 hours.
Strain. Keep in refrigerator and use as needed.
Makes about 1 1/2 pints. This is quickly made and very good.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill thoroughly.
Serve with crackers.

title: heath bar torte
directions: Blend together first 3 ingredients and pat into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar; add sugar.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Spread on graham cracker crust.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Cool at room temperature.
Crush Heath bars. Reserve 1/4 cup of crumbs.
Blend the Heath bars with 1 quart container of Cool Whip.
Spread onto cooled torte.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: arroz con pollo(chicken with rice)
directions: Shake chicken in seasoned flour, fry in oil till brown.
Cover and cook about 10 minutes longer.
Remove.
Saute onion and pepper in same oil.
Add tomatoes and garlic and cook together to blend seasonings.
Stir in uncooked rice and let cook a few minutes.
Mix all ingredients carefully to blend fully.
Pour boiling water into mixture, add salt and saffron, blend thoroughly and cook about 3 minutes more.
Put in casserole and arrange pieces of fried chicken on top of rice mixture.
Bake uncovered 20-30 minutes at 350° until rice is done.
Rice should not be mushy.

title: german rouladen
directions: Combine carrots, onion, parsley, bacon, salt and pepper. Spread on beef slices.
Roll each slice up and secure with toothpick.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper in large skillet on medium heat; drain.
Add salsa, corn and seasonings.
Layer 1/3 of meat sauce, 1/2 of the tortillas and 1/2 of cottage cheese in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix butter or margarine, onion, evaporated milk, water, cheese and salt in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until cheese completely melts.
Mix cheese mixture with tuna, peas, carrots and noodles.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with more cheese or cornflake crumbs.

title: meringue cradle cake
directions: Beat egg whites until soft mounds form.
Gradually add 1 c. sugar, beating constantly until straight, glossy peaks form.
Fold in pecans, finely chopped and chocolate.
Spread evenly over bottom and three-fourths up sides of 10-inch tube pan, well greased and lined with waxed paper on the bottom.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter. Gradually add 1 c. sugar, creaming well.
Add unbeaten egg yolks; beat well.
Combine milk and vanilla.
Add alternately with the dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Blend well after each addition.
Pour into meringue-lined pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours. Do not underbake.
Cool 20 minutes. Loosen cake with spatula; cool 30 minutes longer before removing from pan.
Decorate top of cake with pecan halves dipped in melted semi-sweet chocolate if desired.
(Cake may be baked in two 9x5x3 inch pans for 50 to 60 minutes.)

title: pineapple rice dessert
directions: Whip the cream; add sugar and fold into the rice.
Add diced marshmallows.
Chill.
Have pineapple well chilled.
When ready to serve, add well drained pineapple and nuts.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place melted margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar over butter and lay in the pineapple.
Prepare cake batter; combine cake mix, water, oil and eggs at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed. Bake 35 to 40 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn pan upside-down.
Top with cherries in pineapple if desired.

title: waldorf fostoria stew
directions: Preheat oven to 250°. Put meat and vegetables in layers in roaster or large casserole and sprinkle with seasoning and tapioca. Do not brown meat before cooking. Add tomato juice and then add water or wine. Cover top of pan with foil, then put lid on tight. Cook for 5 hours in oven. This makes its own gravy.

title: caramel dumplings
directions: Boil for 10 minutes.

title: smoked sausage with rice
directions: While rice is cooking, cover and cook sausage in 1/2 cup water about 5 minutes.
Remove from water and cut in thin slices. Combine sausage, onion, green pepper and celery in large skillet. Cook until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Add quartered tomatoes, broth, cubed, drained pineapple (reserving juice) and seasonings. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with pineapple juice. Pour into meat mixture.
Cook, stirring, until clear and thickened, about 2 minutes.
Serve over beds of fluffy rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple deep dish pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
Roll to fit in top of deep dish.
Place apples in dish.
Cover with sugar and spice mixture.
Dot with butter.
Cover with crust that has slits in it. Bake for about 1 hour.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease Bundt pan and dust with granulated sugar. Sprinkle 1/2 of the nuts in pan. Mix other ingredients. Alternate with nuts and batter. When cake is done, remove from oven and spoon 1/2 of the glaze on. Wait 30 minutes and remove cake from pan and spoon on remaining glaze. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix well and pour onto well greased wax paper in a cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 10 minutes.
When baked, put on well covered dry towel with powdered sugar.
Roll up and refrigerate until cooled.
Unroll and spread with filling.
Then roll again and cover with aluminum foil.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight before serving.

title: creamed corn bake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Mix ingredients thru mayonnaise together.
Spread on large plate. Cover with chili sauce, then crab meat or shrimp.
Cover with dried parsley.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with your choice of crackers.

title: butter pecan ice cream(low carb)
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over water. Let stand until softened (about 5 minutes). In a medium bowl, whisk yolks and 1/2 cup sugar substitute to combine.

title: pizza dough
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve sugar in warm water.
Sprinkle with yeast and let stand 10 minutes or until foamy.
Stir oil into yeast mixture.
Stir salt and about half of the flour into the yeast mixture.
Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a slightly sticky ball.
Knead dough on a lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 8 minutes.
Place dough in a greased bowl and let rise 1/2 hour.
Punch down dough and let rest 15 minutes; cut in half.
Roll out each piece of dough and place on a lightly greased 14-inch pan.
Let rest 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Dough is now ready for sauce and toppings.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: In large Dutch oven, brown the beef.
Drain well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Season to taste (salt, pepper, garlic, etc.).

title: crab ball
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, shape into ball and cover with purchased cocktail sauce. Spread on crackers.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and flour.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Melt margarine.
Pour into other mixture.
Pour into frozen pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach betty
directions: Work together like pie dough (no liquid).
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put layer of sliced peaches with juice.
Put crumbs on top. Bake slowly at 300° for about 1 hour (will be done when light brown).
Serve with whipped cream.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil spices in 6 cups of water for 15 minutes.
Boil sugar, tea and other 6 cups of water.
Let steep for 20 minutes.
Squeeze lemons and oranges.
Mix everything together.
More water may be added, if needed.
Heat to serve.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in large casserole dish and bake slow for 30 to 40 minutes at 275°.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Blend all ingredients except shrimp.
Add 2/3 of shrimp and blend coarsely.
Add rest of whole shrimp to dip.
If too thick, add milk.

title: grandma sue's sweet potato pie
directions: Mash potatoes well.
Combine all ingredients and blend thoroughly. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: jody's killer grand marnier sauce
directions: In double boiler, combine egg yolks, cornstarch and sugar. Beat mixture until it is pale yellow.
Add the warm milk and set over the simmering water.
Whisk the mixture constantly until it gets thick and heavily coats a spoon when dipped in.
Do not boil! When custard is done, remove from heat immediately and add Grand Marnier, vanilla and orange rind.
Allow to cool completely, then refrigerate it covered 2 to 3 hours.

title: curried scallop bisque
directions: Heat butter in medium saucepan.
Add curry powder and onion and cook gently for 3 minutes, stirring.
Add tomato soup and chicken stock and bring to the boil.
Add washed scallops (cut if they are large).
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 5 minutes. Stir in milk, cream, salt and pepper and heat, but do not boil! Taste and add more salt and pepper if necessary.
Stir in 2 tablespoons parsley and serve immediately with more parsley sprinkled on each serving.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Mix bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt, pepper and garlic powder together.
Dip chicken in melted butter and roll in dry ingredients.
Sprinkle lemon juice over coated chicken.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cook onions in oleo.
Add chicken and peppers.
Make sauce:
3 tablespoons oleo to 1/4 cup flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stir in chicken broth.
Cook until bubbly.
Add 1 cup Monterey cheese, then add chicken and other ingredients.
Dip tortillas in sauce before layering them in dish alternately with chicken mixture and cheese, then finish top with cheese.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.
Good luck.

title: susie's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni per box directions.
Drain and put butter and mix with Lawry's salt.
Put in casserole dish.
Add 3 to 4 cans of Pet
milk
and
marinate
for 24 hours.
In a separate dish, beat 1 egg, Pet milk,
Lawry's
salt
and 2 cups of mild sharp
Cheddar cheese.
Mix
in	casserole
dish.
Top
with cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 375° until top is crispy brown.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble cooled, baked cake.
Layer half of cake crumbs in punch bowl.
Top with half each of pie filling, pineapple pudding (made by directions on box) and bananas.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.

title: green beans in olive oil and lemon
directions: Blanche beans (quick in and out of boiling water).
Chill and add onion, oil, lemon, salt and pepper.
Serve cold.

title: mexican pasta bean toss(prep:  15.  cook:  00.  stand:  1:00.  total:  1:15.  easy.)
directions: Rinse cooked pasta in cold water and drain.
In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, yogurt, lime juice, cumin and salt.
Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Let set overnight in the refrigerator.
The next day, pack mixture in jars and refrigerate for at least 48 hours before using.
Store in the refrigerator.
Do not heat juice.
This recipe is made without salt.
Keeps well for 1 year in the refrigerator.

title: fried chicken
directions: Wash and season chicken.
Roll chicken pieces in a plate of flour.
Put oil in frying pan under medium fire.
Put chicken in pan and brown.

title: pig cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter, oranges, eggs and oil.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
In mixing bowl, mix Cool Whip, pineapple, pudding mix and powdered sugar.
Spread between layers and all over cool cake.
Keep refrigerated.
The longer it is in refrigerator, the better the flavor.

title: chicken elegante
directions: Place vegetable seasoning packet and 2 tablespoons of margarine in bowl.
Add hot water.
Stir until margarine is partially melted.
Add stuffing crumbs; stir to moisten.
Let stand until water is absorbed.
Cook and stir chicken in remaining margarine until browned.
Place chicken in baking pan.
Top each piece with stuffing and broccoli.
Mix gravy, mushrooms and apple juice.
Pour over broccoli and stuffing.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add onion, bell pepper and mushrooms.
Fry a bit longer.
Drain again.
Add 3 cans tomato paste and 3 cans water using tomato paste cans.
Simmer 20 minutes; serve.

title: garlic cheese potatoes
directions: Microwave 6 red potatoes 5 minutes.
Remove.
Cut up into fourths.
Spread on baking sheet with garlic powder, butter and Asiago cheese.
Salt and pepper.
Roast until fork-tender, brown and crispy.

title: strawberry champagne punch
directions: In punch bowl combine strawberries, sugar and champagne.
Cover and let stand at room temperature 1 hour.
Just before serving, add lemonade and pineapple juice.
Stir until lemonade is thawed.
Stir in club soda and add ice.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix all ingredients and put in plastic bag; shake.
Scrub potatoes and cut in quarters.
Put in bag and shake.
Put in baking dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Beat eggs.
Add mustard, milk and salt. Mix in bread cubes, cheese and sausage.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove; let set a few minutes before serving.

title: new mexican spoon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except chilies and cheese.
Pour 1/2 batter into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle on 1/2 of cheese and chilies.
Add remaining batter and top with cheese and chilies.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Cool slightly and serve.

title: kellogg's all-bran butterscotch refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg until fluffy.
Stir in All-Bran. Add flour and baking powder, sifted together.
Work into first mixture a small amount at a time.
Knead and shape into roll about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Cover ends of roll so dough will not dry out.
Store in refrigerator until firm.
