Cut into thin slices and bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 425° oven for 7 to 10 minutes.
Yields 7 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook the
grits.
Beat
the
eggs
in the milk mixture, then add to the grits.
Add the oleo and garlic cheese and mix well. Pour
into
greased
casserole
and bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350° or until nicely browned.

title: spinach-cheese open sandwiches
directions: Spinach Combination:
Lightly cooked spinach (drained well), and chopped together with black olives.

title: creamy noodle casserole
directions: Drain noodles well. Return to saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss lightly until well mixed. Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: summer squash-zucchini casserole
directions: Slice squash; boil with onion in small amount of water for 10 minutes; drain.
Mix together the carrot, sour cream, soup and 1/2 package croutons, then fold in squash mixture.
Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients; place in buttered casserole.
Top with remaining croutons.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: "i love my vegetables" medallion
directions: Bring 1 cup water to boil in saucepan over medium heat.
Add beans and carrot.
Season with salt and cook 10 minutes.
Remove pan from heat and place under cold, running water for 3 minutes. Drain vegetables and set aside.
Bring 1/2 cup salted water to boil in saucepan over medium heat.
Add peas and cook 4 minutes. Add yellow summer squash and pepper; continue cooking.
As soon as vegetables are cooked, place saucepan over cold running water for 3 minutes.
Drain well.
Heat butter in saucepan over medium heat. Add garlic, tarragon and all vegetables.
Mix and season with salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Simmer 4 minutes, then serve.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes, slightly boiled, about 20 minutes, shredded in large pieces.
Combine soup with onions, butter, sour cream, cheeses, salt and pepper.
Stir potatoes into mixture until combined.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can top with small amount of additional cheese to melt and form a crust during last 10 minutes of baking time.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream sugars and Crisco.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour mixture, then other ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Can add coconut and raisins or substitute for chocolate chips.

title: sunday supper casserole
directions: Melt Crisco; add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk and cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened and beginning to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in mustard and cheese.
Cut hot dogs in 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange alternate layers of potatoes, hot dogs and cheese sauce in 2-quart greased casserole.
Top with cheese sauce.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate french fudge
directions: In top of a double boiler, melt the chocolate chips.
When melted, remove from heat.
Add the Eagle Brand milk, vanilla, nuts and a dash of salt.
Stir until smooth.
Spread mixture evenly into a waxed paper lined 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Chill 2 hours until firm.
Remove from pan and cut into squares.
Makes about 1 3/4 pounds.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and add milk.
Mix well and cook until mixture starts to thicken.
Add small amount of mixture to beaten egg yolks.
Add egg yolks and cook until very thick.
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Pour in baked pie shell. When completely cooled, add whipped topping, cream or Cool Whip.

title: yummy cake
directions: Mix by hand sugar, eggs and oil.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Top with cream cheese icing.

title: cucumber rings
directions: Cut peeled cucumbers into slices.
Cut out centers.
Throw away centers.
Cover with water to which 2 cups lime has been added.
Soak 24 hours.
Drain, cover with clear water and let stand 3 hours.
Drain.
Cover with uncooked solution of vinegar, salt, oil of cloves, oil of cinnamon and sugar.
Let stand overnight.

title: wild rice-shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly in large bowl.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt brown sugar and butter together.
Cool.
Add eggs.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla together.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian curry*
directions: Add milk to the grated coconut and bring mixture to a simmering temperature.
Add garlic, ginger, apples and onions to mixture.
Blend curry powder with 2 tablespoons of butter.
Add curry powder and butter mixture to the coconut mixture and cook slowly for three hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove mixture from heat and let stand in a cool place for several hours or until the next day.

title: molded egg salad
directions: In a medium saucepan, soften gelatin in water for 5 minutes. Stir over low heat until gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat; whisk in mayonnaise.
Stir in eggs, relish, peppers, celery and onion.
Pour into an oiled 8 cup mold.
Chill overnight, unmolded onto a serving platter.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until barely tender (do not overcook).
Drain noodles.
Combine noodles, ham and milk beaten with eggs and seasonings.
Pour in a greased casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until center is set.

title: zero cholesterol carrot cake
directions: Shred carrots to make 2 cups.
Shred zucchini to make 1 cup. Set both of these aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch Bundt pan.
In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder, salt and ginger.
Drain pineapple well, reserving juice.
In medium bowl with wire whisk or fork, mix drained pineapple, brown sugar, egg substitute, salad oil and vanilla extract until smooth.
Stir pineapple mixture, shredded carrots, zucchini and raisins into flour mixture, just until flour is moistened.
Pour batter into Bundt pan.
Bake 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove cake from pan and cool completely on rack.

title: dell's spinach with shrimp
directions: Cook spinach as directed; drain and squeeze out excess water. Make cream sauce; add sherry and cheese.
Combine cream cheese, shrimp, spinach and artichokes.
Place in casserole; top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Bake covered.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: gingered chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces well and drain.
In heavy casserole, place chicken and remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour until chicken is tender and sauce is reduced but not dry.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, syrup, salt, butter and vanilla thoroughly.
Mix pecans and flour and stir into eggs, sugar, salt, butter and vanilla mixture.
Mix.
Pour into a 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 60 minutes.
Serve cold and top with Dream Whip.

title: orange spice cookies
directions: Cream margarine; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add egg substitute and corn syrup; beat well.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients, stirring well.
Gradually add flour mixture to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in orange rind.
Shape dough into 15 x 1-inch log; wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Unwrap log and cut into 1/4 inch slices.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from cookie sheets and let cool on wire racks.
Yield:
4 dozen (42 calories each).

title: squash and bacon casserole
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Save drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Boil squash until tender; drain.
Brown onion in drippings.
Add butter, squash, eggs, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until eggs are done.
Place half squash mixture in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with half of cheese and bacon.
Add remaining squash and top with remaining cheese and bacon.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter sauce
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and butter; cook to a soft ball stage.
Remove and slowly add the evaporated milk.
Gradually stir in peanut butter.
Wonderful served on ice cream.

title: lemon delight cake
directions: Blend all ingredients and beat at moderate speed for 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in oven or microwave for 15 minutes.
Mix and bake.
Stir halfway through. Serves 4 to 6.

title: vanilla sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar with electric mixer.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add baking powder and flour, one cup at a time, mixing after each addition. The dough will be very stiff; blend last flour in by hand.
Do not chill dough!
On a floured surface, divide dough in half.
Roll pieces into balls so that you can get a circle 12 x 1/2-inch thick.
Dip cutters in flour.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet on top rack for 6 to 7 minutes, or until cookies are lightly browned.

title: snickers pie
directions: Melt Snickers bar and half of the Cool Whip in microwave.
Mix well.
Pour in crust and refrigerate until firm, then add other half of Cool Whip as topping.

title: cheezy potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
In a large bowl, mix potatoes and undiluted soup.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in mixture. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: mrs. elsie's never fail cornbread
directions: Stir well and pour into a well-greased heated skillet.
Bake at 450° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: old-fashioned butter cookies
directions: Measure flour and butter into mixture bowl.
Beat until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Blend in sour cream.
Stir until dough forms.
Shape into a smooth ball.

title: mexican dish
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, green pepper, garlic powder and chili powder.
Mix and heat both soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Combine with meat mixture.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with tortilla chips. Pour mixture over chips and top with 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: eclair pie
directions: Prepare vanilla
pudding
as
on
package, but use 1 1/2 cups milk instead
of
2; mix together pudding mixture and Cool Whip. Place
graham
crackers
on
bottom
of
oblong glass or aluminum pan.
Next,
put
1/2 of pudding and Cool Whip mixture over graham crackers.
Make
another layer and end with graham crackers on top.
This would be three layers of graham crackers and 2 layers of pudding.

title: reuben chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in 4-quart roasting pan or baking dish.
Cover with sauerkraut, then cheese.
Pour dressing over all and bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°, or until chicken is tender.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix and pour over vegetables.
Double recipe makes nice large servings.

title: sauteed scallops and mushrooms
directions: On a high temperature, saute in olive oil the shallots, uncovered.
When shallots become a pale gold, add garlic.
When these become a pale gold, add mushrooms.
Turn down the heat to medium and add salt.
Cover the pan, let this stay for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add wine; let cook another 5 minutes or so.
Now add scallops, hot pepper and parsley.
Add another pinch of salt.
Now turn the pan on high and cook until scallops are finished (about 4 minutes).
Serve hot.
(Feeds about 4 people.)

title: heavenly hash fudge cake
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate over low heat.
Add eggs and sugar. Add to chocolate mixture; then add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 30 minutes.
Put on marshmallows.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs first.
Add other ingredients in order to mixer. Break bread into bottom of ungreased baking dish.
Pour egg and milk mixture over bread.
Take a spoon and hold bread down until it's soaked.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top and bake in a pan of hot water at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until pudding is set.

title: best pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Add cream and flour, a little at a time; beat well.
Stir in flavorings; pour into greased pan.
Start in cool oven at 300°; bake for 2 hours. Cool before frosting!

title: granola cereal
directions: Mix oatmeal, wheat germ, coconut, sesame seed, walnuts and bran.
On the stove warm honey, vanilla and oil.
Drizzle over cereal and toss slowly.
Put on cookie sheet at 325° for 25 minutes.
Toss while cooking.
The following can also be added:
1 tablespoon salt, 2 cups almonds, 2 cups nuts or 2 cups sunflower seeds.

title: tuna melts
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients.
Fill rolls with 1/3 cup tuna mixture.
Wrap in foil.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: celery and cabbage slaw
directions: Mix mustard, salad dressing, vinegar and seasonings.
Add to the chopped cabbage and celery.
Makes 4 servings.
Chopped chives may be sprinkled over the salad, if desired.

title: potato chocolate cake
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes. Measure and set aside. Beat sugar and shortening until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each. Add vanilla and potatoes. Add sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately. Beat until smooth. Stir in nuts and pour into 2
9 inch pans. Bake 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: chili con carne
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and bell pepper until meat is lightly browned and vegetables are tender.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes, beans, tomato sauce, salt, chili powder and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Discard bay leaf.
Add additional water, if needed.
Yield: 6 (1 cup) servings (3 meats, 2 breads, 1 vegetable and 1/2 fat).

title: cheese tetrazzini
directions: Mix ground beef and onion in skillet, brown.
Drain off fat and return meat and onion to pan.
Add salt, pepper and spaghetti sauce (could also add basil, oregano and garlic powder to taste) and simmer 5 minutes.
Beat together with electric mixer cream cheese, cottage cheese and sour cream.
Add green pepper, scallions and spaghetti mix gently with spoon.
Spread sour cream-spaghetti mixture in bottom of buttered 10 x 14-inch shallow casserole. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Pour meat sauce over top to cover.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes in a 325° oven.
For last 20 minutes, sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top.
To prepare ahead, assemble casserole (except Mozzarella cheese); cover and chill. Bake directly from refrigerator, uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes. Makes 8 good sized servings.

title: chicken breast in crock-pot
directions: Put chicken breast and mushroom soup in crock-pot and cook on low all day.
Thirty minutes before serving, add sour cream and any optional items you want.
Serve over rice.

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Bake brownies according to box directions.
Mix cream cheese with some sugar to sweeten.
When brownie cools, spread cream cheese on brownies leaving an inch or so around crust.
Sprinkle strawberries and bananas over the cream cheese.
Finally, drizzle chocolate sauce over it and serve.

title: hot dog hors d'oeuvre
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 2 hours at 300° in covered casserole dish.

title: coconut wheaties cookies
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients together.
Sift dry ingredients and add; mix well.
Add Wheaties cereal.
Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes.
Drop by spoonfuls on baking sheet.

title: corned beef mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add all other ingredients. Pour in salad mold.
Refrigerate until firm.
Unmold. Garnish. Serve with crackers.

title: fish with tomato sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Oil a baking dish large enough to hold the fish and place them in a single layer in the dish.
Brush the fish lightly with the olive oil and sprinkle with the garlic. Spoon the tomato sauce over the fish, then sprinkle with the chopped parsley and salt and pepper.
Cover the dish with foil and bake for 20 minutes or until the fish flakes easily.
Serve immediately.

title: baked asparagus
directions: Layer 1 layer of asparagus.
Combine olive oil, butter and garlic mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: fig jam
directions: Mix well in a saucepan.
Boil hard for 5 minutes. Pour into sterilized jars.

title: birthday cake frosting
directions: Mix shortening, egg and almond flavoring.
Slowly add confectioners sugar.
Add milk for consistency.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add slightly beaten eggs. Mix dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Add prunes and nuts.
Mix. Pour into pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: sugar-free punch
directions: Mix together and freeze.
Before serving, let stand 2 hours. Add 2 (16 ounce) bottles diet 7-Up.
Serve slushy.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve warm or cold.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Whisk together mustard, honey, lime juice, water and lime peel.
Place chicken in shallow ovenproof casserole. Set aside 1/4 cup mustard sauce.
Pour remaining sauce on chicken. Cover and bake 20 minutes.
Uncover.
Spoon sauce from casserole on top and continue to bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until completely cooked.
Arrange chicken on lettuce leaves. Add 2 to 4 tablespoons of remaining sauce from casserole to reserved sauce and heat through.
Pour over chicken and serve. Serves 4.
Preparation time is 15 minutes. Cooking time is 30 minutes.
Contains 188 calories and 2.8 g. fat per serving.

title: wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer into crock-pot or regular pot on stove.
I simmer mine all day for the flavor to blend thoroughly.

title: turkey and stuffing quiche
directions: If using stuffing mix, prepare according to instructions. Press stuffing into greased 9 inch pie plate or quiche pan, forming a crust. Bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes. Remove from oven. In a small bowl, combine turkey and Swiss cheese; set aside. In a separate bowl, beat eggs, milk and pepper. Sprinkle turkey and cheese mixture over hot crust. Pour egg mixture over turkey. Lower oven temperature to 350 and bake quiche for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Let quiche stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate filling
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons of milk in saucepan over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese.
Add remaining milk and chocolate mixture and beat until smooth.
Fold chocolate mixture into whipped topping (Cool Whip) in a bowl.
Blend until smooth.
(Fill roll or cake.)

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Take out 1 hour before baking at 350° for 1 hour in greased dish or loaf pan.

title: crockpot baked beans
directions: Brown onion, pepper and meat. Put in crockpot and add the rest of the ingredients. Simmer on low for 8 hours.

title: veal goulash
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add celery, onion and cook until tender. Blend next 5 ingredients; pour over meat.
Cover.
Simmer 2 hours. Serve goulash over hot cooked noodles tossed with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pie shell
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut in shortening to size of small peas. Sprinkle in water, one tablespoon at a time, mixing lightly with fork until all flour is moistened (2 to 3 teaspoons water may be added if needed).
Firmly press dough into ball.
On floured surface, roll crust 1-inch larger than pie plate and about 1/8-inch thick.
Ease and fit pastry into 9-inch pie plate. Trim; flute edge.
Prick well with fork.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done. Cool.
Makes one 9-inch shell.

title: chicken nancy
directions: Place breasts in a single layer in long, shallow casserole dish, and cover with layer of cheese.
Mix sherry and soup together; pour over breasts and cheese.
Top with croutons and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, depending on thickness of breasts.
This can be made in morning and refrigerated, all except melted butter.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: walnut crunch pie
directions: Beat egg whites until fluffy, not stiff.
Add baking powder. Beat in sugar.
Fold in above mixture.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch pie dish. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and press down egg whites while hot.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour and salt, adding enough milk to mix. Add egg yolks.
Cook on low heat until this thickens, then add vanilla and pour in two 9-inch baked pie shells.

title: no-fuss meat loaf
directions: Place meat, stuffing mix, salt and pepper in a large bowl. Combine stewed tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce in blender. Add onions and green peppers and blend. Add to meat mixture.
Press into a loaf pan. Brush with catsup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: rice casserole #2(serve with beef)
directions: Simply dump first 4 ingredients in casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.
Stir once or twice during baking.
Add mushrooms last 10 minutes if desired.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients real well, then pour in an ungreased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until top becomes brown at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar.
Let set overnight.
Next day, put in strainer and drain for 3 to 4 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well. Chill.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well and cook in oven at 350° until brown and firm.

title: smoked sausage noodle bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to package directions, drain.
Melt butter in small saucepan over medium heat.
Cook and stir onion and celery until crisp and tender. Combine noodles, onion mixture, corn, sour cream, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Pour into buttered shallow 2-quart baking dish. Cut sausage into bite-size pieces.
Arrange on top of noodles, push down partially into noodles.
Bake 40 minutes or until hot. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese, pecans and garlic powder.
Form into 2 rolls. Roll in chili powder and chill overnight.
Wrap in Saran Wrap. Serve with crackers.

title: beaumont inn corn pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar together; stir into corn.
Beat eggs well; add to milk.
Stir eggs, milk and melted butter into corn.
Pour into buttered casserole; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab casserole
directions: Make a white sauce of first 3 ingredients on top of stove as follows:
Melt butter and flour and stir in milk.
Stir until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in casserole or 6 crab shells.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup, cheese, mayonnaise and onion.
Fold in eggs.
Fold in broccoli.
Put in casserole and top with crushed Ritz crackers. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, oleo and milk to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat and add Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Stir until well blended.
Pour out onto large greased pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and swirl into fudge.
Let cool and cut into squares.
Makes a lot.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix yeast and water.
Add sugar, buttermilk, and shortening. Add enough flour, a little at a time, until the mixture forms a slightly moist ball.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 35 minutes.
Time may vary depending on oven and altitude.

title: egg custard
directions: With egg beater or electric beater, beat eggs together until frothy; add 1/3 cup sugar.
Beat until well mixed.
Add milk, beat well again.
Add vanilla and salt; beat well again about 1/2 minute.
Pour into regular size pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven approximately 30 minutes or until filling is firm.

title: liver mush
directions: Cook hog jaw and liver until very tender.
Mash all other ingredients with water.
Form into desired patties.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls rolled in 2 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, then let cool for 5 minutes.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Cook this about 3 minutes, then pour over hot cake.

title: lye soap
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young.
When once selected, give your entire thoughts to preparation for domestic use.
Some insist on keeping them in a pickle, others are constantly getting them in hot water.
This makes them sour, hard to get along with and sometimes bitter.
Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened with kisses.
Wrap them in a mantle of charity. Keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion and serve with peaches and cream.
Thus prepared, they will keep for many years.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Beat the first 5 ingredients together well.
Mix together the remaining 4 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients. Pour into 2 loaf pans that are greased.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. May need to cover tops with foil for last 10 minutes to prevent burning.

title: quick peanut blossoms
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine cake mix, peanut butter, water and egg; stir by hand until dough forms.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
(If necessary refrigerate dough for easier handling.)
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes until golden brown.
Immediately top each cookie with candy kiss, pressing down firmly so cookie cracks around edge; remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: crisp crusted baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces and pat dry.
Set aside.
Beat egg and milk in bowl.
In another bowl, mix potato flakes, garlic salt and Parmesan cheese.
Roll chicken, first in egg mix, then in the potato flakes mixture.

title: lipton meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: good rolls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients until well dissolved.
Add the eggs, Crisco and flour, 2 cups at a time, beating until well blended.
Store in refrigerator for 3 or 4 days before using.
Take out amount needed and knead well on floured surface.
Roll out. Cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip in melted butter.
Fold over, if desired.
Place in buttered pan.
Let rise at least 2 hours before baking in a 400° oven.
(Melt butter in a little bowl for dipping rolls.)

title: no spice pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Beat eggs and milk; add pumpkin, then add dry ingredients.
Put into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until pie is firm.
Yields 2 pies.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix beef, rice, onion, and seasonings.
Form into balls about 1 1/2 inches.
Brown meat balls.
Add soup, cover and simmer about 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add flour; stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add broth; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce to low heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook just until thoroughly blended.
Serve immediately with crisp wheat or French bread.

title: one bowl cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Dough will be stiff.
Use a small dropper to place dough on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 375°. Makes 4 dozen.

title: pork and bean bread
directions: Mix beans in mixing bowl real well.
Add eggs, sugar and oil; mix well.
Add flour and rest of dry ingredients; stir well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drain raisins and pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pineapple cream candy
directions: Cook ingredients except vanilla until soft ball stage, then add 12 large marshmallows and 1 cup of nuts.
Beat until creamy. Pour on buttered dish.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars; beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Form into small balls. Place about 1 1/2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet, push down a bit with fork.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool slightly before removing to rack to cool.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: family favorite oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given.
Grease cookie sheets. Roll dough into balls and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen delicious cookies!
Try adding raisins or butterscotch chips, cinnamon.

title: sauerbraten
directions: A heavy 4-quart kettle or Dutch oven having a tight fitting cover will be needed.
Set out a deep 3 or 4-quart bowl, place beef round/rump in bowl.
Combine other ingredients in saucepan and heat without boiling.
Pour hot mixture over meat in bowl. Allow to cool.
Cover, set in refrigerator.
Marinate 72 hours, turning twice a day.
Remove from marinade, dry thoroughly.
Heat in kettle over low heat, 3 tablespoons butter.
Add the meat, and brown slowly on all sides over medium heat.
Slowly add 2 cups of the strained marinade.
Reserve remaining marinade for gravy. Bring liquid to boiling.
Lower heat; cover kettle and simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until fork tender.
Remove to warm platter and keep warm.
Pour cooking liquid from kettle and set aside for gravy.

title: black olive bo-zos(hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Spread olives, onions and cheeses in thin layer over halved muffins.
Bake in flat baking sheet at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut each half in half and serve warm.
One dozen serves 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, onion, egg, margarine and milk.
Layer in casserole dish with cracker crumbs.
Cook until set (350° for about 30 minutes).
Top with cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: oatmeal coconut cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in one bowl.
Roll in balls. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: quick and easy lemon cheesecake
directions: Prepare pudding mix with milk.
Blend in softened cream cheese.
Mix in lemon flavoring or juice.
Fold in cool whip. Pour into pie shell and let set for at least 4 hours.
Top with cool whip, if desired, and sprinkle on top a little lemon zest.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash. Salt and boil squash.
Meanwhile, chop onion and grate cheese. Drain squash. Mix onion and squash in mixing bowl. Crush Ritz crackers with hand into mixture.
Add salt, pepper, celery salt, garlic powder and 1 egg.
Stir. Layer 3/4-inch of mixture into casserole dish.
Layer cheese. Layer mixture and cheese 2 more times.
Spoon butter on top.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake 30 to 45 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except crumbs.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with crushed corn flake crumbs.
Run back in oven for a few minutes.

title: lemon filled cake
directions: Mix according to package directions.
Pour into jelly roll pan (11 x 15-inch).
Bake for 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Check after 20 minutes.
Cool cake thoroughly.
While cake is cooling, mix lemon pudding.
When pudding thickens, beat in cream cheese, softened.
Pour this mixture over cooled cake.
Top with Dream Whip or Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with finely chopped nuts (optional).

title: country potato salad
directions: Mix and toss gently.

title: french onion bread
directions: Slice bread and coat both sides of slices with mixture of sour cream, butter and salt.
Dip slices in crushed onions.
Form into original loaf.
Bake in foil at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in halves.
Remove seeds and stringy portions. Brush cut surfaces with salad oil.
Arrange cut side down in baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Let rest for 5 minutes.
Pat out dough onto cookie sheet with sides.
Complete with sauce and favorite toppings.
Bake at 425°.

title: baker's martha washington candies
directions: Melt chocolate with butter in saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly.
Blend in vanilla, sugar and cream.
Chill about 30 minutes, then shape into small balls and roll in coconut, chocolate sprinkles or finely chopped nuts.
Store in the refrigerator.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen candies.

title: tasty cake-cake
directions: Add first five ingredients; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.

title: swiss steak supreme
directions: Remove all fat from steak.
Mix first four ingredients and beat into both sides of steak.
Make sure steak is well covered with mixture.
Sear until brown in hot skillet.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients (except wine). Cover and place in oven.
Simmer at 375° for 2 hours.
Half hour before serving, add 1/2 cup Port wine.
Serve over noodles.

title: tomato and broccoli bake
directions: Cook macaroni as directed until tender and drained.
Set aside.
In a 3-quart saucepan cook onion and garlic in hot margarine.
Add broccoli, tomatoes, parsley, bouillon, salt, oregano and basil.
Bring to boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Stir in macaroni and 1/2 cup of the cheese. Add thawed broccoli if not using fresh.
Transfer to 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake covered in 375° oven for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake uncovered for 5 more minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: 1 minute oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, margarine, cocoa and salt for 2 minutes after a full boil.
Stir in oatmeal, flavoring and peanut butter.
Drop with spoon on wax paper.

title: burritos enchilada style
directions: Brown ground beef with green chilies and onion.
Drain fat. Put 1 tablespoon ground beef and a pinch of cheese in each tortilla.
Roll up and sit side by side in oblong baking pan. Pour sauce over shells.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and return to oven until cheese has melted.

title: sausage in a sauce
directions: Saute
onions
and
bell pepper in butter until tender. Brown sausages.
Add
soup, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar and mustard.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and warm in crock-pot on low all day.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in large bowl as listed.
Mix Miracle Whip, Parmesan cheese and sugar.
Place on top of ingredients in bowl.
Store in refrigerator 2 to 4 hours or overnight.

title: cracked corn and cheese squares
directions: Pre-heat oven to 400 degrees F. Grease an 8 inch square baking dish with butter.
Stir in cheese, corn, and scallions into cornbread muffin batter.
Pour mixture into baking dish and bake at 400 degrees for approximately 15-18 minutes until golden brown.

title: liver louisiana
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; remove from pan, drain and crumble. Add liver, onion, green pepper, garlic and chili powder; cook until liver is browned.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until tender.
Stir often. Makes 4 servings.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.

Grease and flour two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans. Line the bottom with parchment paper. Cream the butter and 2 cups of the granulated sugar in the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the paddle attachment for about 5 minutes or until light and fluffy.
With the mixer on medium speed, beat in the eggs, one at a time, and the orange zest.
In a large bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In another bowl, combine 1/4 cup of the orange juice, the buttermilk and vanilla.
Add the flour and buttermilk mixtures alternately to the batter, beginning and ending with the flour.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and celery.
Drain grease; add other ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
The amount of ketchup may vary depending upon what consistency you want.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine cake and pudding mixes. Add oil, water and juice.

Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Add almond flavoring. Fold in poppy seed. Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans coated with cinnamon-sugar mixture. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Remove from pan and sprinkle top with more cinnamon-sugar mixture. Do not overbake!

title: reuben dip
directions: Heat all ingredients in a small pan over low heat.
Thin with milk if too thick.
Serve hot with vegetables or crackers.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except poppy seed. Fold poppy seed in slowly.
Grease and flour 4 small foil pans.
Fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: In a bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add egg, milk and corn.
Stir just until mixed. In a deep fat fryer, heat oil to 375°.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Allow to cool slightly and roll in confectioners sugar if desired.
Serve immediately with fried chicken, ham or sausage.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: tuna salad loaf
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over 1/2 cup of water.
Let stand 5 minutes. Stir in cold water, salt, celery salt, paprika and lemon juice over low heat; blend well.
Remove from heat and add mayonnaise, celery, pickle relish and tuna.
Pour into oiled mold.
Chill until firm.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Parboil squash and drain.
In 3-quart greased casserole dish, arrange layers of squash, cheese, onions, peppers and soup. Sprinkle on Cream of Wheat.
Bake in covered dish 35 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Add chocolate to milk and heat.
When melted, beat to blend. Combine sugar, salt and flour and add to mixture and cook until thick.
Add to egg yolks, stirring vigorously.
Cook two minutes longer.
Add vanilla and butter; mix.
Pour into baked pie shell. Make meringue with leftover egg whites and spread on top, then brown in oven.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla, beating well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Chill dough for one hour.

title: beer hot dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over hot dogs in skillet.
Cook about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix pineapple and juice with dry pistachio pudding.
Add marshmallows,
nuts and topping.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
